{"id":"orch-go-0vscq","title":"Epic: Friction Loop Precision \u0026 Automation","description":"Improve the orch learn system to reduce noise and automate the path from detected friction to root-cause resolution. Focus on semantic filtering, skill-context cross-referencing, and automated triage for critical gaps.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"epic","created_at":"2026-01-07T20:39:30.19107-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-17T15:08:53.724119-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-17T15:08:53.724119-08:00","close_reason":"Epic Complete: Noise reduction and automation achieved.","labels":["triage:review"]}
{"id":"orch-go-0vscq.4","title":"Audit recurring gap patterns for semantic filtering","description":"Analyze the 59 recurring patterns in orch learn. Categorize them into 'Systemic' (KB/Skill gaps) and 'Task Noise' (Issue IDs, Phase names). This data will inform the design of a semantic filter.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-07T20:39:42.507504-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-07T21:14:31.580885-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-07T21:14:31.580885-08:00","close_reason":"Audited recurring gap patterns; found semantically related queries treated separately. Recommended template-based pattern matching. Created follow-up issue orch-go-5mm7q."}
{"id":"orch-go-0vscq.5","title":"Implement Task Noise filter in orch learn","description":"Add logic to the learning loop to automatically ignore gap patterns that appear to be task-specific noise (e.g., matching issue ID patterns or phase names).","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-01-07T20:39:42.84593-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-17T12:28:41.721717-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-17T12:28:41.721717-08:00","close_reason":"Implemented isTaskNoise() filter in FindRecurringGaps(), all tests passing (112/112), SYNTHESIS.md created","labels":["triage:ready","triage:review"]}
{"id":"orch-go-0vscq.6","title":"Design Skill-Execution Bridge for friction tracing","description":"Investigate how to cross-reference tool failures with the SKILL.md guidance provided in the spawn context. This will allow the system to identify when incorrect documentation is causing friction.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-07T20:39:43.014219-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-16T11:39:50.077007-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-16T11:39:50.077007-08:00","close_reason":"Phase: Complete - Designed 4-component Skill-Execution Bridge (parser, annotator, analyzer, reporter) to map tool failures to skill guidance gaps. Investigation file and SYNTHESIS.md committed.","labels":["triage:ready","triage:review"]}
{"id":"orch-go-0vscq.7","title":"Implement 800-line bloat gate in orch learn","description":"Operationalize the 800-line gate model by adding proactive bloat detection to the learning loop.\n\n1. Define 'GapTypeBloat' in 'pkg/spawn/gap.go'.\n2. Add a proactive scanner to 'orch learn' that identifies project files \u003e 800 lines.\n3. Record detections as 'GapEvent's in the gap tracker.\n4. Update 'pkg/spawn/learning.go' to suggest creating 'type: gate' beads issues for identified hotspots.\n5. The 'gate' issue should block subsequent implementation tasks for that file via 'bd depend'.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-01-17T12:17:08.293236-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-17T12:23:49.073401-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-17T12:23:49.073401-08:00","close_reason":"Phase: Complete - Designed 800-line bloat gate as third hotspot type in orch hotspot with severity-based recommendations. Added feat-049 for implementation.","labels":["triage:ready"]}
{"id":"orch-go-0vscq.8","title":"Implement bloat-size hotspot type in orch hotspot","description":"Implementation of feat-049 as designed by the architect in .kb/investigations/2026-01-17-inv-design-800-line-bloat-gate.md.\n\n1. Add analyzeBloatFiles() to 'cmd/orch/hotspot.go'.\n2. Use existing shouldCountFile() exclusions.\n3. Add --bloat-threshold flag (default: 800).\n4. Implement severity-based recommendations:\n   - 800-1500 lines: Refer to code-extraction-patterns guide.\n   - \u003e1500 lines: Recommend architect redesign.\n5. Integrate with 'orch hotspot' display.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-01-17T12:24:00.6857-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-17T12:33:02.086768-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-17T12:33:02.086768-08:00","close_reason":"Phase: Complete - Bloat-size hotspot type implemented with severity-based recommendations. 31 files detected at 800-line threshold. MODERATE (800-1500): extraction guide reference. CRITICAL (\u003e1500): architect redesign. All tests passing, SYNTHESIS.md created.","labels":["triage:ready"]}
{"id":"orch-go-0w71z","title":"OpenCode Fork: Create Porting Map for 8 Orchestration Features","description":"Map the 8 custom orchestration features from the current OpenCode fork to the new upstream structure (Jan 16 refactor). Target new route files like routes/session.ts and routes/permission.ts. Ref: 2026-01-17-inv-analyze-divergence-opencode-fork-upstream.md","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-17T23:47:00.367831-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-17T23:54:41.19554-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-17T23:54:41.19554-08:00","close_reason":"Phase: Complete - Created comprehensive porting map for 8 OpenCode fork features to upstream. Investigation: .kb/investigations/2026-01-17-design-create-porting-map-opencode-fork.md"}
