{"id":"orch-go-10iv","title":"Investigate: Auto-generate docs from orch --help output","description":"Meta-gap investigation raised question: can we auto-generate documentation from --help text to prevent drift?\n\nOptions to explore:\n1. orch --help-doc command that outputs markdown\n2. Build step that generates docs/ from help text\n3. orch lint that validates all commands are documented somewhere\n\nThis would prevent the systematic documentation drift problem.\n\nSee: .kb/investigations/2025-12-28-inv-critical-meta-gap-orch-features.md (Unexplored Questions)","status":"closed","priority":3,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-12-28T12:36:35.480967-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-28T13:15:50.034129-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-28T13:15:50.034129-08:00","close_reason":"Investigation committed. Recommended orch lint --docs validation command. Leave it Better: kn decide recorded for drift solution choice.","labels":["triage:ready"]}
