{"id":"orch-go-12yx","title":"Track fix attempts on issues - surface retry patterns","description":"When an issue takes multiple attempts to fix (like orch-go-k5lp streaming dedup - 3 attempts), that's a process signal we should capture and learn from.\n\nPossible implementation:\n1. Add 'attempts' field to beads issues (increment on reopen or related spawn)\n2. Track which issues get reopened or spawn follow-up fixes\n3. Surface patterns: which skills/problem-types have high retry rates?\n4. Feed into orch learn - 'this type of bug often takes multiple attempts'\n\nThis connects to the System Learning Loop - we track context gaps, we should also track fix reliability gaps.\n\nRelated: orch-go-k5lp (3 attempts), possibly others we haven't noticed.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-12-25T20:53:06.112902-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-26T22:03:24.628084-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-26T22:03:24.628084-08:00","close_reason":"Added fix attempt tracking: pkg/verify/attempts.go with FixAttemptStats, spawn warning for retry patterns, orch retries command. All tests passing.","labels":["skill:architect","triage:ready","triage:review"]}
{"id":"orch-go-138x","title":"Spawned agents skip SYNTHESIS.md creation","description":"Feature-impl and architect agents complete work but don't create SYNTHESIS.md in workspace. Observed: workspace only contains SPAWN_CONTEXT.md after Phase: Complete. orch complete fails verification. Likely cause: skill doesn't require synthesis, or agent deviates from skill guidance. Evidence: skillc-rys (feature-impl) and skillc-pax (architect) both missing synthesis. Both had to be --force completed.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-12-21T02:44:36.625983-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-21T02:55:54.849988-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-21T02:55:54.849988-08:00"}
