{"id":"orch-go-18t3i","title":"triage:ready on epic should cascade to children or daemon should infer","description":"**Problem:** When labeling an epic `triage:ready`, the intent is 'process this epic now'. But the daemon only spawns individual issues, not epics. The label doesn't propagate to children.\n\n**Current behavior:**\n```\nbd label add epic-xyz triage:ready\norch daemon preview\n# Shows: epic-xyz type 'epic' not spawnable\n# Children still show: missing label 'triage:ready'\n```\n\n**Expected behavior (option A - cascade):**\n```\nbd label add epic-xyz triage:ready --cascade\n# Adds triage:ready to all unblocked children\n```\n\n**Expected behavior (option B - daemon infers):**\n```\nbd label add epic-xyz triage:ready\norch daemon preview\n# Daemon sees epic is triage:ready\n# Auto-includes unblocked children in spawn queue\n```\n\n**User mental model:**\n'Label the epic ready for the daemon' means 'ensure the entire epic is processed now' - not 'label this one non-spawnable thing'.\n\n**Related:**\n- orch-go-tuofe: Children shouldn't have blocking dep on parent (separate bug)\n- kb-8294e7: Constraint about --parent creating blocking deps\n\n**Design question:**\nShould this be a beads feature (--cascade flag) or daemon behavior (infer from epic label)? Probably daemon - beads shouldn't know about triage workflow.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-01-08T08:18:00.353119-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-08T08:53:25.968691-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-08T08:53:25.968691-08:00","close_reason":"Implemented daemon epic child inference - children of triage:ready epics are now auto-included in spawn queue"}
