{"id":"orch-go-1ni4","title":"Consolidate artifact templates into kb-cli","description":"## Problem\n\nArtifact templates are fragmented across multiple locations:\n- orch-knowledge/skills/src/worker/{skill}/templates/\n- ~/.claude/skills/worker/{skill}/templates/\n- ~/.kb/templates/\n- ~/.orch/templates/\n- kb-cli hardcoded defaults\n\nThis causes:\n- Drift between copies (e.g., investigation template has D.E.K.N. in some places, not others)\n- Confusion about which is authoritative\n- Templates in skill directories that skillc doesn't manage\n\n## Solution\n\n1. **kb-cli owns artifact templates** (investigation, decision, guide, research)\n   - Update hardcoded defaults in kb-cli with current best versions\n   - User overrides at ~/.kb/templates/\n   - Add `kb create research` command if missing\n\n2. **Remove templates from skill directories**\n   - Delete orch-knowledge/skills/src/worker/investigation/templates/\n   - Delete orch-knowledge/skills/src/worker/research/templates/\n   - Delete ~/.claude/skills/worker/*/templates/\n\n3. **orch-go owns spawn-time templates** (already correct)\n   - SYNTHESIS.md, SPAWN_CONTEXT.md, etc. stay in .orch/templates/\n\n4. **Sync ~/.kb/templates/ with kb-cli defaults**\n   - Or remove user overrides if they match defaults\n\n## Scope\n\n| Template | Current Locations | Target |\n|----------|------------------|--------|\n| investigation.md | 5 places | kb-cli only |\n| research.md | 2 places | kb-cli only |\n| decision | 2 places | kb-cli only |\n| guide | 1 place | kb-cli only |\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] kb-cli hardcoded templates updated with D.E.K.N. + structured uncertainty\n- [ ] `kb create research` works (add if missing)\n- [ ] Templates removed from skill directories\n- [ ] Skills reference `kb create` instead of embedding templates\n- [ ] ~/.kb/templates/ cleaned up or synced","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-12-22T11:20:57.484421-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-03T14:17:24.126301-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-03T14:17:24.126301-08:00","close_reason":"Abandoned agent from Dec - force closing stale work"}
{"id":"orch-go-1pxkk","title":"Install and configure opencode-openai-codex-auth plugin","description":"Install the OpenAI OAuth plugin for OpenCode to enable ChatGPT Pro subscription access.\n\nSteps:\n1. Run: npx -y opencode-openai-codex-auth@latest\n2. Configure ~/.config/opencode/opencode.jsonc\n3. Run: opencode auth login (OAuth flow)\n4. Verify: opencode run 'hello world' --model=openai/gpt-5.2\n\nReference: https://numman-ali.github.io/opencode-openai-codex-auth/\nContext: .kb/investigations/2026-01-21-inv-research-openai-potential-partnership-opencode.md","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-20T18:19:28.173887-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-21T22:04:33.136837235Z","closed_at":"2026-01-21T22:04:33.136837235Z","close_reason":"Completed: OpenAI plugin installed and configured"}
