{"id":"orch-go-1qgwg","title":"opencode attach --session fails with 'Session not found' for valid sessions","description":"## Evidence\nSession exists via API:\n```\ncurl -s http://localhost:4096/session/ses_46b686692ffeH8EZVz6b2PCXkH | jq\n{id: 'ses_46b686692ffeH8EZVz6b2PCXkH', title: '...', status: null}\n```\n\nBut opencode attach fails:\n```\nopencode attach http://localhost:4096 --session ses_46b686692ffeH8EZVz6b2PCXkH\nSession not found: ses_46b686692ffeH8EZVz6b2PCXkH\n```\n\n## Impact\nCannot attach TUI to headless spawns - breaks the resumability promise.\n\n## Versions\n- opencode: 1.1.2\n- Server: localhost:4096","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-01-06T10:41:42.342442-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-06T11:13:18.955083-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-06T11:13:18.955083-08:00","close_reason":"Fixed: Session.getGlobal() searches across all projects for cross-directory attach"}
{"id":"orch-go-1qjvb","title":"Diagnose: Investigation skill has 29% completion rate","description":"orch stats shows investigation skill: 31 spawned, 9 completed, 4 abandoned (29% rate). This is the lowest completion rate of production skills. Investigate: Are investigations scoping too broadly? Are they hitting context limits? Are they failing to produce artifacts? Check events.jsonl for investigation abandonment patterns. Skill: investigation","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-06T16:10:22.201082-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-06T19:04:43.36632-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-06T19:04:43.36632-08:00","close_reason":"Investigation finds two root causes for 29% completion rate: (1) 45% test spawn pollution, (2) 37.5% of real work has SYNTHESIS.md but no agent.completed event recorded. True completion rate is ~94%. Recommendations: filter test spawns from stats, investigate completion event recording bug."}
{"id":"orch-go-1qol3","title":"[orch-go] investigation: Workers are attempting to restart orch servers ...","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-07T07:32:11.145798-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-07T07:38:40.056159-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-07T07:38:40.056159-08:00","close_reason":"Phase: Complete - Investigation found current behavior is correct. Workers receive project server instructions (orch servers) for UI skills only. orch serve (dashboard) and daemon are correctly separate (launchd-managed, orchestrator-only). No changes needed."}
{"id":"orch-go-1qwt","title":"Implement auto-switch account when capacity is low","description":"Before spawning, check current account capacity. If \u003c20% remaining on 5-hour limit, automatically switch to healthier account. Logic: 1) GetCurrentCapacity() 2) If low, iterate saved accounts with GetAccountCapacity() 3) Switch to healthiest account 4) Log switch for visibility. Account package has capacity functions but no auto-switch orchestration.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-12-26T09:58:40.617758-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-26T15:04:13.718275-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-26T15:04:13.718275-08:00","close_reason":"Auto-switch was already implemented in account.AutoSwitchIfNeeded. Added comprehensive unit tests for threshold logic, headroom calculation, and decision scenarios. Tests validate the 80% 5-hour threshold behavior (20% remaining triggers switch).","labels":["P1","skill:feature-impl","triage:ready"]}
{"id":"orch-go-1rk4z","title":"Add mode field to registry schema","description":"Extend Agent struct with 'mode' field. Track tmux_window (claude mode) and session_id (opencode mode). Update registry read/write to preserve mode info.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-09T11:55:43.817668-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-09T12:20:15.617396-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-09T12:20:15.617396-08:00","close_reason":"Extended Agent struct with Mode and TmuxWindow fields; updated Register method for persistence. Verified with unit tests."}
{"id":"orch-go-1slp0","title":"Test: GPT-5.2 worker via OpenCode","description":"Test GPT-5.2 as headless worker. Task: Investigate how backend selection priority works in orch spawn - find the code and explain the priority order.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-23T17:46:05.31259-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-23T23:29:53.95593-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-23T23:29:53.95593-08:00","close_reason":"GPT-5.2 worker tests complete. Models struggle with Claude-tuned spawn context - task drift, idle loops. Staying Claude-focused."}
