{"id":"orch-go-20917","title":"[orch-go] feature-impl: Update session hooks and skills to use orch fro...","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-26T10:18:58.653758-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-26T10:40:31.843983-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-26T10:40:31.843983-08:00","comments":[{"id":1,"issue_id":"orch-go-20917","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Planning - Reviewing frontier.go and files to update","created_at":"2026-01-26T10:19:11.644365-08:00"},{"id":2,"issue_id":"orch-go-20917","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Scope: 1. Update load-orchestration-context.py hook to use orch frontier --json 2. Update orchestrator skill template session checkpoints 3. Update orch-commands.md reference 4. Update daemon-workflow.md reference 5. Update meta-orchestrator-interface.md reference 6. Update meta-orchestrator skill template 7. Run skillc deploy","created_at":"2026-01-26T10:20:34.657951-08:00"},{"id":3,"issue_id":"orch-go-20917","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Complete - Updated hook (load-orchestration-context.py) to use orch frontier --json, updated orchestrator and meta-orchestrator skill templates with orch frontier references, updated reference files (orch-commands.md, daemon-workflow.md, meta-orchestrator-interface.md), and deployed all skills via skillc. Tests: orch frontier --json returns valid JSON, deployed skill contains orch frontier references.","created_at":"2026-01-26T10:27:10.762068-08:00"}]}
{"id":"orch-go-20918","title":"Integrate Qwen3-Max into orch-go model system","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-01-26T10:27:55.427305-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-26T10:40:11.900543-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-26T10:40:11.900543-08:00","comments":[{"id":1,"issue_id":"orch-go-20918","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Planning - Reading model system and Qwen investigation for integration approach","created_at":"2026-01-26T10:33:52.44822-08:00"},{"id":2,"issue_id":"orch-go-20918","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Scope: 1. Add qwen/qwen-max/qwen-thinking aliases to Aliases map 2. Add qwen model ID inference in Resolve() 3. Update ListAliases() 4. Add test cases","created_at":"2026-01-26T10:34:25.197397-08:00"},{"id":3,"issue_id":"orch-go-20918","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Implementing - Adding Qwen3-Max aliases and model inference","created_at":"2026-01-26T10:34:33.620851-08:00"},{"id":4,"issue_id":"orch-go-20918","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Complete - Added Qwen3-Max model aliases (qwen, qwen-max, qwen3, qwen3-max, qwen-thinking) to pkg/model with alibaba provider. Tests: go test ./pkg/model/... - ok 0.004s","created_at":"2026-01-26T10:36:37.856256-08:00"}]}
{"id":"orch-go-20919","title":"Run model comparison test: Qwen3-Max vs DeepSeek vs Claude","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-26T10:28:00.05625-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-26T10:56:33.467826-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-26T10:56:33.467826-08:00","dependencies":[{"issue_id":"orch-go-20919","depends_on_id":"orch-go-20918","type":"blocks","created_at":"0001-01-01T00:00:00Z"}],"comments":[{"id":1,"issue_id":"orch-go-20919","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Planning - Setting up model comparison test infrastructure","created_at":"2026-01-26T10:42:33.259801-08:00"},{"id":2,"issue_id":"orch-go-20919","author":"dylanconlin","text":"investigation_path: /Users/dylanconlin/Documents/personal/orch-go/.kb/investigations/2026-01-26-inv-run-model-comparison-test-qwen3.md","created_at":"2026-01-26T10:42:39.917974-08:00"},{"id":3,"issue_id":"orch-go-20919","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Complete - Ran comparative tests (coding, reasoning, tool use) across Qwen3-Max, DeepSeek V3, and Claude Sonnet. Key findings: DeepSeek 18-32x cheaper but fails tool use (1/2 calls); Qwen3-Max 2.4x slower than Claude; current model strategy validated. Investigation at .kb/investigations/2026-01-26-inv-run-model-comparison-test-qwen3.md","created_at":"2026-01-26T10:51:13.859931-08:00"}]}
{"id":"orch-go-20920","title":"Daemon crashes on beads foreign key violation during JSONL hydration","repro":"1. Run orch daemon (via launchd). 2. Observe daemon.log shows 'foreign key violation in imported data: table=dirty_issues rowid=1 parent=issues'. 3. Daemon fails to poll orch-go project, returns exit status 1.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-01-26T10:35:26.271295-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-26T12:19:17.713766-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-26T12:19:17.713766-08:00"}
{"id":"orch-go-20921","title":"Explore native Claude skill-loading integration","description":"Future work: Identify if and how we can integrate skill-loading, kb context, and project awareness into Claude's native TeammateTool/swarm workflow. See investigation: .kb/investigations/2026-01-25-inv-investigate-claude-code-native-swarm.md","status":"open","priority":4,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-26T12:24:34.29125-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-26T12:24:34.29125-08:00"}
{"id":"orch-go-20922","title":"Test CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR fingerprint isolation for worker spawns","description":"## Context\n\nInvestigation `orch-go-20910` found that fingerprint isolation doesn't require Docker - simply pointing `CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR` to a fresh directory creates a new statsig stable_id.\n\n## Current State\n\n- Workers currently use Claude Code CLI (macOS) on single Max account\n- Docker backend disabled (second Max account cancelled)\n- Request-rate throttling is per-fingerprint (statsig stable_id)\n- Weekly usage quota is per-account (unaffected by fingerprint)\n\n## Test Plan\n\n1. Spawn worker with `CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR=~/.claude-test-1`\n2. Verify fresh `statsig.stable_id` is created\n3. Test whether this bypasses request-rate throttling\n4. Compare overhead vs Docker approach\n\n## Implementation Path\n\nIf test succeeds:\n- Add `--backend config-dir` or similar to orch spawn\n- Generate fresh config dir per spawn: `~/.claude-spawn-{beads-id}`\n- Much simpler than Docker: just env var + mkdir\n\n## References\n\n- `.kb/investigations/2026-01-25-inv-investigate-claude-code-native-swarm.md` Finding 5-6\n- sneakpeek uses this pattern: `CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR=~/.claude-sneakpeek/{variant}/config/`","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-26T12:48:58.225387-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-26T12:48:58.225387-08:00"}
{"id":"orch-go-20923","title":"[orch-go] investigation: Clone https://github.com/clawdbot/clawdbot to ~...","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-26T12:56:13.839592-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-26T13:06:26.308534-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-26T13:06:26.308534-08:00","comments":[{"id":1,"issue_id":"orch-go-20923","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Planning - Cloning clawdbot repo and analyzing codebase structure","created_at":"2026-01-26T12:56:26.537681-08:00"},{"id":2,"issue_id":"orch-go-20923","author":"dylanconlin","text":"investigation_path: /Users/dylanconlin/Documents/personal/orch-go/.kb/investigations/2026-01-26-inv-clawdbot-analysis.md","created_at":"2026-01-26T12:56:48.603157-08:00"},{"id":3,"issue_id":"orch-go-20923","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Complete - Cloned clawdbot and analyzed codebase. Key findings: Uses Pi agent runtime (mariozechner/pi-*) with standard OAuth/API key auth (no Opus gate workaround), SKILL.md format similar to orch-go, gateway-centric architecture for multi-channel messaging (WhatsApp, Telegram, etc.) vs. orch-go's CLI wrapper approach.","created_at":"2026-01-26T12:58:54.990072-08:00"}]}
{"id":"orch-go-20924","title":"[orch-go] investigation: Clone https://github.com/mariozechner/pi-ai to ...","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-26T13:06:07.04017-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-26T13:17:41.019984-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-26T13:17:41.019984-08:00","comments":[{"id":1,"issue_id":"orch-go-20924","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Planning - Cloning pi-ai repo and analyzing Anthropic OAuth auth","created_at":"2026-01-26T13:06:19.221302-08:00"},{"id":2,"issue_id":"orch-go-20924","author":"dylanconlin","text":"investigation_path: /Users/dylanconlin/Documents/personal/orch-go/.kb/investigations/2026-01-26-inv-analyze-pi-ai-anthropic-oauth.md","created_at":"2026-01-26T13:06:45.2409-08:00"},{"id":3,"issue_id":"orch-go-20924","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Complete - Analyzed pi-ai (badlogic/pi-mono) Anthropic OAuth implementation. Key finding: third-party tools CAN leverage Claude Max subscriptions by mimicking Claude Code identity (stealth mode). No Opus-specific fingerprinting exists. Investigation documents OAuth flow, stealth mode requirements, and tool naming conventions. See .kb/investigations/2026-01-26-inv-analyze-pi-ai-anthropic-oauth.md","created_at":"2026-01-26T13:09:21.201286-08:00"}]}
{"id":"orch-go-20925","title":"Implement stealth mode in OpenCode for Claude Max OAuth","description":"Add stealth mode to Dylan's OpenCode fork when OAuth tokens are detected (sk-ant-oat prefix). This enables Max subscription access from spawned agents while maintaining dashboard visibility.\n\n## Implementation Requirements (from pi-ai analysis)\n\n### 1. Detect OAuth Tokens\n```go\nfunc isOAuthToken(apiKey string) bool {\n    return strings.Contains(apiKey, \"sk-ant-oat\")\n}\n```\n\n### 2. Set Stealth Mode Headers\nWhen OAuth token detected, include:\n```\nuser-agent: claude-cli/{version} (external, cli)\nx-app: cli\nanthropic-dangerous-direct-browser-access: true\nanthropic-beta: claude-code-{date},oauth-2025-04-20\n```\n\n### 3. Include Identity System Prompt\nCritical - this was the missing piece in Jan 9 workarounds:\n```json\n{\n  \"system\": [{\n    \"type\": \"text\",\n    \"text\": \"You are Claude Code, Anthropic's official CLI for Claude.\",\n    \"cache_control\": { \"type\": \"ephemeral\" }\n  }]\n}\n```\n\n### 4. Tool Name Normalization (Optional)\nIf using tools matching Claude Code names, normalize to PascalCase:\n- bash → Bash, read → Read, write → Write\n\n## Why This Matters\n- Restores dashboard visibility (lost when we switched to Claude CLI backend)\n- Enables Max subscription from OpenCode-spawned agents\n- Leverages existing orch-go/OpenCode integration\n- pi-ai has proven this approach stable for months\n\n## References\n- Decision: .kb/decisions/2026-01-26-claude-max-oauth-stealth-mode-viable.md\n- Investigation: .kb/investigations/2026-01-26-inv-analyze-pi-ai-anthropic-oauth.md\n- pi-ai implementation: packages/ai/src/providers/anthropic.ts (badlogic/pi-mono)\n- Version tracking: https://cchistory.mariozechner.at/\n\n## Location\nDylan's OpenCode fork: ~/Documents/personal/opencode","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-01-26T13:25:54.02423-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-26T16:10:10.121325-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-26T16:10:10.121325-08:00"}
{"id":"orch-go-20926","title":"OpenCode stealth mode: fix model selection and OAuth priority","description":"## Context\nImplementing stealth mode for Claude Max OAuth in OpenCode (orch-go-20925). The stealth headers are implemented but testing revealed issues.\n\n## Issues Found\n\n### 1. OAuth token not being used (FIXED in working tree)\nThe original code only checked for auth.type === 'api', missing OAuth tokens. Fixed but not committed.\n\n### 2. Model selection not working via API (NOT FIXED)\nSession.create schema doesn't accept model field. Sessions fall back to default (DeepSeek) regardless of requested model.\n\n## Current State\n- Stealth headers: complete\n- Tool name normalization: complete  \n- OAuth token priority fix: in working tree, uncommitted\n- Model selection fix: NOT done\n\n## Files Changed (uncommitted)\n- packages/opencode/src/provider/provider.ts - OAuth priority fix\n\n## Next Steps\n1. Commit OAuth priority fix\n2. Fix model selection in API\n3. Test end-to-end with OAuth token\n\n## References\n- Parent: orch-go-20925\n- Decision: .kb/decisions/2026-01-26-claude-max-oauth-stealth-mode-viable.md","repro":"1. Create session via API with model param: curl -X POST .../session -d '{\"model\": \"anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929\"}'\n2. Send message to session\n3. Response uses deepseek instead of anthropic","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-01-26T14:01:00.475232-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-26T16:10:10.18502-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-26T16:10:10.18502-08:00"}
{"id":"orch-go-20927","title":"[opencode] investigation: Investigate OpenCode model selection architectu...","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-26T14:11:51.918337-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-26T14:31:22.590568-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-26T14:31:22.590568-08:00","comments":[{"id":1,"issue_id":"orch-go-20927","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Planning - Investigating OpenCode model selection architecture and API schema","created_at":"2026-01-26T14:12:15.98561-08:00"},{"id":2,"issue_id":"orch-go-20927","author":"dylanconlin","text":"investigation_path: /Users/dylanconlin/Documents/personal/opencode/.kb/investigations/2026-01-26-inv-investigate-opencode-model-selection-architecture.md","created_at":"2026-01-26T14:12:16.116567-08:00"},{"id":3,"issue_id":"orch-go-20927","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Complete - Documented OpenCode model selection architecture. Key finding: model param is per-prompt (not per-session), stored on user messages. Fix for orch-go: pass model in SendMessageAsync instead of CreateSession. Investigation: opencode/.kb/investigations/2026-01-26-inv-investigate-opencode-model-selection-architecture.md","created_at":"2026-01-26T14:16:21.541143-08:00"}]}
{"id":"orch-go-20928","title":"[TEST] Verify stealth mode: Claude should respond with model info","description":"Spawn test for stealth mode verification.\n\n**Task:** Report which model you are and confirm you can see this message.\n\n**Expected behavior if stealth mode works:**\n- Claude responds (not blocked)\n- Reports being Claude (Sonnet/Opus)\n- Can use tools normally\n\n**If stealth mode fails:**\n- Request blocked by Anthropic\n- Wrong model responds (DeepSeek/Gemini)\n- Missing capabilities\n\nJust respond with your model identity and exit. No investigation needed.","status":"closed","priority":3,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-26T14:38:16.037631-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-26T15:11:22.117533-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-26T15:11:22.117533-08:00","comments":[{"id":1,"issue_id":"orch-go-20928","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Planning - Verifying model identity and stealth mode operation","created_at":"2026-01-26T14:39:46.368299-08:00"},{"id":2,"issue_id":"orch-go-20928","author":"dylanconlin","text":"investigation_path: /Users/dylanconlin/Documents/personal/orch-go/.kb/investigations/2026-01-26-inv-report-model-you-confirm-stealth.md","created_at":"2026-01-26T14:40:00.762301-08:00"},{"id":3,"issue_id":"orch-go-20928","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Complete - Model verified as Claude 3.5 Sonnet (new), stealth mode fully operational with all infrastructure working (beads tracking, workspace isolation, kb integration, context loading)","created_at":"2026-01-26T14:41:36.747626-08:00"},{"id":4,"issue_id":"orch-go-20928","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Leave it Better: Straightforward verification, no new knowledge to externalize via kb quick","created_at":"2026-01-26T14:41:41.857171-08:00"}]}
{"id":"orch-go-20929","title":"[orch-go] feature-impl: Implement domain-based ecosystem filtering for ...","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-26T16:00:35.808802-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-26T21:21:34.311783-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-26T21:21:34.311783-08:00","comments":[{"id":1,"issue_id":"orch-go-20929","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Planning - Reading plan at ~/.claude/plans/buzzing-wobbling-fairy.md and analyzing codebase structure","created_at":"2026-01-26T16:01:36.631762-08:00"},{"id":2,"issue_id":"orch-go-20929","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Scope: 1. Add DetectDomain and GetEcosystemRepos functions to ecosystem.go 2. Add RunKBContextCheckWithDomain to kbcontext.go 3. Pass domain from spawn_validation.go 4. Add Domain field to config.go 5. Register scs-special-projects in kb projects","created_at":"2026-01-26T16:01:54.012281-08:00"},{"id":3,"issue_id":"orch-go-20929","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Implementing - Starting with ecosystem.go domain detection","created_at":"2026-01-26T16:02:00.72725-08:00"},{"id":4,"issue_id":"orch-go-20929","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Complete - Implemented domain-based ecosystem filtering for KB context. Tests: go build ./... - PASS. Changes: pkg/spawn/ecosystem.go (domain detection + ecosystem maps), pkg/spawn/kbcontext.go (domain-aware filtering), cmd/orch/spawn_validation.go (pass domain), pkg/config/config.go (Domain field). Also registered scs-special-projects in kb projects.","created_at":"2026-01-26T16:06:40.791504-08:00"}]}
