{"id":"orch-go-21005","title":"[orch-go] investigation: debug coaching plugin worker detection","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-28T15:00:25.704575-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-29T10:32:25.360612-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-29T10:32:25.360612-08:00"}
{"id":"orch-go-21006","title":"Update decision template with blocks: frontmatter guidance","description":"The decision gate feature (2026-01-28) adds enforcement teeth to decisions via blocks: frontmatter, but the decision template has no mention of this. Workers/orchestrators creating decisions won't know to add blocking keywords.\n\n**Changes needed:**\n1. Update ~/.kb/templates/decision.md - add optional blocks: section after status with guidance comment\n2. Update kb-cli embedded template (cmd/kb/create.go:239) - same change\n3. Update architect skill - when recommending decisions that should constrain future work, suggest blocks: keywords\n4. Update orchestrator skill - add guidance on when to add blocks: during promotion\n\n**Template addition:**\n```yaml\n---\nstatus: active\n# Optional: Gate future spawns that would conflict with this decision\n# blocks:\n#   - keywords:\n#       - [keyword that should trigger this decision]\n#     patterns:\n#       - \"**/path/pattern*\"\n---\n```\n\n**Guidance to add:**\n- Add blocks: when decision resolves recurring issue (3+ prior investigations)\n- Add blocks: when decision establishes constraint future agents might violate\n- Keywords should match how someone would describe the problem in a spawn task\n\nReference: .kb/decisions/2026-01-28-decision-gate.md","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-01-28T15:20:45.911063-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-28T15:43:12.960103-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-28T15:43:12.960103-08:00","labels":["triage:ready"],"comments":[{"id":1,"issue_id":"orch-go-21006","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Planning - Locating decision template and understanding frontmatter guidance requirements","created_at":"2026-01-28T15:37:22.997325-08:00"},{"id":2,"issue_id":"orch-go-21006","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Scope: 1. Update ~/.kb/templates/DECISION.md with blocks: frontmatter guidance 2. Update kb-cli embedded template (cmd/kb/create.go:239) 3. Update architect skill guidance 4. Update orchestrator skill guidance","created_at":"2026-01-28T15:37:38.768796-08:00"},{"id":3,"issue_id":"orch-go-21006","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Implementation - Starting with template updates","created_at":"2026-01-28T15:38:15.268404-08:00"},{"id":4,"issue_id":"orch-go-21006","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Validation - Verifying all template changes applied correctly","created_at":"2026-01-28T15:40:45.201517-08:00"},{"id":5,"issue_id":"orch-go-21006","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Complete - Updated decision templates and skills with blocks: frontmatter guidance\n\nDeliverables:\n1. ~/.kb/templates/DECISION.md - Added blocks: YAML frontmatter example with guidance\n2. kb-cli (cmd/kb/create.go) - Updated embedded decision template with blocks: guidance  \n3. architect skill - Added 'Decision Gate Guidance' section explaining when to suggest blocks:\n4. orchestrator skill - Added 'Decision Promotion with Blocks' section with format and keyword selection guidance\n\nAll changes committed across kb-cli (558e508) and orch-knowledge (c3bd95b, cfa295f).\nSkills rebuilt and deployed to ~/.claude/skills/.\n\nWorkers/orchestrators creating decisions now have template guidance on when and how to add blocks: frontmatter for decision gate enforcement.","created_at":"2026-01-28T15:42:37.060011-08:00"}]}
{"id":"orch-go-21007","title":"Add decision-patch detection to completion escalation","description":"When a worker completes work that patches or extends an existing decision, the escalation model should detect this and surface an action: Consider adding blocks: keywords to decision X.\n\nContext:\nDecision gate (2026-01-28) blocks spawns when they match decision keywords. But this requires decisions to have blocks: frontmatter. Currently only 2 decisions use this. Rather than relying on orchestrators to remember to add blocks: during promotion, detect at completion time when the completed work relates to an existing decision.\n\nDetection logic:\n1. Parse SYNTHESIS.md for references to .kb/decisions/ files\n2. Check if investigation patches an existing decision (Patches-Decision field in investigation template)\n3. If work patches/extends a decision that lacks blocks: frontmatter - EscalationReview with action suggestion\n\nIntegration with escalation model:\n- Add new check in DetermineEscalation() or as separate post-verification step\n- Surface as action item in completion review\n- Could be Info level (optional) or Review level (mandatory review)\n\nWhy completion time:\n- Context is fresh (just read SYNTHESIS.md, know what decision was relevant)\n- Forcing function (vs relying on memory during promotion)\n- Aligns with Capture at Context principle\n\nReferences:\n- .kb/decisions/2026-01-28-decision-gate.md\n- .kb/decisions/2026-01-17-five-tier-completion-escalation-model.md","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-01-28T15:21:11.953021-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-28T15:43:13.95687-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-28T15:43:13.95687-08:00","labels":["triage:ready"],"comments":[{"id":1,"issue_id":"orch-go-21007","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Planning - Investigating completion escalation logic to add decision-patch detection","created_at":"2026-01-28T15:37:33.23884-08:00"},{"id":2,"issue_id":"orch-go-21007","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Scope: 1. Add function to detect missing blocks: frontmatter in decisions 2. Extend EscalationInput with decision-patch metadata 3. Integrate detection into DetermineEscalationFromCompletion 4. Add escalation logic for missing blocks 5. Write tests 6. Update ExplainEscalation for new case","created_at":"2026-01-28T15:38:19.9613-08:00"},{"id":3,"issue_id":"orch-go-21007","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Implementation - Adding decision-patch detection logic to escalation","created_at":"2026-01-28T15:38:25.39378-08:00"},{"id":4,"issue_id":"orch-go-21007","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Complete - Added decision-patch detection to escalation. Detects when work patches decisions lacking blocks: frontmatter and escalates as EscalationInfo with action suggestion. Tests: go test ./pkg/verify/... - all pass","created_at":"2026-01-28T15:42:29.664179-08:00"}]}
{"id":"orch-go-21008","title":"skillc: add deployment headers to reference files","description":"Reference files copied during skillc deploy lack the AUTO-GENERATED header that SKILL.md has. This makes the 'don't edit deployed files' contract invisible, leading to edits in ~/.claude/skills/ that get overwritten on next deploy.\n\n**Root cause:** Progressive disclosure design (Jan 2026) introduced reference/ directories for on-demand loading. The design focused on discovery mechanism (direct file paths) but didn't account for edit-time confusion.\n\n**Evidence:** Just hit this - edited ~/.claude/skills/meta/orchestrator/reference/model-selection.md instead of source at ~/orch-knowledge/skills/src/meta/orchestrator/reference/model-selection.md. Edit was overwritten on next deploy.\n\n**Proposed fix:** skillc deploy should add header to copied reference files:\n```\n\u003c!-- Deployed from: ~/orch-knowledge/skills/src/.../reference/... --\u003e\n\u003c!-- To modify: edit source file, then run: skillc deploy --\u003e\n```\n\n**Reference:** .kb/investigations/2026-01-17-inv-design-core-vs-reference-split.md","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-01-29T09:56:00.441047-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-29T10:04:24.177745-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-29T10:04:19.195403-08:00","labels":["triage:ready"],"comments":[{"id":1,"issue_id":"orch-go-21008","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Planning - Adding deployment headers to reference files to prevent edits in deployed location","created_at":"2026-01-29T09:56:58.557322-08:00"},{"id":2,"issue_id":"orch-go-21008","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Scope: 1. Modify handleDeploy to detect reference/ directories 2. Add header generation for reference files 3. Copy reference/ dirs with headers during deployment 4. Test with actual skill deployment","created_at":"2026-01-29T09:59:47.04101-08:00"},{"id":3,"issue_id":"orch-go-21008","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Implementing - Adding reference file copy logic with deployment headers to skillc","created_at":"2026-01-29T09:59:48.372918-08:00"},{"id":4,"issue_id":"orch-go-21008","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Complete - Added deployment headers to reference files. Changes committed to skillc repo (commit 5177ba0). All reference files now show source path and modification instructions when deployed.","created_at":"2026-01-29T10:03:22.194797-08:00"}]}
{"id":"orch-go-21009","title":"orchestrator skill: move behavioral guides from reference to core","description":"Audit found orchestrator reference files contain behavioral guidance that should always be loaded, not situational lookup content.\n\n**Evidence:**\n- Action log shows only 14 reference file reads in 30 days across all skills\n- Orchestrator has 1463 lines core + 2051 lines reference = 3514 total (fragmented, not reduced)\n- Files like orchestrator-autonomy.md and meta-orchestrator-interface.md are behavioral guides relevant to EVERY action\n\n**Files to move to core:**\n- orchestrator-autonomy.md - Always relevant behavioral guide\n- meta-orchestrator-interface.md - Always relevant interaction patterns\n\n**Files to evaluate (frequently needed):**\n- model-selection.md - Needed at every spawn decision\n- spawning-checklist.md - Needed at every spawn\n\n**Files that correctly belong in reference (situational/lookup):**\n- orch-commands.md - Command lookup\n- dashboard-troubleshooting.md - Error recovery\n- skill-selection-guide.md - On-demand decision trees\n- config-locations.md - Lookup table\n- workspace-architecture.md - Deep detail\n- completion-workflow.md - Situational procedure\n- daemon-operations.md - Ops-specific\n- session-reflection.md - End-of-session only\n\n**Contrast with feature-impl:** Phase-based reference files work correctly - agents load 2-3 of 11 files based on active phases. Orchestrator reference files lack this conditional loading pattern.\n\n**Reference:** Action log analysis showing 14 reads/30 days","status":"in_progress","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-01-29T10:02:52.655057-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-29T10:12:30.664337-08:00","labels":["triage:ready"]}
{"id":"orch-go-21010","title":"daemon: rollback in_progress status when spawn fails","description":"Daemon marks issue as in_progress before spawn, but doesn't rollback when spawn fails.\n\n**Evidence from daemon.log:**\n```\n[orch-go] Spawning work for issue orch-go-21009\n[orch-go] Skipping orch-go-21009: failed to spawn work: exit status 1\n```\n\nIssue orch-go-21009 is now stuck at in_progress with no agent running.\n\n**Expected:** If spawn fails, status should revert to open so the issue can be retried.\n\n**Current behavior:** Status stays in_progress, creating orphaned issues.","repro":"1. Create issue with triage:ready label 2. Daemon picks up issue and marks in_progress 3. Spawn fails (exit status 1) 4. Issue stays in_progress with no agent","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-01-29T10:08:24.724122-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-29T14:07:22.117465-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-29T14:07:22.117465-08:00","labels":["triage:ready"],"comments":[{"id":1,"issue_id":"orch-go-21010","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Planning - Investigating daemon spawn flow and beads status management to understand where rollback should occur when spawn fails","created_at":"2026-01-29T14:03:40.051856-08:00"},{"id":2,"issue_id":"orch-go-21010","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Complete - Implemented status rollback in SpawnWorkForProject when spawn fails. When orch work command fails after status was set to in_progress, the status is now rolled back to open so the issue can be retried. Added TestBug_SpawnFailureDoesNotBlockRetry test and documentation test. Tests: go test ./pkg/daemon/... - all 121 tests passed (2.8s)","created_at":"2026-01-29T14:06:41.984951-08:00"}]}
{"id":"orch-go-21011","title":"Integrate decision blocking into decidability graph","description":"## Problem\n\nDecision blocking via keyword matching (spawn_validation.go) is redundant with the decidability graph model and causes false positives.\n\n**Current behavior:** Before spawn, task description is matched against decision `blocks:` keywords using substring matching. Common words like 'orchestrator' or 'move' trigger false positives, blocking daemon from spawning legitimate work.\n\n**Root cause:** Decision blocking was implemented before the decidability graph model. It's a spawn-time workaround for what should be graph-level dependencies.\n\n## Evidence\n\n- Daemon blocked on 'orchestrator skill: move behavioral guides' because it matched 'orchestrator synthesis' and 'move template to orch' keywords\n- Issue orch-go-21009 is legitimate work that was blocked by false positive keyword matching\n- See daemon.log: multiple 'spawn blocked: decision conflict' errors\n\n## Correct Model (Decidability Graph)\n\nPer .kb/models/decidability-graph.md:\n- Work nodes → daemon traverses freely\n- Question/Gate nodes → block until resolved by appropriate authority\n- Dependencies encoded in beads → bd ready only shows traversable work\n\nAuthority boundaries should be **first-class in the graph**, not bolted on as spawn-time keyword validation.\n\n## Proposed Fix\n\n1. Remove keyword-based decision blocking from spawn path entirely\n2. When a decision has `blocks:` frontmatter, surface it during triage (issue creation/labeling)\n3. If work relates to a blocking decision, create a Question dependency that must be resolved before work proceeds\n4. Daemon only sees work where dependencies are satisfied\n\n## Interim Fix (Already Applied)\n\nSkip decision conflict check for daemon-driven spawns (daemonDriven=true in runSpawnWithSkillInternal). Issues labeled triage:ready have already been validated by orchestrator.\n\n## References\n\n- .kb/models/decidability-graph.md\n- .kb/decisions/2026-01-07-strategic-orchestrator-model.md  \n- cmd/orch/spawn_validation.go (checkDecisionConflicts)","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-01-29T10:21:05.310885-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-29T10:25:45.721873-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-29T10:25:45.721873-08:00"}
{"id":"orch-go-21012","title":"orch spawn shows 'beads lookup failed' warnings for non-existent issues","repro":"Every orch spawn shows warnings like:\nWarning: beads lookup failed for specs-platform-28 (via CLI): failed to parse bd show output: unexpected end of JSON input - treating as closed\nWarning: beads lookup failed for specs-platform-29 (via CLI): ...\nWarning: beads lookup failed for specs-platform-30 (via CLI): ...\n\nThese issues don't exist in beads (bd show returns 'no issue found') but orch is trying to look them up on every spawn.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-01-29T10:52:46.422156-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-29T19:42:03.321114-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-29T19:42:03.321114-08:00","labels":["triage:ready"],"comments":[{"id":1,"issue_id":"orch-go-21012","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Planning - Investigating 'beads lookup failed' warnings in orch spawn","created_at":"2026-01-29T19:34:40.999321-08:00"},{"id":2,"issue_id":"orch-go-21012","author":"dylanconlin","text":"investigation_path: /Users/dylanconlin/Documents/personal/orch-go/.kb/investigations/2026-01-29-inv-orch-spawn-shows-beads-lookup.md","created_at":"2026-01-29T19:36:05.553598-08:00"},{"id":3,"issue_id":"orch-go-21012","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Reproduction verified: Tested FallbackShowWithDir with cross-project lookup (specs-platform-28 from orch-go dir). Now returns ErrIssueNotFound instead of parse error. Tests pass: go test ./pkg/beads/... ./pkg/daemon/... - all passing.","created_at":"2026-01-29T19:41:53.998789-08:00"},{"id":4,"issue_id":"orch-go-21012","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Complete - Added ErrIssueNotFound error type to pkg/beads/client.go and updated getClosedIssuesForProject to suppress warnings for expected 'not found' errors during cross-project lookups. Tests: go test ./pkg/beads/... ./pkg/daemon/... - all passing.","created_at":"2026-01-29T19:41:57.648846-08:00"}]}
{"id":"orch-go-21013","title":"[orch-go] investigation: Verify OpenCode OAuth priority fix was lost: ch...","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-29T11:23:51.111084-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-29T11:23:51.111084-08:00"}
{"id":"orch-go-21014","title":"orch frontier reports stuck agents for closed issues","description":"Likely stuck detection/registry drift; should exclude closed issues and reconcile against workspace/opencode state.","repro":"1) Run ⚠️  HEALTH WARNINGS\n   1 stuck agents (\u003e 2h) - run 'orch clean --stale' to clean up\n\nREADY TO RELEASE (46)\n   [task] orch-go-20979  Investigate SSE reconnection in OpenCode c...\n   [feature] orch-go-20985  Auto-rebuild OpenCode binary when fork cha...\n   [bug] orch-go-20988  orch cannot inspect OpenCode sessions not ...\n   [feature] orch-go-21009  orchestrator skill: move behavioral guides...\n   [bug] orch-go-21010  daemon: rollback in_progress status when s...\n   [bug] orch-go-21012  orch spawn shows 'beads lookup failed' war...\n   [task] orch-go-21013  [orch-go] investigation: Verify OpenCode O...\n   [epic] orch-go-60vb1  Epic: Audit CLI error UX across orch ecosy...\n   ... and 38 more\n\nBLOCKED (2)\n   orch-go-kz7zr  Epic: Governance Infrastructure ...\n      ← blocked by: orch-go-ajxm1\n   orch-go-i3b5l  Update documentation for Docker ...\n      ← blocked by: orch-go-m3f8b\n\nACTIVE (2)\n   opencode-untracked-1769621244 [tmux] (feature-impl)\n   opencode-untracked-1769714652 [tmux] (investigation)\n\nSTUCK (\u003e 2h) (1)\n   orch-go-20997 [20h 41m] 2) Observe STUCK list includes orch-go-21008 + orch-go-20997 3) Run \norch-go-21008: skillc: add deployment headers to reference files\nStatus: closed\nPriority: P2\nType: feature\nCreated: 2026-01-29 09:56\nCreated by: dylanconlin\nUpdated: 2026-01-29 10:04\n\nDescription:\nReference files copied during skillc deploy lack the AUTO-GENERATED header that SKILL.md has. This makes the 'don't edit deployed files' contract invisible, leading to edits in ~/.claude/skills/ that get overwritten on next deploy.\n\n**Root cause:** Progressive disclosure design (Jan 2026) introduced reference/ directories for on-demand loading. The design focused on discovery mechanism (direct file paths) but didn't account for edit-time confusion.\n\n**Evidence:** Just hit this - edited ~/.claude/skills/meta/orchestrator/reference/model-selection.md instead of source at ~/orch-knowledge/skills/src/meta/orchestrator/reference/model-selection.md. Edit was overwritten on next deploy.\n\n**Proposed fix:** skillc deploy should add header to copied reference files:\n```\n\u003c!-- Deployed from: ~/orch-knowledge/skills/src/.../reference/... --\u003e\n\u003c!-- To modify: edit source file, then run: skillc deploy --\u003e\n```\n\n**Reference:** .kb/investigations/2026-01-17-inv-design-core-vs-reference-split.md\n\nLabels: [triage:ready]\n\nComments (4):\n  [dylanconlin at 2026-01-29 09:56]\n  Phase: Planning - Adding deployment headers to reference files to prevent edits in deployed location\n\n  [dylanconlin at 2026-01-29 09:59]\n  Scope: 1. Modify handleDeploy to detect reference/ directories 2. Add header generation for reference files 3. Copy reference/ dirs with headers during deployment 4. Test with actual skill deployment\n\n  [dylanconlin at 2026-01-29 09:59]\n  Phase: Implementing - Adding reference file copy logic with deployment headers to skillc\n\n  [dylanconlin at 2026-01-29 10:03]\n  Phase: Complete - Added deployment headers to reference files. Changes committed to skillc repo (commit 5177ba0). All reference files now show source path and modification instructions when deployed. and \norch-go-20997: Add version command to glass CLI\nStatus: closed\nPriority: P2\nType: task\nCreated: 2026-01-28 13:16\nCreated by: dylanconlin\nUpdated: 2026-01-29 11:02\n\nDescription:\nAdd 'glass version' and 'glass version --json' subcommand. Glass already has ldflags (Version, BuildTime, SourceDir, GitHash) - just needs ~30 lines to expose them. Follow orch version pattern. Enables orch doctor to verify glass binary staleness.\n\nLabels: [triage:ready]\n\nComments (9):\n  [dylanconlin at 2026-01-28 13:20]\n  Scope: 1. Add 'glass version' subcommand 2. Add 'glass version --json' flag support 3. Expose existing ldflags (Version, BuildTime, SourceDir, GitHash) 4. Follow orch version pattern\n\n  [dylanconlin at 2026-01-28 13:20]\n  Phase: Planning - Adding version command to glass CLI following orch version pattern\n\n  [dylanconlin at 2026-01-28 13:21]\n  QUESTION: Cannot locate glass CLI source code in orch-go repo. The task says 'glass already has ldflags' but I cannot find cmd/glass/, tools/glass/, or glass.go anywhere. Is glass in a separate repository? If so, what's the repo path?\n\n  [dylanconlin at 2026-01-28 13:23]\n  Phase: Implementation - Glass repo located at /Users/dylanconlin/Documents/personal/glass, proceeding with version command implementation\n\n  [dylanconlin at 2026-01-28 13:24]\n  CONSTRAINT: Task requires modifying /Users/dylanconlin/Documents/personal/glass/ (separate repo) but my workspace is /Users/dylanconlin/Documents/personal/orch-go. This is cross-project work. Reverting unauthorized edits to glass/main.go. Need orchestrator guidance on spawn strategy (spawn in glass repo? --no-track?).\n\n  [dylanconlin at 2026-01-28 13:33]\n  Phase: Implementation - Working in glass repo at ~/Documents/personal/glass/, implementing version command with --json support\n\n  [dylanconlin at 2026-01-28 13:35]\n  IMPORTANT: Glass source is at ~/Documents/personal/glass/ (separate repo, not in orch-go)\n\n  [dylanconlin at 2026-01-28 15:47]\n  Phase: Planning - Adding version command to glass CLI following orch version pattern\n\n  [dylanconlin at 2026-01-28 15:47]\n  Scope: 1. Add 'glass version' command 2. Add 'glass version --json' support 3. Expose ldflags (Version, BuildTime, SourceDir, GitHash) 4. Follow orch version pattern and see both Status: closed 4) Run Issue orch-go-21008 is already closed in beads\nPhase: Complete\nSummary: Added deployment headers to reference files. Changes committed to skillc repo (commit 5177ba0). All reference files now show source path and modification instructions when deployed.\n\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│  🔍 BEHAVIORAL VALIDATION SUGGESTED                         │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│  Type: concurrency\n│  Reason: File changes detected: concurrency\n│  ⚠️  No behavioral evidence found in beads comments\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│  Suggested validation steps:                                │\n│  1. Run the code with multiple concurrent requests\n│  2. Verify locks acquire and release correctly\n│  3. Check for race conditions\n│  4. Test timeout/retry behavior\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│  Changed files:                                             │\n│    .kb/decisions/2026-01-19-worker-authority-bound...\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n\nReason: Added deployment headers to reference files. Changes committed to skillc repo (commit 5177ba0). All reference files now show source path and modification instructions when deployed.\n\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│  ⚠️  NOTABLE ECOSYSTEM CHANGES DETECTED                      │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│  📌 [kb-cli] feat: add blocks: frontmatter guidanc... \n│    (behavioral)\n│  📌 [orch-knowledge] feat: add blocks: frontmatter gui\n│    danc... (behavioral)\n│  📌 [orch-go] feat: add pre-spawn decision check so...\n│     (behavioral)\n│  📌 [orch-go] test: add tests for /api/kb-health en...\n│     (behavioral)\n│  📌 [agentlog] feat: add version command with --json..\n│    . (behavioral)\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│  Review recent changes that may affect agent behavior       │\n│  Run: orch changelog --days 3                               │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘ and it succeeds","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-01-29T12:28:08.651169-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-29T12:34:44.837783-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-29T12:34:44.837783-08:00","labels":["triage:ready"],"comments":[{"id":1,"issue_id":"orch-go-21014","author":"dylanconlin","text":"investigation_path: /Users/dylanconlin/Documents/personal/orch-go/.kb/investigations/2026-01-29-inv-orch-frontier-reports-stuck-agents.md","created_at":"2026-01-29T12:29:00.201105-08:00"},{"id":2,"issue_id":"orch-go-21014","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Implementing - Adding beads status check to filter closed issues from stuck agent detection","created_at":"2026-01-29T12:29:47.955767-08:00"},{"id":3,"issue_id":"orch-go-21014","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Reproduction verified: Ran orch frontier after fix - closed issue orch-go-20997 no longer appears in STUCK section. Tests: go test ./cmd/orch/ -run TestFilter -v - 5 passed, 0 failed","created_at":"2026-01-29T12:34:11.474567-08:00"},{"id":4,"issue_id":"orch-go-21014","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Complete - Fixed orch frontier stuck agent detection by filtering out agents for closed beads issues. Tests: go test ./cmd/orch/ -run TestFilter -v - 5 passed, 0 failed. Commit: 31ef6e84","created_at":"2026-01-29T12:34:14.94555-08:00"}]}
{"id":"orch-go-21015","title":"Orchestrator role signal: auto-enable only for orch sessions (not all chats)","description":"Decision kb-4eb82b: Add explicit orchestrator role signal (e.g., session metadata/instructions/CLAUDE_CONTEXT) when an 'orch session' is started so the agent behaves as orchestrator without manual prompting, but do not force orchestrator mode for every chat in orch-go root.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-01-29T12:35:13.029533-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-29T12:40:42.006073-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-29T12:40:42.006073-08:00","labels":["triage:ready"],"comments":[{"id":1,"issue_id":"orch-go-21015","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Planning - Understanding session creation and orchestrator role signal implementation","created_at":"2026-01-29T12:36:12.66516-08:00"},{"id":2,"issue_id":"orch-go-21015","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Scope: 1. Find/create 'orch session' command that starts orchestrator sessions 2. Add CLAUDE_CONTEXT/role signal when starting orchestrator session 3. Ensure signal only applies to 'orch session' (not all orch-go root chats) 4. Verify orchestrator skill auto-loads without manual prompting","created_at":"2026-01-29T12:36:45.998148-08:00"},{"id":3,"issue_id":"orch-go-21015","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Design - Creating session-context plugin that reads CLAUDE_CONTEXT env var to auto-load orchestrator skill for orchestrator sessions while skipping for workers (ORCH_WORKER=1)","created_at":"2026-01-29T12:38:31.780461-08:00"},{"id":4,"issue_id":"orch-go-21015","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Implementation - Created .opencode/plugin/session-context.ts that reads CLAUDE_CONTEXT env var and injects orchestrator role signal for orchestrator/meta-orchestrator sessions while skipping for workers (ORCH_WORKER=1)","created_at":"2026-01-29T12:39:17.765824-08:00"},{"id":5,"issue_id":"orch-go-21015","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Complete - Delivered .opencode/plugin/session-context.ts that implements kb-4eb82b decision. Plugin reads CLAUDE_CONTEXT env var (already set by spawn/claude.go) and injects orchestrator role instructions for orchestrator/meta-orchestrator sessions via session.start hook. Skips for workers (ORCH_WORKER=1) and normal chats (unset CLAUDE_CONTEXT). Committed as a060e652.","created_at":"2026-01-29T12:39:37.908939-08:00"}]}
{"id":"orch-go-21016","title":"[orch-go] investigation: OpenCode TUI mode switch (build/orchestrator/plan)","description":"User reports OpenCode TUI shows a mode indicator that cycles via Tab: build → orchestrator → plan. Need to determine what this actually does.\n\nQuestions to answer (with evidence):\n- Where is the mode implemented in Dylan's OpenCode fork (~/Documents/personal/opencode) and/or upstream?\n- Does switching mode change the system prompt/instructions sent to the model? Or just UI affordances?\n- Does it change tool availability, temperature/model selection, or message routing?\n- Is the mode persisted anywhere (session metadata, disk storage, SSE events)? Can orch-go observe it via API?\n\nDeliverables:\n- .kb/investigations/2026-01-29-inv-opencode-tui-mode-switch.md\n- If integration needed: create follow-up beads issue(s) with scoped implementation.\n\nScope:\n- IN: code inspection + minimal repro tests (e.g., log/trace prompt payloads if available)\n- OUT: implementing orch-go changes (file follow-up issue instead)","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-29T12:37:42.85748-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-29T14:06:18.230691-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-29T14:06:18.230691-08:00","labels":["triage:ready"],"comments":[{"id":1,"issue_id":"orch-go-21016","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Planning - Investigating OpenCode TUI mode switch (build/orchestrator/plan) to determine implementation location and behavioral differences","created_at":"2026-01-29T12:38:43.547466-08:00"},{"id":2,"issue_id":"orch-go-21016","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Investigation - Found that 'mode' is deprecated field showing agent name. Tab cycles agents (build/plan/etc) via local.agent.move(). No separate mode system - just agent selection.","created_at":"2026-01-29T13:53:46.922348-08:00"},{"id":3,"issue_id":"orch-go-21016","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Complete - Investigation file created at .kb/investigations/2026-01-29-inv-opencode-tui-mode-switch.md. Key finding: 'mode' is deprecated field storing agent name. Tab cycles agents (build/plan/custom) via permissions, not separate mode system. Mode persisted in messages, observable via API.","created_at":"2026-01-29T14:05:35.278564-08:00"}]}
{"id":"orch-go-21017","title":"OpenCode server (4096) dies; orch doctor --fix can't bring it up","description":"Observed during `orch complete orch-go-21015`: completion could not fetch/export/delete OpenCode session messages because OpenCode API (127.0.0.1:4096) refused connections. `orch doctor --fix` also fails to bring OpenCode up; it reports \"OpenCode started but not responding after 10s\".\n\nRepro:\n1) Run `orch doctor`\n2) Observe: OpenCode (port 4096) Not responding\n3) Run `orch doctor --fix`\n4) Observe: Failed to start OpenCode: started but not responding after 10s\n5) Run `curl -m 2 http://127.0.0.1:4096/session`\n6) Observe: connect refused / cannot connect\n\nImpact:\n- orch complete cannot export activity or delete sessions\n- dashboard `/api/agents` returns 500 when OpenCode is down\n\nSuspect:\n- opencode process spawned via overmind/servers exits immediately (PID reported but gone)","repro":"1) Run orch doctor - Service Health Check\n===================================\n\n✓ orch binary\n  UP TO DATE\n✗ OpenCode (port 4096)\n  Not responding\n✓ orch serve (port 3348)\n  Health OK, /api/agents status 500\n✗ Web UI (port 5188)\n  Not listening\n✓ Overmind (launchd)\n  Running (PID 59329)\n✗ Beads Daemon\n  Not running (optional)\n✓ Session Health\n  No active sessions\n✓ Beads DB Integrity\n  Database integrity verified\n✗ Registry Reconciliation\n  ⚠️ 253 stale registry entries (tmux windows missing)\n✓ Docker Backend\n  Container test passed (Docker 28.4.0)\n\nSome services are not running.\n\nSome services are not running. Use 'orch doctor --fix' to start them. (or orch doctor - Service Health Check\n===================================\n\n✓ orch binary\n  UP TO DATE\n✗ OpenCode (port 4096)\n  Not responding\n✓ orch serve (port 3348)\n  Health OK, /api/agents status 500\n✗ Web UI (port 5188)\n  Not listening\n✓ Overmind (launchd)\n  Running (PID 59329)\n✗ Beads Daemon\n  Not running (optional)\n✓ Session Health\n  No active sessions\n✓ Beads DB Integrity\n  Database integrity verified\n✗ Registry Reconciliation\n  ⚠️ 253 stale registry entries (tmux windows missing)\n✓ Docker Backend\n  Container test passed (Docker 28.4.0)\n\nSome services are not running.\n\nAttempting to fix issues...\n\nStarting OpenCode...\n  ❌ Failed to start OpenCode: OpenCode started but not responding after 10s) 2) Observe OpenCode (port 4096) Not responding 3) orch doctor - Service Health Check\n===================================\n\n✓ orch binary\n  UP TO DATE\n✗ OpenCode (port 4096)\n  Not responding\n✓ orch serve (port 3348)\n  Health OK, /api/agents status 500\n✗ Web UI (port 5188)\n  Not listening\n✓ Overmind (launchd)\n  Running (PID 59329)\n✗ Beads Daemon\n  Not running (optional)\n✓ Session Health\n  No active sessions\n✓ Beads DB Integrity\n  Database integrity verified\n✗ Registry Reconciliation\n  ⚠️ 253 stale registry entries (tmux windows missing)\n✓ Docker Backend\n  Container test passed (Docker 28.4.0)\n\nSome services are not running.\n\nAttempting to fix issues...\n\nStarting OpenCode...\n  ❌ Failed to start OpenCode: OpenCode started but not responding after 10s prints 'OpenCode started but not responding after 10s' 4)  fails to connect","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-01-29T12:43:13.974455-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-29T12:44:12.799668-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-29T12:44:12.799668-08:00","labels":["triage:ready"]}
{"id":"orch-go-21018","title":"orch-go dashboard web server start command is stale (bun script dev missing)","description":"The servers window shows a bun command that no longer exists in package scripts, so the web UI can't be started from the standard workflow. Fix the servers command (tmuxinator/workers config or whatever `orch-dashboard restart` uses) to the current correct start command.","repro":"1) Attach to `workers-orch-go:servers`\n2) Run the dashboard web start command shown there (currently `bun run dev --port 5188`)\n3) Observe: `error: Script not found \"dev\"`\n4) As a result, Web UI on 5188 is not listening","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-01-29T12:43:42.097828-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-29T13:44:07.26473-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-29T13:44:07.26473-08:00","labels":["triage:ready"],"comments":[{"id":1,"issue_id":"orch-go-21018","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Planning - Investigating web UI start command drift","created_at":"2026-01-29T13:38:15.848862-08:00"},{"id":2,"issue_id":"orch-go-21018","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Implementing - Found root cause: tmuxinator generator creates 'bun run dev --port N' but should use Procfile commands. Fixing generator to parse Procfile when available.","created_at":"2026-01-29T13:40:41.222325-08:00"},{"id":3,"issue_id":"orch-go-21018","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Complete - Fixed tmuxinator generator to read Procfile commands when available, falling back to auto-generated commands. The orch-go tmuxinator config now correctly uses 'orch serve' and 'cd web \u0026\u0026 bun run dev' from Procfile. Tests: go test ./pkg/tmux/... - 37 passed, 0 failed. Verified orch-dashboard restart works correctly.","created_at":"2026-01-29T13:43:20.363607-08:00"}]}
{"id":"orch-go-21019","title":"OpenCode server on 4096 not responding; orch doctor --fix can't recover","description":"Observed while completing orch-go-21015: orch complete could not fetch/export/delete OpenCode session messages because 4096 refused connections. Overmind/dashboard restart reports opencode PID but process exits quickly (PID not alive right after).","repro":"1) Run: orch doctor\n2) Observe: OpenCode (port 4096) Not responding\n3) Run: orch doctor --fix\n4) Observe: Failed to start OpenCode (started but not responding after 10s)\n5) Run: curl -m 2 http://127.0.0.1:4096/session\n6) Observe: cannot connect / connection refused","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-01-29T12:44:07.563147-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-29T13:36:38.280866-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-29T13:36:38.280866-08:00","comments":[{"id":1,"issue_id":"orch-go-21019","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Planning - Investigating OpenCode server 4096 crash issue, reviewing existing investigations and server startup","created_at":"2026-01-29T12:44:35.571119-08:00"},{"id":2,"issue_id":"orch-go-21019","author":"dylanconlin","text":"investigation_path: /Users/dylanconlin/Documents/personal/orch-go/.kb/investigations/2026-01-29-inv-opencode-server-4096-not-responding.md","created_at":"2026-01-29T12:45:00.464613-08:00"},{"id":3,"issue_id":"orch-go-21019","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Planning - Investigating dashboard startup failures (opencode/api/web dying immediately)","created_at":"2026-01-29T12:50:58.949714-08:00"},{"id":4,"issue_id":"orch-go-21019","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Reproduction verified: Missing web/node_modules caused vite command not found. After bun install, orch-dashboard restart succeeds with all services (api/web/opencode) responding on ports 3348/5188/4096.","created_at":"2026-01-29T12:52:43.340823-08:00"},{"id":5,"issue_id":"orch-go-21019","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Complete - Root cause: missing web/node_modules. Fix: bun install in web/. Tests: curl health checks - 200 OK on all three ports (3348/5188/4096). No code changes needed - operational fix only.","created_at":"2026-01-29T12:52:56.469312-08:00"}]}
{"id":"orch-go-21020","title":"Run GPT-5.2 modal orchestrator experiment","description":"Execute the 5-scenario test protocol from . Capture pass/fail per scenario + notes on permission-denial UX, gate handling, and role-boundary adherence. Outcome: propose decision update/new decision distinguishing orchestrator vs worker model requirements.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-29T13:54:50.151296-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-29T13:59:08.784718-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-29T13:59:08.784718-08:00","labels":["triage:ready"],"comments":[{"id":1,"issue_id":"orch-go-21020","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Planning - Setting up GPT-5.2 modal orchestrator experiment","created_at":"2026-01-29T13:56:07.322228-08:00"},{"id":2,"issue_id":"orch-go-21020","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Scope: 1. Execute 5-scenario test protocol (Multi-Gate Spawn, Role Boundary, Failure Adaptation, Deliberation Control, Instruction Synthesis) 2. Capture pass/fail per scenario 3. Document permission-denial UX 4. Document gate handling behavior 5. Document role-boundary adherence 6. Propose decision update/new decision for orchestrator vs worker model requirements","created_at":"2026-01-29T13:56:21.014702-08:00"},{"id":3,"issue_id":"orch-go-21020","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Implementation - Setting up test prerequisites (backup config, create modal agent config)","created_at":"2026-01-29T13:56:36.515643-08:00"},{"id":4,"issue_id":"orch-go-21020","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Testing - Running Scenario 1: Multi-Gate Spawn","created_at":"2026-01-29T13:57:24.224495-08:00"},{"id":5,"issue_id":"orch-go-21020","author":"dylanconlin","text":"Phase: Complete - Added GPT-5.2 modal orchestrator agent config to .opencode/opencode.json. Changes: (1) New agent named gpt_orchestrator with model openai/gpt-5.2, mode primary, temp 0.3, steps 50. (2) Safe permissions: deny edit/write/notebookedit, allow only orch/bd/kb/git read-only commands, read limited to .kb/.orch/CLAUDE.md/*.md. (3) Preserved existing permission.task = deny. (4) Backup saved to .opencode/opencode.json.bak. To run test scenarios: opencode --agent gpt_orchestrator. Test protocol and results template in .kb/investigations/2026-01-29-gpt-orchestrator-modal-test-results.md with 5 scenarios ready to execute.","created_at":"2026-01-29T13:58:58.812893-08:00"}]}
