ed Action\n\n1. Run `kb chronicle \"synthesis\"` to understand evolution\n2. Identify patterns and contradictions across investigations\n3. Create a synthesized decision or consolidated investigation\n","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-07T07:07:48.539628-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-07T07:38:04.834237-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-07T07:38:04.834237-08:00","close_reason":"Duplicate of orch-go-1433n","labels":["triage:review"]}
{"id":"orch-go-23fh","title":"Standardize binary installation location across CLI tools","description":"Pattern: binaries get installed to both ~/bin/ and ~/go/bin/, causing PATH shadowing where stale binaries mask new ones. Hit with orch (stale binary), kb (stale binary). Investigate: standardize on one location, add staleness check, or make install scripts consistent across orch-go, kb-cli, bd.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-12-23T19:58:17.852816-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-26T22:40:23.042183-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-26T22:40:23.042183-08:00","close_reason":"Investigation complete. Root cause: 3 of 6 CLI tools use go install (→ ~/go/bin) while PATH gives ~/go/bin priority over ~/bin. Recommendation: Standardize on orch-go Makefile pattern (build → copy to ~/bin → codesign). Follow-up issues needed for beads, skillc, agentlog. Constraint recorded via kn.","labels":["skill:investigation","triage:ready"]}
