{"id":"orch-go-256a9","title":"Bug: Orchestrator coaching fires on worker agents","description":"Coaching plugin injects orchestrator-specific alerts into worker sessions. Workers receiving 'spawn an agent instead of investigating yourself' when reading files - but that's exactly what workers should do. Coaching should detect session type (orchestrator vs worker) and skip worker sessions.","repro":"Spawn worker via orch spawn --backend opencode. Worker receives coaching alerts like 'spawn an agent instead of investigating' when doing file reads - but workers SHOULD be investigating.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-01-23T17:50:27.79296-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-23T18:02:21.056408-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-23T18:02:21.056408-08:00","close_reason":"Phase: Complete - Fixed coaching plugin worker detection. Changed from unreliable session.metadata.role to file-path based detection (SPAWN_CONTEXT.md reads, .orch/workspace/ paths). Workers now properly skip coaching alerts."}
