{"id":"orch-go-25s2","title":"Epic: Split serve_agents.go into focused handler files","description":"## Problem\n\nserve_agents.go (1399 lines) is part of serve.go hotspot cluster (34 fix commits in 28 days). \n\n## Goal\n\nSplit serve_agents.go into focused files by endpoint domain, similar to how serve_beads.go, serve_errors.go, serve_learn.go were already extracted.\n\n## Approach\n\n1. Spawn architect to analyze and design split\n2. Extract by endpoint groupings\n3. Verify tests pass after each extraction\n\n## Success Criteria\n\n- serve_agents.go reduced to routing + shared utilities\n- Each handler domain in its own file\n- All tests pass\n- Fix commit density decreases","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"epic","created_at":"2026-01-04T13:26:12.897358-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-04T14:30:23.257907-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-04T14:30:23.257907-08:00","close_reason":"All phases complete. serve_agents.go reduced from 1399 to 724 lines via cache and events extraction."}
{"id":"orch-go-25s2.2","title":"Design: Analyze serve_agents.go and plan extraction","description":"Spawn architect to:\n1. Analyze serve_agents.go (1399 lines) structure\n2. Identify endpoint groupings/domains  \n3. Design extraction plan with phases\n4. Document in .kb/investigations/\n\nOutput: Investigation with phased extraction plan, similar to main.go split design.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-04T13:26:37.422696-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-04T13:35:40.434183-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-04T13:35:40.434183-08:00","close_reason":"Validated extraction plan: 3 files (cache ~470, events ~230, core ~700 lines). Added feat-027/028 to features.json."}
{"id":"orch-go-25s2.3","title":"Phase 1: Extract serve_agents_cache.go (~470 lines)","description":"Extract cache infrastructure from serve_agents.go.\n\nMove: beadsCache (lines 27-227), workspaceCache (lines 277-496), TTL constants (88-92), globals (62-64, 124).\n\nVerify: go build ./cmd/orch/ \u0026\u0026 go test ./cmd/orch/\n\nSee: .kb/investigations/2026-01-04-inv-analyze-serve-agents-go-1399.md","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-04T13:37:26.84936-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-04T13:46:45.213568-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-04T13:46:45.213568-08:00","close_reason":"Extracted serve_agents_cache.go"}
{"id":"orch-go-25s2.4","title":"Phase 2: Extract serve_agents_events.go (~230 lines)","description":"Extract event handlers from serve_agents.go.\n\nMove: handleEvents, handleAgentlog, handleAgentlogJSON, handleAgentlogSSE, readLastNEvents (lines 954-1195).\n\nDepends on Phase 1 completing first.\n\nVerify: go build ./cmd/orch/ \u0026\u0026 go test ./cmd/orch/","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-04T13:37:31.910057-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-04T14:28:33.939029-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-04T14:28:33.939029-08:00","close_reason":"Work was already done by prior agent (commit fb018a5e). Verified build and tests pass. serve_agents.go is now 724 lines with event handlers in serve_agents_events.go (259 lines)."}
{"id":"orch-go-25wz","title":"Add config setting to disable desktop notifications","description":"Desktop notifications for agent completion are no longer needed now that dashboard is reliable. Add config option to ~/.orch/config.yaml to disable them. Something like: notifications: enabled: false. The notify code is in pkg/notify/. Should default to enabled for backward compatibility.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-12-26T09:31:35.598055-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-26T15:04:12.408491-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-26T15:04:12.408491-08:00","close_reason":"Added notifications.enabled config setting to ~/.orch/config.yaml via new pkg/userconfig package. Users can now disable desktop notifications by setting notifications.enabled: false.","labels":["skill:feature-impl","triage:ready"]}
{"id":"orch-go-25y1h","title":"Fix guarded-files plugin false positives on documentation","description":"Guarded-files plugin triggers on files containing 'AUTO-GENERATED' anywhere in content, not just file headers.\n\n**Fix approach:**\n- Check if AUTO-GENERATED appears in first N lines (header area)\n- Or check if it's in a comment block at the start of the file\n- Not just `content.includes('AUTO-GENERATED')`\n\n**Files:**\n- ~/.config/opencode/lib/guarded-files.ts (detection logic)","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-01-08T10:45:28.19439-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-08T18:05:36.817437-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-08T18:05:36.817437-08:00","close_reason":"Plugin fix at ~/.config/opencode/plugin/guarded-files.ts - outside orch-go git scope"}
