{"id":"orch-go-2h473","title":"Trial: One week daemon-first workflow (Jan 6-13)","description":"## Purpose\n\nBuild trust in daemon through direct experience, not theory.\n\n## Rules\n\n- Issues via `bd create` → daemon picks them up\n- No `orch spawn` for workers (unless true emergency)\n- Meta-orchestrator produces issues, not spawns\n- `--bypass-triage` only for orchestrator sessions or emergencies\n\n## Observe\n\n- Skill inference accuracy\n- Context quality\n- Timing (30-60s delay)\n- Completion quality\n\n## Capture\n\n- Every friction point\n- Every bypass (with reason)\n- Every 'I wish I could spawn' impulse\n\n## End Date\n\n2026-01-13 - Review results and decide next steps","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-06T08:13:48.393158-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-07T15:36:11.008732-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-07T15:36:11.008732-08:00","close_reason":"Trial successful - daemon-first workflow adopted. Strategic Orchestrator Model decision (2026-01-07) formalized this: daemon coordinates, orchestrator comprehends.","labels":["triage:blocked"]}
{"id":"orch-go-2i7ab","title":"Synthesize headless investigations (15)","description":"## Synthesis Needed\n\nTopic **headless** has accumulated 15 investigations that may benefit from consolidation.\n\n### Investigations to synthesize:\n\n- 2025-12-20-inv-implement-headless-spawn-mode-add.md\n- 2025-12-20-inv-make-headless-mode-default-deprecate.md\n- 2025-12-20-inv-scope-out-headless-swarm-implementation.md\n- 2025-12-21-inv-headless-spawn-not-sending-prompts.md\n- 2025-12-22-debug-headless-spawns-not-discoverable-by-beads-id.md\n- 2025-12-22-inv-headless-spawn-mode-readiness-what.md\n- 2025-12-22-inv-headless-spawn-registers-wrong-project.md\n- 2025-12-23-debug-headless-spawn-model-format.md\n- 2025-12-23-inv-headless-spawn-does-not-pass.md\n- 2025-12-23-inv-orch-status-shows-headless-agents.md\n- 2025-12-23-inv-token-limit-explosion-headless-spawn.md\n- 2025-12-22-inv-test-headless-mode.md\n- 2025-12-22-inv-test-headless-spawn-list-files.md\n- 2025-12-22-inv-test-headless-spawn.md\n- 2025-12-23-inv-test-headless-spawn-after-fix.md\n\n### Chronicle Timeline\n\n```\n2025-12-20 [INV] Legacy Artifacts Synthesis Protocol Alignment\n2025-12-20 [INV] Enhance status command with swarm progress\n2025-12-20 [INV] Fix Spawn to Use Standalone Mode with TUI\n2025-12-20 [INV] Implement Headless Spawn Mode\n2025-12-20 [INV] Make Headless Mode Default for Spawn\n... (run kb chronicle for full timeline)\n```\n\n### Suggested Action\n\n1. Run `kb chronicle \"headless\"` to understand evolution\n2. Identify patterns and contradictions across investigations\n3. Create a synthesized decision or consolidated investigation\n","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-07T01:16:56.278479-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-07T06:56:57.938683-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-07T06:56:57.938683-08:00","close_reason":"Duplicate of orch-go-jbyzr","labels":["triage:review"]}
{"id":"orch-go-2jnp","title":"action-log.ts plugin logs duplicate entries - same timestamp appearing twice","description":"Observed duplicate entries in ~/.orch/action-log.jsonl with identical timestamps. Plugin has deduplication logic (loggedCalls Set) but it's not preventing duplicates. Suggests either: 1) tool.execute.after hook called twice per action, 2) multiple plugin instances, or 3) callID not unique across calls. Evidence: tail -100 ~/.orch/action-log.jsonl shows many entries appearing exactly twice with same timestamp.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2025-12-29T16:39:11.879785-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-29T17:39:51.263616-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-29T17:39:51.263616-08:00","close_reason":"Fixed duplicate action-log entries by implementing file-based lock deduplication with atomic operations. Changes already committed in 4641be0b. Requires OpenCode restart to take effect."}
{"id":"orch-go-2mpf","title":"Dashboard doesn't detect completion for untracked agents","description":"## Problem\n\nDashboard shows untracked agents (--no-track) as 'active' indefinitely because:\n1. No beads issue exists → no Phase: Complete comment to check\n2. Falls back to 10-minute activity timeout only\n\n## Evidence\n\nAgent orch-knowledge-untracked-1766690045 completed its work (committed to repo) but dashboard shows it as Active at 7m 25s.\n\n## Solution\n\nFor agents without beads tracking, check alternative completion signals:\n1. SYNTHESIS.md exists in workspace → completed (full tier)\n2. .tier file says 'light' AND commits exist → completed (light tier)\n3. OpenCode session is_processing=false for \u003e2 minutes → idle\n\n## Related\n\nFix orch-go-k08g only addressed tracked agents with beads Phase: Complete comments.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2025-12-25T11:22:56.483991-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-25T13:31:10.67273-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-25T13:31:10.67273-08:00","close_reason":"Added workspace SYNTHESIS.md check as fallback for untracked agent completion detection. Tests pass, implementation follows existing patterns.","labels":["triage:ready"]}
{"id":"orch-go-2nruy","title":"Add dedup check before spawn to prevent duplicate sessions for same beads issue","description":"**Problem:** Daemon spawns new sessions for the same beads issue instead of resuming existing ones.\n\n**Impact:**\n- Multiple OpenCode sessions for same issue (e.g., 12+ sessions for orch-go-nqgjr)\n- All recent sessions count toward concurrency limit\n- Concurrency limit hit even though only 2 agents actually running\n\n**Evidence (Jan 15):**\n- orch-go-nqgjr: 12+ sessions all within 2 hours\n- price-watch 'investigate run 93': 4 duplicate sessions\n\n**Solution:** Check for existing session with same beads ID before spawn. If found and recent, resume instead of spawn fresh.\n\n**Related:**\n- Stuck agent recovery design\n- Ghost filtering decision","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-01-15T11:29:45.756236-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-16T10:46:15.655314-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-16T10:46:15.655314-08:00","close_reason":"Phase: Complete - Design validation complete: two-layer dedup (session-level + TTL backup) is substrate-aligned, observability gap identified, feat-048 added for telemetry implementation","labels":["triage:ready"]}
