ations-13-synthesis.md\n- 2026-01-08-inv-synthesize-model-investigations-11-synthesis.md\n- 2026-01-08-inv-synthesize-status-investigations-12-synthesis.md\n- 2026-01-08-inv-synthesize-tmux-investigations-12-synthesis.md\n- 2025-12-20-inv-beta-flash-synthesis-protocol-design.md\n\n### Chronicle Timeline\n\n```\n2025-12-19 [INV] CLI orch complete Command Implementation\n2025-12-19 [INV] CLI orch spawn Command Implementation\n2025-12-19 [INV] CLI Orch Status Command\n2025-12-19 [INV] CLI Project Scaffolding and Build Setup\n2025-12-19 [INV] OpenCode Client Package Session Management\n... (run kb chronicle for full timeline)\n```\n\n### Suggested Action\n\n1. Run `kb chronicle \"synthesis\"` to understand evolution\n2. Identify patterns and contradictions across investigations\n3. Create a synthesized decision or consolidated investigation\n","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-08T12:13:48.264908-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-08T14:57:35.486258-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-08T14:57:35.486258-08:00","close_reason":"Duplicate synthesis issue","labels":["triage:review"]}
{"id":"orch-go-2pyaw","title":"Bug: Worker agents cause tmux session switch from orchestrator to workers-orch-go","description":"When headless worker agents run, something causes the tmux client to switch from the 'orchestrator' session to 'workers-orch-go' session, disrupting the orchestrator's workflow.\n\n## Symptoms\n- Dylan is in 'orchestrator' tmux session\n- Spawns headless agents (confirmed: spawn_mode=headless in events)\n- tmux suddenly switches to 'workers-orch-go' session\n- Has to manually switch back\n\n## Investigation needed\n1. What triggers the switch? (agents all ran headless, not tmux mode)\n2. Is it orch servers, daemon, or something else?\n3. Could be glass tools or playwright triggering something?\n\n## Constraint\nHeadless spawns should NEVER affect the orchestrator's tmux session.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-01-08T05:57:20.136434-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-08T06:05:51.654656-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-08T06:05:51.654656-08:00","close_reason":"Investigation complete: orch-go headless spawn code does NOT interact with tmux. Bug is external. See .kb/investigations/2026-01-08-inv-bug-worker-agents-cause-tmux.md","labels":["triage:ready"]}
{"id":"orch-go-2qiig","title":"Synthesize api investigations (11)","description":"## Synthesis Needed\n\nTopic **api** has accumulated 11 investigations that may benefit from consolidation.\n\n### Investigations to synthesize:\n\n- 2025-12-20-inv-add-api-agentlog-endpoint-serve.md\n- 2025-12-20-inv-poc-port-python-standalone-api.md\n- 2025-12-24-inv-add-api-usage-endpoint-serve.md\n- 2025-12-26-inv-add-api-errors-endpoint-error.md\n- 2025-12-26-inv-api-endpoint-api-agents-hangs.md\n- 2025-12-26-inv-evaluate-building-api-proxy-layer.md\n- 2025-12-27-inv-api-agents-endpoint-takes-19s.md\n- 2026-01-03-inv-add-api-changelog-endpoint-orch.md\n- 2026-01-03-inv-map-serve-go-api-handler.md\n- 2026-01-05-inv-pending-reviews-api-times-out.md\n- 2025-12-26-add-api-reflect-endpoint-expose.md\n\n### Chronicle Timeline\n\n```\n2025-12-19 [INV] CLI Orch Status Command\n2025-12-19 [INV] SSE Event Monitoring Client\n2025-12-19 [INV] Desktop Notifications on Completion\n2025-12-19 [INV] OpenCode POC - Spawn Session Via Go\n2025-12-19 [INV] Fix comment ID parsing - Comment.ID type mismatch\n... (run kb chronicle for full timeline)\n```\n\n### Suggested Action\n\n1. Run `kb chronicle \"api\"` to understand evolution\n2. Identify patterns and contradictions across investigations\n3. Run `kb create guide \"api\"` to create authoritative reference\n","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-06T16:17:36.486288-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-06T19:56:37.109662-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-06T19:56:37.109662-08:00","close_reason":"Duplicate synthesis issue","labels":["triage:review"]}
{"id":"orch-go-2rtc","title":"Registry file needs self-describing header","description":"## Problem\n\nWhen orchestrator tried to manually edit `~/.orch/registry.json` to clean up untracked agents, the structure was unexpected. Multiple jq attempts failed because the format wasn't documented.\n\n## Evidence (session ses_474f)\n\nLines 230-265: Orchestrator tried various jq queries assuming different structures, all failed.\n\n## Solution\n\nAdd a comment header or companion `.schema.json` explaining:\n- What each field means\n- Valid values for status/phase\n- How entries are keyed\n- What operations are safe\n\nExample header approach (JSON5 or separate file):\n```\n// Registry Schema:\n// - Key: session_id (from OpenCode)\n// - Fields: workspace, issue_id, status, phase, started_at, updated_at\n// - Status values: active, idle, completed, abandoned\n// - Safe operations: read-only; use orch commands to modify\n```\n\n## Principle\n\n**Self-Describing Artifacts** - 'If an agent encounters this file with no memory of how it was created, can they modify it correctly?' Currently: no.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-04T14:25:38.922424-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-07T17:44:56.333655-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-07T17:44:56.333655-08:00","close_reason":"Zombie reconciled","labels":["triage:ready"]}
{"id":"orch-go-2rwlf","title":"Daemon doesn't see issues with newly added labels","description":"## Problem\n\nDaemon polling doesn't pick up issues when labels are added after creation. orch-go-7rgz has `triage:ready` and `skill:feature-impl` labels but daemon log shows it's not in the 10 issues found.\n\n## Evidence\n\n```\nbd list --status open --limit 0 | grep 7rgz\norch-go-7rgz [P1] [feature] open [skill:feature-impl triage:ready] - Add periodic kb reflect to daemon\n\ntail ~/.orch/daemon.log\nDEBUG: Found 10 open issues\n# 7rgz not listed, not skipped - simply not found\n```\n\nLabels were added via `bd update --add-label` after issue creation. Daemon restart didn't help.\n\n## Likely Cause\n\n`ListReadyIssues()` in `pkg/daemon/issue_adapter.go` may be caching or using a stale query.\n\n## Success Criteria\n\n- Issues with newly added labels appear in daemon's next poll cycle\n- No restart required","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-01-06T08:50:13.408846-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-06T11:01:17.03583-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-06T11:01:17.03583-08:00","close_reason":"Root cause: bd ready defaults to limit 10. Fix: added --limit 0 to both RPC and CLI paths. Tests: go build ./... - success, test-limit-fix.go - 20 issues found (was 10). Commits: e6aeb559 (fix), 21ce441e (docs). Note: Restart daemon to apply fix: launchctl kickstart -k gui/$(id -u)/com.orch.daemon","labels":["skill:systematic-debugging"]}
{"id":"orch-go-2s2d","title":"[opencode] issue-creation: OpenCode crashes with 'No user message found in...","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-12-24T12:16:31.232383-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-25T22:51:03.430043-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-25T22:51:03.430043-08:00","close_reason":"Root cause identified in OpenCode (missing await at server.ts:1240), defensive session.error handling added to orch-go for better error visibility. All tests passing."}
{"id":"orch-go-2srug","title":"Add dashboard/serve health check to orch doctor with --fix","description":"orch doctor should check if orch serve is running and offer to fix:\n\n$ orch doctor\n❌ Dashboard server not running\n   Run: orch serve \u0026\n\n$ orch doctor --fix\n✓ Started dashboard server on :3348\n\nThis creates a gate that agents can pass (Gate Over Remind principle, passable caveat). Check port 3348, if not listening offer to start.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-01-07T09:40:56.6296-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-07T09:52:07.431784-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-07T09:52:07.431784-08:00","close_reason":"Manually verified: orch doctor shows 'orch serve (port 3348)' check, --fix flag available"}
