{"id":"orch-go-2u5m","title":"Document decision authority criteria: when agents can decide vs escalate to human","description":"Currently there's no clear documented criteria for when agents/architects can make decisions autonomously vs when to escalate to Dylan.\n\n## The Gap\n- spawn.md mentions 'Authority levels (what agent can decide vs escalate)' but doesn't define criteria\n- Orchestrator skill mentions escalation but no concrete rules\n- Result: orchestrators are overly cautious, asking Dylan about things agents could handle\n\n## Observed Pattern (implicit, needs documenting)\n\n| Escalate to Dylan | Agent can decide |\n|-------------------|------------------|\n| Strategic direction changes | Implementation details |\n| User-facing behavior changes | Internal conventions |\n| Trade-offs with unclear values | Trade-offs with clear criteria |\n| Irreversible decisions | Reversible decisions |\n| Cross-project impact | Single-project scope |\n| New capabilities/features | Refinements to existing features |\n| Resource allocation (cost, time) | Technical approach within budget |\n\n## Examples\n- Workspace naming convention → Agent can decide (implementation detail, reversible)\n- Whether to use beads for orchestrators → Dylan decides (strategic, changes mental model)\n- Which test framework to use → Agent can decide (technical, reversible)\n- Whether to support a new platform → Dylan decides (strategic, resource commitment)\n\n## Deliverables\n1. Add 'Decision Authority' section to .kb/guides/ (new file or extend existing)\n2. Update orchestrator skill to reference the criteria\n3. Update SPAWN_CONTEXT.md template to include authority level for the specific task\n\n## References\n- .kb/guides/spawn.md mentions authority but doesn't define\n- Orchestrator skill has implicit patterns","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-05T11:09:40.320062-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-05T11:25:21.854655-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-05T11:25:21.854655-08:00","close_reason":"Created .kb/guides/decision-authority.md with six-axis decision framework, decision tree, and examples. Updated spawn.md and SPAWN_CONTEXT.md template to reference the guide.","labels":["skill:feature-impl"]}
{"id":"orch-go-2vr2","title":"Glass: Form state clears when clicking other elements","description":"When using Glass to fill out the config editor form, entering text in Name/Description fields gets cleared when clicking quantity or competitor toggle buttons. Suggests the page is re-rendering or state management issue in the SvelteKit form.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2025-12-29T15:06:28.973505-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-03T14:24:28.33217-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-03T14:24:28.33217-08:00","close_reason":"Already completed: Could not reproduce form state clearing issue. Tested via Glass: Config Name field persisted through"}
{"id":"orch-go-2wq6m","title":"CI gate for bloat control","description":"Create GitHub Actions workflow that fails if modified files exceed 800 lines.\n\n**Design:** .kb/investigations/2026-01-23-inv-design-bloat-control-system-800.md\n\n**Implementation:**\n- .github/workflows/bloat-check.yml\n- Check line count of files modified in PR\n- Fail if any modified file exceeds threshold\n- Consider: distinguish 'was already bloated' vs 'this PR made it bloated'\n\n**Intra-task decisions (worker authority per kb-768886):**\n- Test file handling\n- Threshold (800 block or 1500 block with 800 warn)\n- How to handle already-bloated files\n- Vendored/generated code exclusions\n\n**Provenance:** Bloat control design session 2026-01-23","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-23T16:21:17.673638-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-23T16:54:05.802806-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-23T16:54:05.802806-08:00","close_reason":"Phase: Complete - Created .github/workflows/bloat-check.yml CI gate that fails PRs increasing file size past 800 lines, with base branch comparison to allow existing bloat fixes. Tests: N/A - workflow executes on GitHub, not locally testable.","labels":["triage:ready"]}
{"id":"orch-go-2x7u5","title":"Make investigation file mandate conditional on skill type","description":"## Context\nInvestigation orch-go-fkn0p found SPAWN_CONTEXT template mandates investigation files for ALL spawns (line 220-222). This causes investigation over-production for implementation tasks.\n\n## Change\nModify pkg/spawn/context.go template to only mandate investigation files for investigation-type skills:\n- investigation\n- architect  \n- research\n\nSkills that should NOT mandate investigation files:\n- feature-impl\n- systematic-debugging\n\n## Implementation\nAdd conditional in template generation based on skill type. Something like:\n```go\nif isInvestigationSkill(config.SkillName) {\n    // include investigation file mandate\n}\n```\n\n## Reference\n- Decision: .kb/decisions/2026-01-23-investigation-overhead-firefighting-mode.md\n- Investigation: .kb/investigations/2026-01-23-inv-so-many-investigations-created-root.md","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-23T19:45:50.788234-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-23T19:54:22.148771-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-23T19:54:22.148771-08:00","close_reason":"Phase: Complete - Added IsInvestigationSkill helper and conditional template logic. Investigation-type skills (investigation, architect, research, codebase-audit) mandate investigation files; implementation skills (feature-impl, systematic-debugging) do not. Tests: go build ./... - successful, manual verification script passed all assertions.","labels":["triage:ready"]}
{"id":"orch-go-2y1ag","title":"Update orchestrator-session-lifecycle model with 4 Evolution entries","description":"orchestrator-session-lifecycle.md has stale/unclear content needing Evolution section updates.\n\n**Updates needed:**\n\n1. **Tactical → Strategic framing**\n   - Current: 'Orchestrators do tactical execution'  \n   - Fix: 'Orchestrators do strategic comprehension (COMPREHEND → TRIAGE → SYNTHESIZE)'\n   - Reason: Strategic Orchestrator Model (Jan 7) changed this\n\n2. **Token usage constraint**\n   - Add: 'Agents cannot observe their own token usage. Duration-based thresholds (2h/3h/4h) serve as proxy for context consumption.'\n   - Reference: .kb/investigations/2026-01-06-inv-orchestrator-sessions-checkpoint-discipline-max.md line 75\n\n3. **Clarify skill-type: policy meaning**\n   - Current: 'Skills with skill-type: policy trigger orchestrator context generation, which sets behavioral mode through framing, not instructions.'\n   - Fix: Expand with example of framing vs instructions difference\n   - Worker instructions: 'TASK: Implement X'\n   - Orchestrator framing: 'You are an orchestrator. COMPREHEND → TRIAGE → SYNTHESIZE'\n\n4. **Resume protocol status**\n   - Add: 'Resume protocol designed but not yet implemented. Session registry supports lookups, ORCHESTRATOR_CONTEXT.md has resume guidance, but orch resume command pending (see orch-go-xyz).'\n   - Mark which parts are design vs implemented\n\n**Deliverable:** Evolution section with 4 timestamped entries (2026-01-13)","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-13T08:09:32.697376-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-14T20:22:26.882923-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-14T20:22:26.882923-08:00","close_reason":"Work completed (commit 330fadcb) but agent didn't run exit workflow","labels":["triage:ready"]}
{"id":"orch-go-2yzjl","title":"Is the Question vs Gate distinction crisp, or is the boundary fuzzy?","status":"closed","priority":3,"issue_type":"question","created_at":"2026-01-19T14:07:15.958044-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-19T14:47:19.641887-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-19T14:47:19.641887-08:00","close_reason":"Phase: Complete - Question/Gate distinction is crisp but dynamic (lifecycle-based). Questions have unknown option spaces; Gates have known options requiring commitment. Same issue transitions from Question to Gate as understanding develops. Provided sharpened criteria table and lifecycle test."}
{"id":"orch-go-2z9k4","title":"What is the right substrate for decidability graphs?","description":"## The Question\n\nBeads (fork) is currently the substrate for work tracking. As we develop decidability graph concepts (questions, gates, frontier-awareness), should we:\n1. Continue extending beads\n2. Replace with a simpler model (e.g., directory of markdown files)\n3. Build something purpose-designed for decidability semantics\n4. Something else\n\n## Why This Matters\n\nThis question has come up repeatedly:\n- **Dec 2025:** \"Clean Slate\" decision - dropped unused local features, use upstream\n- **Jan 2026:** Added `question` entity type to fork - now diverging from upstream\n- **Jan 19, 2026:** Decidability graph model raises substrate question again\n\nEach time we touch beads, we're implicitly choosing to extend it rather than replace it. That's fine if beads is the right substrate - but we've never explicitly decided.\n\n## What Beads Currently Provides\n\n- JSONL storage format\n- SQLite for querying\n- CLI (`bd`) for operations\n- Dependencies between issues\n- Status lifecycle (open/in_progress/closed)\n- Comments as integration hub\n- Sync with git\n\n## What Decidability Graphs Need\n\n- Work nodes (issues) ✓ beads has this\n- Question nodes ✓ added to fork\n- Gate nodes (option-space decisions) - not yet\n- Dependency edges ✓ beads has this\n- Blocking semantics (questions block work) - partial\n- Frontier queries (`bd ready`) ✓ beads has this\n- Authority annotations - not yet\n\n## Alternative Substrates to Consider\n\n### A. Directory of Markdown Files\n```\n.work/\n├── issues/\n│   └── {id}.md\n├── questions/\n│   └── {id}.md\n└── gates/\n    └── {id}.md\n```\n- **Pro:** Human-readable, git-native, no tooling needed to inspect\n- **Pro:** Each entity is a self-contained file\n- **Con:** No query capability without building it\n- **Con:** Relationships harder to express\n\n### B. SQLite-only (drop JSONL)\n- **Pro:** Better query performance, proper relations\n- **Con:** Not human-readable, harder to debug\n- **Con:** Beads uses both (JSONL for git, SQLite for queries)\n\n### C. Graph Database (embedded)\n- **Pro:** Native graph semantics (edges, traversal)\n- **Con:** Complexity, learning curve, tooling\n\n### D. Purpose-Built Decidability Substrate\n- **Pro:** Exactly what we need, nothing more\n- **Con:** Build cost, maintenance burden\n\n### E. Continue Extending Beads Fork\n- **Pro:** Already works, sunk cost\n- **Con:** Diverging from upstream, carrying assumptions\n\n## Questions to Answer\n\n1. What fraction of beads do we actually use?\n2. What beads assumptions are fighting us?\n3. What would a minimal decidability substrate look like?\n4. Is frontier-awareness a substrate concern or orchestrator concern?\n5. What's the rebuild cost vs. extension cost?\n\n## Dependencies\n\nThis question should block:\n- Further beads fork extensions\n- Decidability graph implementation work\n- Dashboard graph visualization\n\n## How to Close This Question\n\nInvestigate options, make explicit tradeoff analysis, produce decision document.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"question","created_at":"2026-01-19T16:20:20.464155-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-19T16:27:36.668506-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-19T16:27:36.668506-08:00","close_reason":"Phase: Complete - Recommend extending beads fork with 3 targeted changes (authority on edges, resolution typing, answered-unblocking). Investigation shows beads provides 85% of decidability needs; rebuild costs 2-4x higher for alternatives."}
{"id":"orch-go-2zesu","title":"Extend daemon to run open reflection with issue creation","description":"## Problem\n\nDaemon only runs synthesis reflection with issue creation. Open type (investigations with forgotten Next: actions) should also auto-create issues.\n\n## Solution\n\n1. Add ReflectOpenEnabled config (default: true when ReflectCreateIssues is true)\n2. Add open reflection to daemon run loop (hourly, same as synthesis)\n3. Call kb reflect --type open --create-issue\n\n## Blocked By\n\n**kb-cli-538**: Add --create-issue support for open type in kb reflect\n\nThis issue cannot be implemented until kb-cli supports `kb reflect --type open --create-issue`.\n\n## Success Criteria\n\n- Investigations \u003e3 days with unimplemented Next: actions get triage:review issues\n- No false positives from paused or just-created investigations","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-01-06T12:09:18.459759-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-07T15:38:56.551535-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-07T15:38:56.551535-08:00","close_reason":"No longer relevant per decision 2026-01-07-synthesis-is-strategic-orchestrator-work. Auto-issue creation caused duplicate noise. Reflection opportunities now surfaced via orch status instead.","labels":["triage:backlog"]}
{"id":"orch-go-2zzpm","title":"Synthesize headless investigations (15)","description":"## Synthesis Needed\n\nTopic **headless** has accumulated 15 investigations that may benefit from consolidation.\n\n### Investigations to synthesize:\n\n- 2025-12-20-inv-implement-headless-spawn-mode-add.md\n- 2025-12-20-inv-make-headless-mode-default-deprecate.md\n- 2025-12-20-inv-scope-out-headless-swarm-implementation.md\n- 2025-12-21-inv-headless-spawn-not-sending-prompts.md\n- 2025-12-22-debug-headless-spawns-not-discoverable-by-beads-id.md\n- 2025-12-22-inv-headless-spawn-mode-readiness-what.md\n- 2025-12-22-inv-headless-spawn-registers-wrong-project.md\n- 2025-12-23-debug-headless-spawn-model-format.md\n- 2025-12-23-inv-headless-spawn-does-not-pass.md\n- 2025-12-23-inv-orch-status-shows-headless-agents.md\n- 2025-12-23-inv-token-limit-explosion-headless-spawn.md\n- 2025-12-22-inv-test-headless-mode.md\n- 2025-12-22-inv-test-headless-spawn-list-files.md\n- 2025-12-22-inv-test-headless-spawn.md\n- 2025-12-23-inv-test-headless-spawn-after-fix.md\n\n### Chronicle Timeline\n\n```\n2025-12-20 [INV] Legacy Artifacts Synthesis Protocol Alignment\n2025-12-20 [INV] Enhance status command with swarm progress\n2025-12-20 [INV] Fix Spawn to Use Standalone Mode with TUI\n2025-12-20 [INV] Implement Headless Spawn Mode\n2025-12-20 [INV] Make Headless Mode Default for Spawn\n... (run kb chronicle for full timeline)\n```\n\n### Suggested Action\n\n1. Run `kb chronicle \"headless\"` to understand evolution\n2. Identify patterns and contradictions across investigations\n3. Create a synthesized decision or consolidated investigation\n","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-08T07:35:04.297997-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-08T10:11:02.044189-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-08T10:11:02.044189-08:00","close_reason":"Synthesis is orchestrator work, not spawnable. Auto-creation disabled per decision 2026-01-07-synthesis-is-strategic-orchestrator-work.md","labels":["triage:review"]}
