{"id":"orch-go-36b","title":"[orch-go] design-session: Dashboard needs better agent activity visibilit...","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-12-21T00:54:36.495597-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-22T20:52:18.39691-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-22T20:52:18.39691-08:00","close_reason":"Implemented three UI improvements for better agent visibility: error count in stats bar (red highlighting), expanded event panels (64px height, 12px font, 20 events), and bold error messages. All changes validated with TypeScript check, successful build, and Playwright tests."}
{"id":"orch-go-38c6","title":"Cross-project agent visibility: fetch beads comments from agent's project, not current directory","description":"When viewing agents from different projects (e.g., skillc agent from orch-go dashboard), beads comments aren't found because bd commands run in current directory. Need to: 1) Store project path in agent metadata, 2) Fetch comments from correct repo, or 3) Use a cross-repo beads query. Currently agents from other projects show no phase info.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2025-12-24T10:58:40.914432-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-25T20:31:31.663815-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-25T20:31:31.663815-08:00","close_reason":"Added project-aware beads comment fetching: GetCommentsWithDir, GetCommentsBatchWithProjectDirs, extractProjectDirFromWorkspace. Cross-project visibility now works.","labels":["skill:feature-impl","triage:ready"]}
{"id":"orch-go-38zik","title":"Interactive orchestrator sessions don't create workspaces or SESSION_HANDOFF.md","description":"## Problem\nInteractive orchestrator sessions (opened directly via opencode/oc) don't get workspaces like spawned sessions do. This means:\n- No SESSION_HANDOFF.md on exit\n- No .session_id file linking to OpenCode session\n- Session context lost on exit\n\n## Impact\nSession amnesia - next orchestrator has no context about what was done.\n\n## Contrast\nSpawned orchestrators via `orch spawn orchestrator` DO get workspaces with ORCHESTRATOR_CONTEXT.md and produce SESSION_HANDOFF.md.\n\n## Potential Solutions\n1. OpenCode plugin that creates workspace on session.created for orchestrator sessions\n2. `orch session start` creates workspace (already has some of this?)\n3. Manual discipline (current workaround)\n\n## Reference\nDiscovered in session 2026-01-06 while wrapping up.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-01-06T11:38:53.209076-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-06T13:09:24.417907-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-06T13:09:24.417907-08:00","close_reason":"Fixed interactive orchestrator sessions not creating workspaces. Added createSessionWorkspace() to session.go that creates ~/.orch/session/{date}/SESSION_HANDOFF.md on orch session start. Tests: go test ./pkg/session/... ./pkg/spawn/... - all 178 tests passing. Smoke test verified workspace creation works.","labels":["triage:ready"]}
{"id":"orch-go-391i","title":"Workspace names should include distinguishing task keywords","description":"Similar workspace names like 'og-feat-fix-dashboard-show-24dec' and 'og-feat-fix-dashboard-status-24dec' are confusing in the UI. Consider: 1) Include more task keywords in name generation, 2) Use beads issue title hash, or 3) Let orchestrator provide custom suffix. Goal: at-a-glance differentiation.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-12-24T10:58:43.675922-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-25T13:07:16.453483-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-25T13:07:16.453483-08:00","close_reason":"Investigated in orch-go-ya22 - naming from task slug at spawn"}
{"id":"orch-go-39jx","title":"[orch-go] investigation: Dashboard requirements: What questions should i...","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-12-30T13:08:15.617424-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-30T13:19:08.552237-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-30T13:19:08.552237-08:00","close_reason":"Dashboard requirements investigation complete. Key finding: Dylan's 5 questions collapse to one ('What needs my attention?'). Recommends killing Ops/History modes in favor of attention-based design with consolidated Attention Panel. Full section verdicts in investigation file."}
