{"id":"orch-go-3dem","title":"[orch-go] Redesign orch status output to be actionable","description":"Current problems: (1) Shows 62 'active' but most are phantoms - can't tell what's actually running, (2) All show 'unknown' runtime, (3) SESSION ID just shows 'tmux' - not useful, (4) WINDOW truncated to 'workers...', (5) BEADS ID truncated, (6) No PHASE column (Investigating/Implementing/Complete), (7) No phantom indicator despite IsPhantom() existing, (8) No task description. Proposed output: separate Active vs Phantom counts, show phase from beads comments, show task description, real runtime, actionable window IDs, add filter flags (--active-only, --project, --phantoms). Default should hide phantoms and only show truly active agents.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2025-12-22T10:36:31.775749-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-25T22:14:46.090231-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-25T22:14:46.090231-08:00","close_reason":"Batch close from orch review"}
