{"id":"orch-go-3ih8","title":"Replace duplicate agent counts with usage progress bars in stats bar","description":"## Problem\n\nStats bar shows active/recent/archive counts that are already visible in Swarm Map section headers. This wastes horizontal space (critical at 666px width constraint).\n\n## Solution\n\nReplace agent count section with usage progress bars:\n- Before: `1 active | 25 recent | 184 archive | 0 errors`\n- After: `[████░░] 64% hr ↻5hr | [██░░░░] 28% wk | 0 errors`\n\n## Design\n\nProgress bars for hourly and weekly usage:\n- Green (\u003c50%), Yellow (50-80%), Red (\u003e80%)\n- Show reset time for hourly (the constraining limit)\n- Compact format to fit 666px width\n\n## Keep\n- 0 errors (not duplicated)\n- focused indicator\n- beads ready/blocked  \n- servers status\n- @personal account indicator\n\n## Remove\n- active count (shown in Active section header)\n- recent count (shown in Recent section header)\n- archive count (shown in Archive section header)\n\n## Files\n- web/src/routes/+page.svelte - stats bar layout","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2025-12-24T14:52:19.027462-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-26T12:36:49.558844-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-26T12:36:49.558844-08:00","close_reason":"Replaced duplicate active/recent/archive counts with usage progress bars showing hourly and weekly limits with reset times. Extended /api/usage to include reset times. Commit e708c66."}
{"id":"orch-go-3k0j5","title":"Implement decidability substrate extensions in beads fork","description":"## Context\n\nInvestigation `2026-01-19-design-investigate-substrate-options-decidability-graphs.md` recommended extending beads with 3 targeted additions. This was theoretical until **2026-01-22 when we hit a live instance**: a worker cited a superseded decision because there's no graph-based way to know decisions have lifecycle.\n\n## Live Validation (Jan 22)\n\n- GLM research worker cited Jan 9 decision (\"Gemini Flash primary\")\n- That decision was **superseded** by Jan 18 decision (\"Claude Max via CLI primary\")\n- Worker had no way to know - decisions lack lifecycle metadata\n- Result: Investigation contains incorrect information about current model stack\n\n**This proves:** Decisions are decidability nodes. They have supersedes edges, authority levels, and frontier queries (current state). The substrate isn't theoretical - we're hitting real errors without it.\n\n## Implementation (from investigation)\n\n### 1. Wire `answered` status to unblock dependencies\n- Modify `GetBlockingDependencies()` to treat `answered` like `closed`\n- Enables question lifecycle without forcing immediate close\n- Also enables: `superseded` status for decisions\n\n### 2. Add authority field to dependency edges\n- Schema: `authority: \"daemon\" | \"orchestrator\" | \"dylan\"`\n- CLI: `bd dep add X Y --authority orchestrator`\n- Query: `bd ready --authority daemon`\n- Also enables: `bd dep add decision-new decision-old --type supersedes`\n\n### 3. Add resolution_type to questions (and decisions)\n- Schema: `resolution_type: \"factual\" | \"judgment\" | \"framing\" | null`\n- For decisions: `domain: \"model-selection\" | \"spawn-architecture\" | ...`\n- Enables: `bd ready --type decision --domain model-selection` → current HEAD\n\n## Success Criteria\n\n- [ ] `answered` or `superseded` status unblocks dependent work\n- [ ] Edges can have authority and type metadata\n- [ ] `bd ready --type decision --domain X` returns current (non-superseded) decisions\n- [ ] Dashboard shows decision lifecycle (active vs superseded)\n\n## Reference\n\n- `.kb/investigations/2026-01-19-design-investigate-substrate-options-decidability-graphs.md`\n- `.kb/models/decidability-graph.md`\n- `.kb/investigations/2026-01-22-inv-research-glm-ai-orchestration-context.md` (the error that validated this)\n- `orch-go-htxgc` (manual hygiene fix while substrate is built)","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-01-22T05:24:31.155795887Z","updated_at":"2026-01-22T13:41:41.259441-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-22T13:41:41.259441-08:00","close_reason":"Decidability substrate extensions implemented - confirmed by Dylan","labels":["triage:ready"]}
{"id":"orch-go-3k8t","title":"[orch-go] meta-orchestrator: Continue managing orchestrator sessions. Prior ...","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-04T19:33:57.548004-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-04T19:40:54.095776-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-04T19:40:54.095776-08:00","close_reason":"Meta-orchestrator continuation - superseded by current session"}
{"id":"orch-go-3l2tc","title":"Fix session discovery to scan all windows when current window has no history","description":"discoverSessionHandoff() needs cross-window scan between current-window check and legacy fallback. Scan all .orch/session/*/latest, pick most recent by timestamp. Enables: same window = window history (isolation), new window = most recent across all (convenience).","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-01-13T19:31:33.816395-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-14T10:34:35.03077-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-14T10:34:35.03077-08:00","close_reason":"Root cause: missing cross-window scan in discovery flow. Fix: added scanAllWindowsForMostRecent() helper and inserted call between current-window check and legacy fallback. Tests: go test ./cmd/orch -run 'Session|Handoff' - 10 passed, 0 failed (includes new TestDiscoverSessionHandoff_CrossWindowScan)"}
