{"id":"orch-go-3o962","title":"Add workspace_path tracking to session.json","description":"## Enhancement\n\nOptional improvement to session tracking:\n\n- Add workspace_path field to Session struct in pkg/session/session.go\n- Update createSessionWorkspace() to save workspace path to session.json\n- Display workspace location in 'orch session status' output\n- Enable 'orch session end' to easily find/validate workspace\n\n## Context\n\nCurrent implementation creates workspaces at ~/.orch/session/{date}/ but doesn't track the path in session.json. This works fine but could be more discoverable.\n\n## Priority\n\nP3 - Nice to have, not blocking. Current implementation is functional without this.","status":"closed","priority":3,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-09T14:56:32.388546-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-18T08:19:34.767342-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-18T08:19:34.767342-08:00","close_reason":"Phase: Complete - Workspace path tracking feature verified complete. WorkspacePath field exists in Session struct, captured at session start, persisted to session.json, and displayed in both text and JSON outputs. All manual tests passed. Investigation and SYNTHESIS.md committed.","labels":["triage:ready"]}
