{"id":"orch-go-3t8p","title":"Completed agents shouldn't count against concurrency limit","description":"Bug: orch spawn hits concurrency limit (5) even when 3 of those agents are idle at Phase: Complete. Completed agents should be excluded from the active count since they're not consuming resources. Current behavior forces --max-agents workaround or manual cleanup of sessions that are already done.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-12-24T09:15:12.287165-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-24T10:01:48.883903-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-24T10:01:48.883903-08:00","close_reason":"Fixed concurrency limit to exclude Phase: Complete agents. Added check in checkConcurrencyLimit() that calls verify.IsPhaseComplete() to skip counting completed sessions. All tests pass, committed as d0eae36.","labels":["triage:ready"]}
