{"id":"orch-go-3ujo","title":"Add missing orch commands to CLAUDE.md and orchestrator skill","description":"Investigation found 12+ undocumented commands. Priority order:\n\nP0 (orchestrators need these):\n- orch servers init/up/down/gen-plist - launchd integration for dev servers\n- orch kb ask - inline KB queries (5-10 sec vs spawning agents)\n- orch sessions list/search/show - find past sessions/decisions\n- orch doctor - health checks\n\nP1:\n- orch lint, synthesis, tokens, swarm, port, handoff\n\nSee: .kb/investigations/2025-12-28-inv-critical-meta-gap-orch-features.md","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2025-12-28T12:36:07.232142-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-28T13:15:50.786139-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-28T13:15:50.786139-08:00","close_reason":"Added 12+ missing orch commands to both CLAUDE.md and orchestrator skill. P0 commands: servers init/up/down/gen-plist, kb ask/extract, sessions list/search/show, doctor. P1 commands: lint, tokens, synthesis, swarm, handoff, port. CLAUDE.md verified within limits (2825/15000 tokens). Orchestrator skill rebuilt (19003 tokens). Leave it Better: kn-9e2f0f recorded need for periodic documentation audits.","labels":["triage:ready"]}
{"id":"orch-go-3ukg","title":"Dashboard shows stale/dead agents after OpenCode restart - doesn't clear old sessions","description":"After restarting OpenCode, the dashboard continues showing old dead agents as 'Active Agents' with 'Dead - needs attention' status. The CLI (orch status) shows correct data, but the dashboard at localhost:5188 shows 4 stale agents that should have been cleared. This appears to be a sync issue between the dashboard's SSE connection and the registry state after OpenCode restarts.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2025-12-30T16:57:44.315287-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-30T17:17:20.057206-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-30T17:17:20.057206-08:00","close_reason":"Investigation found threshold already aligned (3 min). The 'stale agents' shown on dashboard are from OpenCode's session persistence - dead sessions are intentionally shown in Active section for user attention. Not a bug, working as designed."}
{"id":"orch-go-3wgmo","title":"Research OpenCode Zen/Black architecture and economics","description":"Investigate how OpenCode Zen/Black actually works:\n\nQuestions to answer:\n1. Architecture - Just a proxy or running compute?\n2. Economics - How do they make /mo flat rate work with Opus //MTok pricing?\n3. Bulk deals - Do providers (Anthropic, OpenAI, Google) give resellers cheaper rates?\n4. Usage limits - What caps exist (if any) on the /mo tier?\n5. Sustainability - Is this viable long-term or subsidized land-grab?\n6. Infrastructure - What compute/serving do they actually run?\n\nContext:\n- OpenCode Black launched Jan 6, sold out in 30s\n- /mo for access to claude-opus-4-5 and ~20 other models\n- No usage meters disclosed yet\n- Community skeptical about economics\n\nSources to check:\n- OpenCode docs/GitHub for Zen architecture\n- Twitter posts from @opencode about Black\n- Community discussions on pricing/limits\n- Any technical docs on how gateway works","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-13T16:34:20.35309-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-13T16:42:19.991434-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-13T16:42:19.991434-08:00","close_reason":"Research investigation complete. OpenCode Zen = potentially viable cooperative (pending transparency), OpenCode Black = temporary drama. Recommendation: maintain status quo. Investigation: .kb/investigations/2026-01-13-research-opencode-zen-black-architecture-economics.md"}
