{"id":"orch-go-44aes","title":"Clean up stale beadsClient when daemon socket disappears","description":"## Problem\nWhen beads daemon stops or crashes, the beadsClient reference in orch serve becomes stale. Subsequent RPC attempts may hang or timeout before falling back to CLI.\n\n## Current Behavior\n- Socket existence check added to short-circuit when daemon not running\n- But beadsClient itself may still hold stale connection state\n- Reconnect logic has exponential backoff adding latency\n\n## Expected Behavior\n- Detect when daemon socket disappears\n- Clear/reset beadsClient state\n- Next request should immediately fall back to CLI or attempt fresh connection\n\n## Reference\n- .kb/investigations/2026-01-07-inv-api-beads-endpoint-takes-5s.md\n- pkg/beads/client.go (RPC client with auto-reconnect)\n- cmd/orch/serve_beads.go (socket existence check)","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-01-07T11:02:26.231522-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-09T18:14:52.394718-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-09T18:14:52.394718-08:00","close_reason":"Fixed stale beadsClient with socket-aware lifecycle management (cleanup on disappear + reinit on reappear) and mutex protection. Tests: go build (success), go test ./... (2 pre-existing failures unrelated - TestIntegration_ChildID_Comments, TestResolve_Aliases). Commit: 4735e16c. Manual verification needed: start orch serve, stop/start beads daemon, verify no hangs."}
