{"id":"orch-go-46yq2","title":"[orch-go] architect: Research OpenAI's potential partnership with Op...","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-20T17:42:35.043907-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-20T17:48:35.093956-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-20T17:48:35.093956-08:00","close_reason":"Phase: Complete - OpenAI is officially collaborating with OpenCode (opposite of Anthropic). GPT-5.2 Codex and 22 model variants available via plugin at same $200/mo cost. Recommend adding OpenAI as secondary backend option. Investigation: .kb/investigations/2026-01-21-inv-research-openai-potential-partnership-opencode.md"}
{"id":"orch-go-47k35","title":"Dashboard: collapsible sections should persist state across refreshes","description":"## Problem\n\nCollapsible sections (Active, Recent, Archive) reset to default state on page refresh. User has to re-expand/collapse every time.\n\n## Solution\n\nStore collapsed/expanded state in localStorage keyed by section name. Restore on page load.\n\n## Implementation\n\n```typescript\n// On toggle\nlocalStorage.setItem('dashboard-section-active', collapsed ? 'collapsed' : 'expanded')\n\n// On load\nconst state = localStorage.getItem('dashboard-section-active') ?? 'expanded'\n```","status":"closed","priority":3,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-01-06T13:35:10.278494-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-06T14:51:48.803426-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-06T14:51:48.803426-08:00","close_reason":"Fixed dashboard collapsible section state not persisting across page refresh. Root cause was reactive statement firing during initialization, overwriting stored preferences. Added sectionStateLoaded flag to prevent saves until after initial load. 3 new Playwright tests confirm fix works."}
