{"id":"orch-go-4bi3","title":"Implement symlink-based install in orch-go Makefile","description":"Phase 1 of stale binary solution. Update Makefile to use symlinks instead of copy for install target.\n\n## Context\nDecision: .kb/decisions/2025-12-28-stale-binary-solution.md\n\n## Changes Required\n1. Change install target from `cp` to `ln -sf`\n2. Ensure build directory exists before symlinking\n3. Update README with new pattern\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `make install` creates symlink `~/bin/orch` → `build/orch`\n- [ ] `make build` followed by `orch version` shows new version\n- [ ] README documents the symlink pattern","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-12-28T13:08:36.64304-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-01T14:19:04.955575-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-01T14:19:04.955575-08:00","close_reason":"Already implemented - symlink pattern was already in Makefile"}
