{"id":"orch-go-4f0s4","title":"Phase 3.5: Bidirectional Pattern Detection (Dylan patterns)","description":"Extend coaching.ts to detect Dylan's behavioral patterns in addition to orchestrator patterns. Coach watches BOTH sides of conversation. MVP scope: explicit prefixes (compensation:, frame-collapse:, focus:, step-back:), priority uncertainty (\"what's next?\" 2+ times), compensation pattern (repeated context via keyword similarity). Emit Dylan metrics (compensation_pattern, priority_uncertainty, dylan_signal_prefix) to coach session. Coach intervention targets Dylan, orchestrator, or both based on pattern. Defer complex patterns (deference, tool experience gap, frustration peak timing) to later iteration. Reference: Meta-Orchestrator Interface section in orchestrator skill, two-tier sensing pattern guide (.kb/guides/two-tier-sensing-pattern.md). Extends coaching.ts (~/.config/opencode/plugin/coaching.ts) with experimental.chat.messages.transform for user message parsing.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-10T15:13:15.145173-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-10T15:21:19.180422-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-10T15:21:19.180422-08:00","close_reason":"Cross-repo work: Extended ~/.config/opencode/plugin/coaching.ts with chat.messages.transform hook for Dylan pattern detection (explicit prefixes, priority uncertainty, compensation patterns). Investigation file shows phase Complete with TypeScript compilation verified. All three pattern types implemented and wired to coach session streaming."}
