{"id":"orch-go-4gxrr","title":"Dashboard shows wrong investigation artifact for cross-project agents","description":"**Pattern:** Second occurrence of this bug - cross-project artifact path confusion.\n\n**Expected:** Investigation tab should show the investigation file from the agent's project (scs-slack), referenced in SYNTHESIS.md\n\n**Actual:** Shows an unrelated investigation from orch-go (the orchestration home project)\n\n**Likely cause:** Investigation file lookup not scoped to agent's workdir/project - may be searching globally or defaulting to orch-go's .kb/","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-01-08T13:46:59.416624-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-08T13:55:45.229995-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-08T13:55:45.229995-08:00","close_reason":"Phase: Complete - Fixed cross-project investigation tab bug by guarding auto-discovery with hasReliableProjectDir flag. Root cause: session directory unreliable for --workdir spawns."}
{"id":"orch-go-4gy3j","title":"Demote Cytoscape graph to optional deep-dive","description":"The Cytoscape graph view becomes secondary to the readable frontier view.\n\n**Changes:**\n- Move graph from primary nav to \"Advanced\" or submenu\n- Or: keep as tab but frontier section is default/prominent\n- Update graph epic description to reflect this pivot\n\n**Context:** Graph was built but didn't match vision. \"Readable first, graphical second\" - the text frontier view is primary, graph is for exploration when needed.\n\n**Not urgent** - graph still works, just not the primary interface.","status":"closed","priority":3,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-24T08:14:59.729441-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-24T10:58:56.711567-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-24T10:58:56.711567-08:00"}
{"id":"orch-go-4hwk","title":"Dashboard artifact viewer doesn't find cross-project investigation files","description":"When viewing a completed agent from another project (e.g., pw-4014 from price-watch while dashboard runs from orch-go), the Investigation tab fails to load with 404.\n\n## Root Cause\nArtifact API only searches current project's directories:\n- .orch/workspace/{name}/SYNTHESIS.md\n- .kb/investigations/\n\nBut cross-project agents have their artifacts in the source project's directories.\n\n## Example\nAgent: og-inv-kb-setup-audit-30dec [pw-4014]\nInvestigation at: price-watch/.kb/investigations/2025-12-30-inv-kb-setup-audit-price-watch.md\nAPI searches: orch-go/.kb/investigations/ (wrong project)\n\n## Possible Solutions\n1. Store PROJECT_DIR in agent metadata, use it to resolve artifact paths\n2. Parse beads ID prefix (pw- vs orch-go-) to infer project\n3. Search all known project directories for artifacts\n\n## Related\n- Fixed workspace ID suffix bug: 32cf0792\n- Cross-project agent visibility already works for status/phase","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2025-12-30T15:29:48.093987-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-01T14:31:55.945513-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-01T14:31:55.945513-08:00","close_reason":"Fixed cross-project investigation/decision file discovery"}
