{"id":"orch-go-4m1y","title":"[orch-go] design-session: Skill change taxonomy - when do skill modificat...","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-12-27T12:38:53.261916-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-27T12:43:34.232351-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-27T12:43:34.232351-08:00","close_reason":"Created skill change taxonomy with decision tree based on blast radius (local/cross-skill/infrastructure) and change type (documentation/behavioral/structural). ~80% of changes are direct-implementable. Investigation at .kb/investigations/2025-12-27-inv-skill-change-taxonomy.md"}
{"id":"orch-go-4m867","title":"Synthesize api investigations (13)","description":"## Synthesis Needed\n\nTopic **api** has accumulated 13 investigations that may benefit from consolidation.\n\n### Investigations to synthesize:\n\n- 2025-12-20-inv-add-api-agentlog-endpoint-serve.md\n- 2025-12-20-inv-poc-port-python-standalone-api.md\n- 2025-12-24-inv-add-api-usage-endpoint-serve.md\n- 2025-12-26-inv-add-api-errors-endpoint-error.md\n- 2025-12-26-inv-api-endpoint-api-agents-hangs.md\n- 2025-12-26-inv-evaluate-building-api-proxy-layer.md\n- 2025-12-27-inv-api-agents-endpoint-takes-19s.md\n- 2026-01-03-inv-add-api-changelog-endpoint-orch.md\n- 2026-01-03-inv-map-serve-go-api-handler.md\n- 2026-01-05-inv-pending-reviews-api-times-out.md\n- 2026-01-07-inv-api-beads-endpoint-takes-5s.md\n- 2026-01-08-inv-backend-sends-last-activity-api.md\n- 2025-12-26-add-api-reflect-endpoint-expose.md\n\n### Chronicle Timeline\n\n```\n2025-12-19 [INV] SSE Event Monitoring Client\n2025-12-19 [INV] Desktop Notifications on Completion\n2025-12-19 [INV] OpenCode POC - Spawn Session Via Go\n2025-12-19 [INV] Fix comment ID parsing - Comment.ID type mismatch\n2025-12-19 [INV] CLI Orch Status Command\n... (run kb chronicle for full timeline)\n```\n\n### Suggested Action\n\n1. Run `kb chronicle \"api\"` to understand evolution\n2. Identify patterns and contradictions across investigations\n3. Create a synthesized decision or consolidated investigation\n","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-08T07:35:04.510734-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-08T10:11:02.020894-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-08T10:11:02.020894-08:00","close_reason":"Synthesis is orchestrator work, not spawnable. Auto-creation disabled per decision 2026-01-07-synthesis-is-strategic-orchestrator-work.md","labels":["triage:review"]}
{"id":"orch-go-4mxx","title":"Active agents constantly reorder as they update, causing visual instability","description":"## Problem\n\nActive agents in the Swarm Map fight for position as they update, causing jarring visual jumps. The gold-highlighted active cards rapidly swap positions.\n\n## Evidence\n\nScreenshot shows 4 active agents. As each updates (every few seconds), they jump around in the grid.\n\n## Expected\n\nActive agents should maintain stable positions. Either:\n- Sort once on initial render, then maintain position\n- Sort by a stable key (beads ID, spawn time) rather than last update time\n\n## Files\n- web/src/routes/+page.svelte - agent grid rendering and sorting logic","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2025-12-24T14:23:38.305047-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-24T14:32:26.123105-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-24T14:32:26.123105-08:00","close_reason":"Fixed active agents grid reordering by using spawned_at (stable) instead of updated_at (volatile) for secondary sort. Removed dead code (unused filteredAgents). All tests pass."}
