{"id":"orch-go-4oh7","title":"Epic: Orchestrator behavioral self-correction","description":"Enable orchestrator to detect and correct repeated behavioral mistakes without human intervention.\n\nRoot cause: Tool outcomes are ephemeral - no feedback loop exists for 'you tried X 3 times with empty result'.\n\nCurrent mechanisms track knowledge state (kn, kb, orch learn) but not action outcomes. Self-correction requires: action → outcome → pattern detection → adjustment.\n\nImplementation sequence:\n1. Action logging subsystem (~/.orch/action-log.jsonl)\n2. Pattern analyzer (extend learning.go)\n3. Surfacing mechanism (orch patterns or SessionStart injection)\n\nSee investigation: .kb/investigations/2025-12-27-inv-orchestrator-self-correction-mechanisms-problem.md","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"epic","created_at":"2025-12-27T12:24:31.070039-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-27T13:04:39.098414-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-27T13:04:39.098414-08:00","close_reason":"All children complete. Implemented: pkg/action/ (action logging), pkg/patterns/ (pattern analyzer), orch patterns command. Tests passing, integrated with existing patterns infrastructure."}
{"id":"orch-go-4oh7.1","title":"Action logging subsystem for tool outcomes","description":"Create ~/.orch/action-log.jsonl to track tool invocations with outcomes (success/empty/error). Define ActionEvent struct with tool name, target, outcome, timestamp, workspace context. Extend PostToolUse hook to log outcomes.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-12-27T12:24:46.746433-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-27T12:41:29.070611-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-27T12:41:29.070611-08:00","close_reason":"Implemented action logging subsystem in pkg/action/ with ActionEvent struct, Logger, Tracker, and pattern detection. Integrated with orch patterns command. All tests passing. Committed as 35d516f6.","labels":["skill:feature-impl","triage:ready"]}
{"id":"orch-go-4oh7.2","title":"Pattern analyzer for repeated behavioral failures","description":"Extend learning.go or create new analyzer to detect 'repeated action with same outcome' patterns. Example: 'Read SYNTHESIS.md returned empty 3 times in workspaces with .tier=light'","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-12-27T12:24:46.82744-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-27T12:40:25.173386-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-27T12:40:25.173386-08:00","close_reason":"Created pkg/patterns/ package with ActionEvent struct, ActionLog, and pattern detection (repeated empty reads, errors). Includes workspace context awareness for tier detection. 24 tests passing. Leave it Better: recorded constraint via kn (7-day vs 30-day retention).","labels":["skill:feature-impl","triage:ready"]}
{"id":"orch-go-4oh7.3","title":"orch patterns command to surface behavioral patterns","description":"Create 'orch patterns' command that shows detected behavioral patterns to orchestrator. Surface patterns like 'you tried X 3+ times with empty result'. Consider SessionStart hook injection as alternative surfacing mechanism.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-12-27T12:24:46.909386-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-27T12:37:21.522509-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-27T12:37:21.522509-08:00","close_reason":"Added orch patterns command that surfaces behavioral patterns (retry patterns, persistent failures, empty context queries, recurring gaps) from events.jsonl and gap-tracker.json. Includes JSON output, verbose mode, and tests.","labels":["skill:feature-impl","triage:ready"]}
