{"id":"orch-go-4pv4w","title":"Add infrastructure health to orch status (dashboard, opencode, daemon)","description":"orch status should surface infrastructure health: dashboard server running/not, opencode server, daemon status. Follows Surfacing Over Browsing principle. Currently silent failure when dashboard down - orchestrator has to manually debug. Add section like:\n\n📊 System Health\n   Dashboard: ❌ not running (orch serve)\n   OpenCode:  ✅ running on :4096\n   Daemon:    ✅ running (last poll 2m ago)\n\nImplementation: check ports 3348 (dashboard), 4096 (opencode), read daemon-status.json","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-01-07T09:40:53.920647-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-07T09:52:06.638737-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-07T09:52:06.638737-08:00","close_reason":"Manually verified: orch status now shows System Health section with Dashboard/OpenCode/Daemon status"}
{"id":"orch-go-4r1","title":"Investigate: stale dev OpenCode server caused Insufficient Balance errors","description":"orch usage showed 99% remaining but spawns failed with 'Insufficient Balance'. Root cause: dev server (0.0.0-dev-202512122356) running since Dec 12 had stale credentials. Fix: restart server with newer version (1.0.174). Document for future debugging.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-12-20T08:18:47.727714-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-20T08:18:57.849938-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-20T08:18:57.849938-08:00"}
{"id":"orch-go-4rboe","title":"skillc should include dependencies in deployed SKILL.md frontmatter","description":"## Problem\n\nWhen skillc deploys skills, it doesn't include the `dependencies` field from skill.yaml in the generated SKILL.md frontmatter.\n\n## Current Behavior\n\nskill.yaml has dependencies, but deployed SKILL.md doesn't include them.\n\n## Expected Behavior\n\nDeployed SKILL.md should include dependencies from skill.yaml.\n\n## Impact\n\norch-go's LoadSkillWithDependencies() reads dependencies from SKILL.md frontmatter. Without the dependencies field, dependencies aren't loaded at spawn time.\n\n## Workaround\n\nManually edit deployed SKILL.md files to add dependencies field after each skillc deploy.","status":"closed","priority":3,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-01-14T17:02:13.088818-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-21T22:03:59.317666231Z","closed_at":"2026-01-21T22:03:59.317666231Z","close_reason":"Duplicate: Investigation confirmed no bug - user workflow issue (deploying from wrong directory)","labels":["triage:ready"]}
{"id":"orch-go-4rfy","title":"Synthesize api investigations (10)","description":"## Synthesis Needed\n\nTopic **api** has accumulated 10 investigations that may benefit from consolidation.\n\n### Investigations to synthesize:\n\n- 2025-12-20-inv-add-api-agentlog-endpoint-serve.md\n- 2025-12-20-inv-poc-port-python-standalone-api.md\n- 2025-12-24-inv-add-api-usage-endpoint-serve.md\n- 2025-12-26-inv-add-api-errors-endpoint-error.md\n- 2025-12-26-inv-api-endpoint-api-agents-hangs.md\n- 2025-12-26-inv-evaluate-building-api-proxy-layer.md\n- 2025-12-27-inv-api-agents-endpoint-takes-19s.md\n- 2025-12-30-inv-pending-reviews-api-count-doesn.md\n- 2025-12-30-inv-pre-process-documents-locally-vs-api.md\n- 2025-12-26-add-api-reflect-endpoint-expose.md\n\n### Chronicle Timeline\n\n```\n2025-12-19 [INV] CLI Orch Status Command\n2025-12-19 [INV] SSE Event Monitoring Client\n2025-12-19 [INV] Desktop Notifications on Completion\n2025-12-19 [INV] Fix comment ID parsing - Comment.ID type mismatch\n2025-12-19 [INV] OpenCode POC - Spawn Session Via Go\n... (run kb chronicle for full timeline)\n```\n\n### Suggested Action\n\n1. Run `kb chronicle \"api\"` to understand evolution\n2. Identify patterns and contradictions across investigations\n3. Create a synthesized decision or consolidated investigation\n","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-01T15:00:18.327811-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-03T14:24:50.347196-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-03T14:24:50.347196-08:00","close_reason":"Stale synthesis task - closing during backlog cleanup","labels":["triage:review"]}
{"id":"orch-go-4tlwm","title":"Synthesize session investigations (10)","description":"## Synthesis Needed\n\nTopic **session** has accumulated 10 investigations that may benefit from consolidation.\n\n### Investigations to synthesize:\n\n- 2025-12-21-inv-fix-session-id-capture-timing.md\n- 2025-12-22-inv-debug-session-id-write.md\n- 2025-12-26-inv-session-end-workflow-orchestrators.md\n- 2026-01-02-inv-orch-session-status-reconcile-spawn.md\n- 2026-01-05-inv-feat-035-session-registry-orchestrator.md\n- 2026-01-06-inv-session-registry-doesnt-update-orchestrator.md\n- 2026-01-07-inv-feature-orch-abandon-export-session.md\n- 2026-01-08-inv-bug-session-checkpoint-alert-miscalibrated.md\n- 2025-12-21-inv-implement-session-handoff-md-template.md\n- 2025-12-26-inv-add-session-context-token-usage.md\n\n### Chronicle Timeline\n\n```\n2025-12-19 [INV] CLI orch complete Command Implementation\n2025-12-19 [INV] CLI orch spawn Command Implementation\n2025-12-19 [INV] CLI Orch Status Command\n2025-12-19 [INV] CLI Project Scaffolding and Build Setup\n2025-12-19 [INV] OpenCode Client Package Session Management\n... (run kb chronicle for full timeline)\n```\n\n### Suggested Action\n\n1. Run `kb chronicle \"session\"` to understand evolution\n2. Identify patterns and contradictions across investigations\n3. Create a synthesized decision or consolidated investigation\n","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-08T14:24:09.960612-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-08T14:57:22.120971-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-08T14:57:22.120971-08:00","close_reason":"Duplicate synthesis issue","labels":["triage:review"]}
{"id":"orch-go-4tven","title":"Epic: Model \u0026 System Efficiency","description":"## Understanding\n\nProblem: We make model decisions based on vibes and external benchmarks, not evidence from our own system. We don't know our actual failure distribution, success rate by model/skill, or scaling limits. Previous approach: reactive model switching when costs/limits hit. Constraints: need telemetry before we can measure, need definitions before we can track. Risks: optimizing model choice when real problem is skill/context quality. Done: evidence-based model selection, measurable system efficiency.\n\n---\n\nParent epic for understanding model selection, system efficiency, and scaling constraints. Core question: Are we optimizing the right things?","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"epic","created_at":"2026-01-09T12:37:09.120394-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-17T15:08:53.769354-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-17T15:08:53.769354-08:00","close_reason":"Epic Complete: Evidence-based model selection delivered."}
{"id":"orch-go-4tven.2","title":"Investigate actual failure distribution across spawns","description":"What causes spawn failures? Hypotheses: context too long, skill instructions ambiguous, tool schema unclear, verification gates missing. Goal: determine if model choice is the real variable or downstream of other problems. May require manual review of failed spawns to categorize.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-09T12:37:18.16059-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-09T14:05:12.940849-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-09T14:05:12.940849-08:00","close_reason":"Investigated failure distribution: model restrictions top cause, skill errors second, 4.8M daemon spawn failures. Investigation file: .kb/investigations/2026-01-09-inv-investigate-actual-failure-distribution-across.md"}
{"id":"orch-go-4tven.3","title":"Define 'success' for spawn telemetry","description":"What does success actually mean? Options: agent completes + commits, agent completes + code works, agent completes + human verified. The Verification Bottleneck principle says we can't know success without human observation. Need to decide: track claimed success or verified success? This definition shapes the telemetry schema.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-09T12:37:27.21428-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-09T13:40:01.316016-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-09T13:40:01.316016-08:00","close_reason":"Defined success as 'verification_passed \u0026\u0026 !forced'. Telemetry schema recommendations documented in investigation file."}
{"id":"orch-go-4tven.4","title":"Analyze spawn-to-value ratio","description":"What's the ratio of spawns to actual lasting value? If we spawn 50 agents/week but only 10 produce lasting value, that's a system smell. Could indicate: wrong granularity, premature spawning, model mismatch. Requires telemetry (orch-go-x67lc) plus qualitative assessment.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-09T12:37:27.259851-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-17T12:28:41.658681-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-17T12:28:41.658681-08:00","close_reason":"Completed spawn-to-value ratio investigation synthesis: D.E.K.N. summary shows 86.7% completion rate (contradicts 'spawn 50, get 10' hypothesis), but January abandonment spiked 4.8x (4.4% → 21.0%) requiring immediate investigation. Deliverables: investigation file with full synthesis, SYNTHESIS.md, kb decision kb-de30d9, git commit 6e0b28a0. Recommendation: spawn investigation for January abandonment root cause.","labels":["triage:ready"]}
{"id":"orch-go-4tven.5","title":"Measure context preparation vs execution cost","description":"What ratio of tokens go to SPAWN_CONTEXT.md, skill embedding, kb context vs actual work? If 60% is setup, that's an optimization lever. Could inform: context compression, selective inclusion, caching strategies.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-09T12:37:27.304438-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-17T12:09:31.312916-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-17T12:09:31.312916-08:00","close_reason":"Creating SYNTHESIS.md with findings and recommendations","labels":["triage:ready"]}
{"id":"orch-go-4tven.6","title":"Identify orchestrator value-add vs routing overhead","description":"When does orchestrator judgment actually matter vs when is it just routing? If daemon could handle 80% of spawns correctly, orchestrator should focus on the 20%. Informs: daemon autonomy expansion, orchestrator focus areas.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-09T12:37:27.344268-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-17T14:30:52.031627-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-17T14:30:52.031627-08:00","close_reason":"Investigation complete: orchestrator value-add is synthesis/triage judgment (20%); routing is daemon-automated (80%); overhead is workflow debt. SYNTHESIS.md created with findings and 4 follow-up issue recommendations.","labels":["triage:ready"]}
{"id":"orch-go-4tven.7","title":"Stress test: what breaks at 10x spawn volume","description":"Current: ~5-15 agents/day. What breaks at 50? 150? Candidates: registry scaling, beads issue volume, human verification bottleneck, context staleness, OpenCode server limits. Goal: know limits before hitting them.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-09T12:37:27.383889-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-17T12:35:20.891159-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-17T12:35:20.891159-08:00","close_reason":"Phase: Complete - Investigation complete. Found human verification is the binding constraint before technical limits. Ranked bottlenecks: (1) human review (2) registry locking (3) KB context growth (4) OpenCode stability (5) beads queries. Recommends batch review workflow with automated gates to achieve 5-10x review capacity. Deliverables: investigation file and SYNTHESIS.md committed.","labels":["triage:ready"]}
{"id":"orch-go-4tven.8","title":"Configure OpenAI and DeepSeek API credentials in OpenCode","description":"The model aliases for GPT-5 and DeepSeek were added to orch (pkg/model/model.go) but OpenCode needs provider credentials configured to actually use them. Setup required: OpenAI API key, DeepSeek API key. Verify with test spawns using --model gpt-5 and --model deepseek-r1.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-09T12:43:37.907227-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-09T12:51:53.769059-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-09T12:51:53.769059-08:00","close_reason":"Configured OpenAI and DeepSeek API keys in launchd plist and opencode.jsonc. Fixed model IDs to match models.dev (deepseek-chat, deepseek-reasoner, gpt-5, gpt-5-mini). Verified working with test spawns."}
{"id":"orch-go-4ues","title":"Add orch account add command for OAuth flow","description":"Currently accounts must be manually added to ~/.orch/accounts.yaml. Need 'orch account add \u003cname\u003e' command that: (1) Opens browser for Claude OAuth, (2) Captures refresh token, (3) Saves to accounts.yaml. This would fix the workflow when refresh tokens expire - currently no way to re-auth without manual token extraction.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2025-12-22T14:14:05.273958-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-22T14:38:52.649997-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-22T14:38:52.649997-08:00","close_reason":"Implemented orch account add command with OAuth authorization code flow using PKCE. Added pkg/account/oauth.go, pkg/account/oauth_test.go, and account add command in main.go. All 19 account tests pass."}
{"id":"orch-go-4ufh","title":"orch wait fails with 'failed to get issue' when using session ID","description":"orch wait ses_xxx errors with 'failed to get issue: exit status 1'. The command should work with session IDs directly, not require beads issue resolution. This forces manual curl polling instead of proper wait semantics.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2025-12-23T10:02:18.442769-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-25T22:14:46.164707-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-25T22:14:46.164707-08:00","close_reason":"Batch close from orch review"}
{"id":"orch-go-4v7qb","title":"Validate session discovery cross-window fix works across all scenarios","description":"Test scenarios: 1) Cross-window resume (most recent), 2) Same-window continuity (window history), 3) Concurrent session isolation (each window keeps history), 4) Fresh window resume (finds most recent), 5) Active directory mid-session, 6) Legacy fallback. Report: which scenarios pass/fail, discovery behavior for each, any edge cases found.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-13T19:43:56.750041-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-13T21:19:15.335435-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-13T21:19:15.335435-08:00","close_reason":"All 6 scenarios pass (100% success rate): cross-window resume, same-window continuity, concurrent isolation, fresh window error, active directory, legacy fallback. Session discovery fix (commit 85a6a283) is production-ready. Investigation: .kb/investigations/2026-01-13-inv-systematically-validate-session-discovery-cross.md"}
