{"id":"orch-go-4xmrw","title":"Bug: Dashboard config panel DropdownMenu not rendering","description":"Backend API for config editing works (tested via curl). Frontend DropdownMenu has rendering issue.\n\nRoot cause candidates from investigation:\n- bits-ui/Svelte 5 compatibility issue with portals\n- SSE connection (HTTP/1.1 limit) interfering with dropdown rendering\n- Same issue seen with Settings dropdown\n\nSee: .orch/workspace/og-feat-dashboard-config-editing-08jan-13ee/SYNTHESIS.md","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-01-08T11:31:06.774933-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-09T14:41:37.982155-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-09T14:41:37.982155-08:00","close_reason":"Applied dropdown z-index fix + Portal target. Manual browser verification required at localhost:5188 (test daemon indicator + settings dropdowns). Commit: c5959277. Investigation: .kb/investigations/2026-01-09-inv-bug-dashboard-config-panel-dropdownmenu.md. Note: SYNTHESIS.md created in wrong workspace (og-feat-dashboard-config-editing-08jan-13ee instead of og-arch-bug-dashboard-config-08jan-1f2d) - workspace artifact bug.","labels":["triage:ready"]}
