{"id":"orch-go-4zc2s","title":"[orch-go] investigation: Audit OpenCode session start injection: What pl...","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-16T13:45:23.617581-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-16T13:52:22.773313-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-16T13:52:22.773313-08:00","close_reason":"Audited OpenCode session start injection: ~4KB direct injection vs Claude Code's ~25KB. Key difference is orchestrator skill loaded via instructions (file ref) vs injection. Found 8 plugins across global and project locations, documented hook-to-plugin mapping and worker detection mechanisms."}
{"id":"orch-go-4ztg","title":"Epic: Migrate skills to skillc-managed structure","description":"## Goal\n\nMigrate ~/.claude/skills/ from manual SKILL.md files to skillc-managed .skillc/ sources, enabling modular skill development with dependency resolution and automated compilation.\n\n## Context\n\n- skillc exists at ~/Documents/personal/skillc with production-ready CLAUDE.md compilation\n- orch-knowledge repo no longer exists (confirmed)\n- Current skills have mixed structures: src/ (modular, 2 skills) vs manual SKILL.md (rest)\n- skillc already supports custom output filenames (can output SKILL.md)\n\n## Scope\n\n**In scope:**\n- Enhance skillc manifest for SKILL.md-specific patterns (frontmatter handling)\n- Pilot migration of one skill to validate the pattern\n- Convert existing modular skills (feature-impl, codebase-audit) to .skillc/\n- Documentation of the migration pattern\n- Verification that orch spawn works with compiled SKILL.md\n\n**Out of scope:**\n- Converting all monolithic skills (optional, low-value)\n- Changes to orch-go pkg/skills/loader.go (read-only, no changes needed)\n- Recursive skill dependencies (future enhancement)\n\n## Success Criteria\n\n- [ ] skillc can compile .skillc/ → SKILL.md with valid YAML frontmatter\n- [ ] orch spawn works with skillc-compiled SKILL.md files\n- [ ] At least 3 skills migrated (investigation, feature-impl, codebase-audit)\n- [ ] Migration pattern documented for future skill authors\n\n## Investigation Reference\n\nSee: orch-go/.kb/investigations/2025-12-22-inv-epic-replace-orch-knowledge-skillc.md","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"epic","created_at":"2025-12-22T07:01:44.488699-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-22T11:13:50.849989-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-22T11:13:50.849989-08:00","close_reason":"Epic complete. All success criteria met:\n- skillc compiles .skillc/ → SKILL.md with valid frontmatter (type: skill support added)\n- orch spawn works with skillc-compiled SKILL.md files (verified)\n- 3 skills migrated: investigation, feature-impl, codebase-audit\n- Migration pattern documented at ~/orch-knowledge/docs/skillc-skill-migration.md\n\nSources now in orch-knowledge, deployed to ~/.claude/skills/. Old src/ structures removed."}
{"id":"orch-go-4ztg.1","title":"Enhance skillc for SKILL.md frontmatter handling","description":"## Context\n\nPart of orch-go-4ztg: Epic: Migrate skills to skillc-managed structure\n\n## Problem\n\nskillc currently adds header comments at the start of compiled output:\n```markdown\n\u003c!-- AUTO-GENERATED by skillc --\u003e\n\u003c!-- Source: .skillc --\u003e\n...\n```\n\nSKILL.md files require YAML frontmatter at line 1:\n```yaml\n---\nname: investigation\nskill-type: procedure\n...\n---\n```\n\nIf skillc header appears first, YAML parsing fails.\n\n## Task\n\nModify skillc to handle SKILL.md compilation:\n1. Add `type: skill` option in skill.yaml manifest\n2. When type=skill: emit frontmatter first, header comments after\n3. Support explicit frontmatter source file (e.g., frontmatter.yaml → merged into output)\n\n## Alternative Approaches\n\n- Option A: type field switches header placement\n- Option B: Explicit frontmatter.yaml file in sources\n- Option C: Detect output filename ends with SKILL.md, auto-adjust\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] skill.yaml can specify type: skill\n- [ ] Compiled SKILL.md has frontmatter at line 1\n- [ ] orch-go ParseSkillMetadata() parses compiled output correctly\n- [ ] Existing CLAUDE.md compilation unchanged (backward compatible)\n\n## Technical Notes\n\n- See skillc/pkg/compiler/compiler.go:91 for header generation\n- See orch-go/pkg/skills/loader.go:103-125 for ParseSkillMetadata","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-12-22T07:01:59.94467-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-25T22:14:51.157824-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-25T22:14:51.157824-08:00","close_reason":"Batch close from orch review","labels":["target:skillc","triage:ready"]}
{"id":"orch-go-4ztg.2","title":"Pilot migration: Convert investigation skill to .skillc/","description":"## Context\n\nPart of orch-go-4ztg: Epic: Migrate skills to skillc-managed structure\n\n## Task\n\nConvert the investigation skill from manual SKILL.md to skillc-managed .skillc/ structure.\n\n## Current Structure\n\n```\n~/.claude/skills/worker/investigation/\n├── SKILL.md          # Manual, single file\n└── templates/        # Subdirectory with template files\n```\n\n## Target Structure\n\n```\n~/.claude/skills/worker/investigation/\n├── .skillc/\n│   ├── skill.yaml    # Manifest with type: skill, output: SKILL.md\n│   ├── frontmatter.yaml\n│   ├── intro.md\n│   ├── workflow.md\n│   └── template-refs.md  # References to templates/ subdirectory\n├── SKILL.md          # Compiled output (do not edit)\n└── templates/        # Unchanged\n```\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] .skillc/ structure created with modular sources\n- [ ] skillc build produces valid SKILL.md\n- [ ] orch spawn investigation \"test\" works correctly\n- [ ] templates/ subdirectory still accessible\n- [ ] Old SKILL.md backed up before replacement\n\n## Why This Skill First\n\n- Medium complexity (has templates/ subdirectory)\n- Well-understood skill with clear structure\n- Good test case for the pattern","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-12-22T07:02:07.496606-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-22T11:09:05.487725-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-22T11:09:05.487725-08:00","close_reason":"Investigation skill migrated to .skillc/ in orch-knowledge. Sources at ~/orch-knowledge/skills/src/worker/investigation/.skillc/, deployed to ~/.claude/skills/. Verified working."}
{"id":"orch-go-4ztg.3","title":"Convert feature-impl skill from src/ to .skillc/","description":"## Context\n\nPart of orch-go-4ztg: Epic: Migrate skills to skillc-managed structure\n\n## Task\n\nConvert feature-impl from legacy src/ structure to skillc .skillc/ structure.\n\n## Current Structure\n\n```\n~/.claude/skills/worker/feature-impl/\n├── SKILL.md              # Compiled output\n├── src/\n│   ├── SKILL.md.template # Template with placeholders?\n│   └── phases/           # Phase-specific content\n└── reference/            # Reference docs\n```\n\n## Target Structure\n\n```\n~/.claude/skills/worker/feature-impl/\n├── .skillc/\n│   ├── skill.yaml\n│   ├── frontmatter.yaml\n│   └── phases/           # Migrated from src/phases/\n├── SKILL.md              # Compiled by skillc\n└── reference/            # Unchanged\n```\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] src/ content migrated to .skillc/\n- [ ] skillc build produces valid SKILL.md\n- [ ] orch spawn feature-impl \"test\" works correctly\n- [ ] src/ directory removed after successful migration\n- [ ] reference/ subdirectory preserved\n\n## Dependencies\n\nDepends on: skillc enhancement task (orch-go-4ztg child 1)","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-12-22T07:02:13.950851-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-22T10:21:46.370781-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-22T10:21:46.370781-08:00"}
{"id":"orch-go-4ztg.4","title":"Convert codebase-audit skill from src/ to .skillc/","description":"## Context\n\nPart of orch-go-4ztg: Epic: Migrate skills to skillc-managed structure\n\n## Task\n\nConvert codebase-audit from legacy src/ structure to skillc .skillc/ structure.\n\n## Current Structure\n\n```\n~/.claude/skills/worker/codebase-audit/\n├── SKILL.md\n└── src/\n    └── [source files]\n```\n\n## Target Structure\n\n```\n~/.claude/skills/worker/codebase-audit/\n├── .skillc/\n│   ├── skill.yaml\n│   └── [migrated sources]\n└── SKILL.md              # Compiled by skillc\n```\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] src/ content migrated to .skillc/\n- [ ] skillc build produces valid SKILL.md\n- [ ] orch spawn codebase-audit \"test\" works correctly\n- [ ] src/ directory removed after successful migration\n\n## Dependencies\n\nDepends on: skillc enhancement task (orch-go-4ztg child 1)","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-12-22T07:02:18.417004-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-22T11:13:43.790781-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-22T11:13:43.790781-08:00","close_reason":"Migrated codebase-audit to .skillc/ structure in orch-knowledge. Sources at ~/orch-knowledge/skills/src/worker/codebase-audit/.skillc/, deployed to ~/.claude/skills/. Old src/ removed. Commit c332d4f."}
{"id":"orch-go-4ztg.5","title":"Document skillc skill migration pattern","description":"## Context\n\nPart of orch-go-4ztg: Epic: Migrate skills to skillc-managed structure\n\n## Task\n\nDocument the pattern for migrating skills to skillc-managed structure so future skill authors can follow it.\n\n## Deliverables\n\nCreate documentation (location TBD - skillc/docs/ or ~/.claude/skills/docs/):\n\n1. **Migration Guide**\n   - When to use skillc for skills (modular \u003e 200 lines, phases, reusable sections)\n   - When to keep manual SKILL.md (simple, monolithic skills)\n   - Step-by-step migration process\n\n2. **skill.yaml Reference for Skills**\n   - type: skill option\n   - frontmatter handling\n   - output: SKILL.md\n\n3. **Best Practices**\n   - File organization (frontmatter.yaml, intro.md, phases/, etc.)\n   - When to split vs keep together\n   - Template directory handling\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] Migration guide created with step-by-step instructions\n- [ ] skill.yaml reference for skill-type manifests\n- [ ] At least 2 examples (investigation, feature-impl)\n- [ ] Added to skillc README or docs/\n\n## Dependencies\n\nDepends on: Pilot migration complete (to document proven pattern)","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-12-22T07:02:26.004461-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-22T11:11:12.470041-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-22T11:11:12.470041-08:00","close_reason":"Documentation created at ~/orch-knowledge/docs/skillc-skill-migration.md. Covers directory structure, manifest format, frontmatter, template markers, migration steps, verification checklist, and troubleshooting."}
{"id":"orch-go-4zvvn","title":"Improve cross-project daemon handling of uninitialized projects","description":"## Problem\n\nCross-project daemon logs generic warnings for projects without beads:\n```\nwarning: failed to get ready issues for project /Users/dylanconlin/orch-knowledge: exit status 1\n```\n\n## Improvement\n\nEither:\n1. Check for .beads/ directory before attempting bd ready\n2. Provide clearer warning: 'Project X has no beads initialized, skipping'\n\n## Location\n\n- `pkg/daemon/issue_adapter.go:listReadyIssuesForProjectCLI()`\n- Could check `filepath.Exists(projectPath + '/.beads')` before calling bd","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-21T21:48:55.166122195Z","updated_at":"2026-01-22T20:17:33.185377-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-22T20:17:33.185377-08:00","close_reason":"Added .beads/ directory check in ListReadyIssuesForProject - projects without beads silently return empty list"}
