{"id":"orch-go-50hv","title":"orch status still slow: getCompletionsForReview runs VerifyCompletionFull on 303 workspaces","description":"## Problem\n\n`orch status` is still 1m26s despite workspace cache fix (c4d21d8d). JSON mode is fast (1s) but text output is slow.\n\n## Root Cause\n\n`getCompletionsForReview()` in cmd/orch/review.go:138 runs `verify.VerifyCompletionFull()` for EVERY workspace with SYNTHESIS.md:\n- 303 workspaces with SYNTHESIS.md\n- Each VerifyCompletionFull does beads lookups, file reads, etc.\n- Called from `GetArchitectRecommendationsSurface()` which is called in text output mode\n\n## Evidence\n\n```\ntime orch status --json  # 1.0s (fast)\ntime orch status         # 1m26s (slow)\nfind .orch/workspace -name 'SYNTHESIS.md' | wc -l  # 303\n```\n\n## Fix Options\n\n1. **Cache completions** - Don't re-verify on every status call\n2. **Lazy load** - Only verify when explicitly requested \n3. **Skip old workspaces** - Only verify recent (e.g., \u003c24h old)\n4. **Move to API** - Have orch serve cache this data","status":"closed","priority":0,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2025-12-29T07:59:05.66381-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-29T09:18:45.970884-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-29T09:18:45.970884-08:00","close_reason":"Zombie issue reconciled - no active agent found"}
