{"id":"orch-go-528","title":"Explore tradeoffs for orch-go opencode integration.","description":"Explore tradeoffs for orch-go opencode integration. Current problem: orch-go uses 'opencode run --attach {server} --title {name} {prompt}' which doesn't render TUI correctly in tmux. Python orch-cli uses standalone mode: 'opencode {project_dir}' then waits for TUI ready, then types prompt via send-keys. Options to explore: 1) Match Python's standalone approach, 2) Fix attach mode to work with TUI, 3) Hybrid approach, 4) Other alternatives. Consider: session management, server coordination, TUI rendering, complexity, reliability, feature parity with Python orch-cli.","notes":"workspace: .orch/workspace/og-explore-tradeoffs-orch-20dec","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-12-20T09:33:24.720422-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-20T10:14:36.639099-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-20T10:14:36.639099-08:00"}
{"id":"orch-go-528w","title":"Regression: agent cards jostling for first position on SSE updates","description":"Agent cards in dashboard are fighting for first position again when SSE updates come in. This was previously fixed with stable sort by spawned_at. Likely regression from recent SSE/CPU fix commits (ed772bac or 04defd83). Check web/src/lib/stores/ and sorting logic - may have reverted to updated_at sort or lost the stable sort key.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-12-25T22:29:38.97179-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-25T22:51:02.187005-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-25T22:51:02.187005-08:00","close_reason":"No regression found. Stable sort fix from dfd61e05 is intact. Commits ed772bac/04defd83 did not touch sorting logic. Issue was false positive.","labels":["P1","skill:systematic-debugging","triage:ready"]}
