{"id":"orch-go-531vo","title":"Research GLM 4.7 from z.ai for orchestration use","description":"## Context\n\nReddit discussion about GLM 4.7 from z.ai surfaced interesting data points for potential orchestration use.\n\n**Source:** `.orch/glm-4-7-reddit.txt`\n\n## Key Claims from Discussion\n\n**Positive signals:**\n- \"GLM best at iterative implementation (fewer context losses)\" vs Opus\n- \"200M tokens for $3\" - extremely high value if true\n- GLM 4.7 Flash just dropped (faster variant)\n- Works well with Claude Code direct connection\n- 5-hour token window, no weekly cap (on some plans)\n\n**Concerns:**\n- Concurrency limits (1-3 connections on 4.7, 12+ on 4.6)\n- Slowness during US peak hours\n- OpenCode has more issues than Claude Code (gateway vs direct?)\n- \"Air\" fallback model hallucinates badly\n- z.ai may be unsustainably priced (~$7 loss per $1 revenue claimed)\n\n## Research Questions\n\n1. **Model capabilities:** How does GLM 4.7 compare to Opus/Sonnet for agentic coding tasks?\n2. **Pricing/limits:** What are actual plan tiers, pricing, token limits, concurrency?\n3. **Integration:** How would this work with orch-go? (Claude Code compatible = could use --mode claude?)\n4. **Reliability:** Is z.ai stable enough for production orchestration?\n5. **GLM 4.7 Flash:** Is this a viable \"haiku-tier\" alternative?\n\n## Deliverables\n\n- Investigation file with findings\n- Recommendation: use/don't use/watch\n- If promising: comparison matrix vs current model stack (Opus, Gemini Flash)\n\n## Reference\n\n- z.ai website: https://z.ai\n- Existing model decisions: `.kb/decisions/2026-01-09-abandon-claude-max-oauth-use-gemini-primary.md`","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-22T04:52:30.27854255Z","updated_at":"2026-01-21T20:59:43.617248-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-21T20:59:43.617248-08:00","close_reason":"Phase: Complete - Investigation complete. GLM 4.7 is a strong model at exceptional value (-60/mo), but NOT recommended for orch-go currently due to: (1) OpenCode integration issues (tool calls in thinking tags, timeouts), (2) strict concurrency limits (1-5 vs 12+ on 4.6) conflicting with multi-agent spawning. Recommendation: WATCH status, revisit in 30-60 days. Deliverable: .kb/investigations/2026-01-22-inv-research-glm-ai-orchestration-context.md","labels":["triage:ready"]}
