{"id":"orch-go-549r","title":"Dashboard: Duplicate key error in recent section","description":"Bug: Same pattern as orch-go-gne4 (archive). Recent section throws 'each_key_duplicate' - workspace 'og-debug-spawn-context-includes-26dec [orch-go-i914]' appears at indexes 0 and 18. Fix from gne4 used agent.id but duplicates still exist in data. Need: 1) Use composite key (id + index) or just index, 2) Investigate why duplicate entries exist in /api/agents data.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2025-12-26T16:28:03.76777-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-26T16:46:00.623168-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-26T16:46:00.623168-08:00","close_reason":"Fixed duplicate key error in dashboard. Root cause: OpenCode had multiple sessions with same title. Two fixes: 1) Backend deduplication by title keeping most recent session 2) Frontend composite keys (id+session_id) as defense-in-depth. Verified via curl - no duplicates in /api/agents response.","labels":["skill:feature-impl","triage:ready"]}
