{"id":"orch-go-559o","title":"Update tmux spawn to use attach mode for dual TUI+API access","description":"## Problem\n\nCurrently `orch spawn --tmux` uses standalone mode (`opencode /path --model X`) which creates an ephemeral server on a random port. Sessions created in standalone mode are NOT visible to the main OpenCode server at `:4096`, so:\n\n- No `session_id` captured in registry\n- Cannot interact via HTTP API (`orch send`, `orch tail` fall back to tmux capture)\n- No structured message access\n- Monitoring/status checks require tmux scraping\n\nThis means tmux spawns are \"human-friendly\" (TUI visible) but NOT \"AI-friendly\" (no API access).\n\n## Solution\n\nSwitch from standalone mode to attach mode:\n\n```go\n// OLD (standalone - ephemeral server)\nopencode /path/to/project --model X\n\n// NEW (attach - shared server)  \nopencode attach http://127.0.0.1:4096 --dir /path/to/project --model X\n```\n\nWith attach mode + the OpenCode fix (already applied locally):\n1. TUI connects to shared server at `:4096`\n2. Sessions created with correct `directory` (via `x-opencode-directory` header)\n3. Sessions visible in API immediately\n4. Can capture `session_id` and store in registry\n5. Full API access: messages, status, send prompts\n\n## Implementation Details\n\n### 1. Update `pkg/tmux/tmux.go`\n\nChange `BuildStandaloneCommand()` to `BuildAttachCommand()`:\n\n```go\ntype AttachConfig struct {\n    ServerURL  string // http://127.0.0.1:4096\n    ProjectDir string\n    Model      string\n    SessionID  string // optional: continue existing session\n}\n\nfunc BuildAttachCommand(cfg *AttachConfig) string {\n    cmd := fmt.Sprintf(\"opencode attach %s --dir %s\", \n        cfg.ServerURL, \n        shlex.Quote(cfg.ProjectDir))\n    if cfg.Model != \"\" {\n        cmd += fmt.Sprintf(\" --model %s\", shlex.Quote(cfg.Model))\n    }\n    if cfg.SessionID != \"\" {\n        cmd += fmt.Sprintf(\" --session %s\", cfg.SessionID)\n    }\n    return cmd\n}\n```\n\n### 2. Update `cmd/orch/main.go` `runSpawnTmux()`\n\nAfter TUI is ready and prompt is sent:\n1. Query `/session` API with `x-opencode-directory` header\n2. Find most recent session for this project\n3. Store `session_id` in registry\n\n```go\n// After SendPromptAfterReady succeeds\nsessionID, err := findRecentSession(serverURL, cfg.ProjectDir)\nif err != nil {\n    // Log warning but don't fail - tmux fallback still works\n    log.Printf(\"Warning: could not capture session_id: %v\", err)\n}\n\n// Update registry with session_id\nagent.SessionID = sessionID\n```\n\n### 3. Update registry usage\n\nCommands that currently fall back to tmux when `session_id` is missing can now use API:\n- `orch tail` - use `/session/{id}/message` \n- `orch send` - use `/session/{id}/prompt`\n- `orch question` - parse from API messages\n\n## Dependencies\n\n**OpenCode fix required:** The SDK must pass `directory: process.cwd()` to API calls.\n\nFix already applied locally at:\n`opencode/packages/opencode/src/cli/cmd/tui/context/sdk.tsx`\n\n```typescript\nconst sdk = createOpencodeClient({\n  baseUrl: props.url,\n  signal: abort.signal,\n  directory: process.cwd(),  // THIS LINE ADDED\n})\n```\n\nThis fix needs to be:\n1. Committed to opencode repo\n2. Released as new version\n3. Or: use locally built opencode binary\n\n## Testing\n\n1. `orch spawn --tmux investigation \"test\"` creates session\n2. Session visible via: `curl http://127.0.0.1:4096/session -H \"x-opencode-directory: $PWD\"`\n3. `session_id` present in registry: `cat ~/.orch/agent-registry.json | jq '.agents[-1].session_id'`\n4. `orch tail \u003cid\u003e` uses API (not tmux fallback)\n5. `orch send \u003cid\u003e \"message\"` uses API\n\n## Evidence\n\nTested attach mode with fixed OpenCode locally:\n\n```bash\n# Session created with correct directory\ncurl -s http://127.0.0.1:4096/session \\\n  -H \"x-opencode-directory: /Users/dylanconlin/Documents/personal/orch-go\" \\\n  | jq 'sort_by(.time.created) | last'\n\n# Output:\n{\n  \"id\": \"ses_4bf7f116bffeaVAetTEdKTtsD4\",\n  \"title\": \"New session - 2025-12-21T10:42:30.164Z\",\n  \"dir\": \"/Users/dylanconlin/Documents/personal/orch-go\",\n  ...\n}\n\n# Can fetch messages via API\ncurl -s \"http://127.0.0.1:4096/session/ses_4bf7f116bffeaVAetTEdKTtsD4/message\" \\\n  -H \"x-opencode-directory: /Users/dylanconlin/Documents/personal/orch-go\"\n# Returns structured message history\n```\n\n## Related\n\n- Investigation: `.kb/investigations/2025-12-21-inv-tmux-spawn-killed.md`\n- Python orch-cli gave up on attach mode due to this bug: `src/orch/spawn.py:959-960`\n- OpenCode source: `packages/opencode/src/cli/cmd/tui/context/sdk.tsx`","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-12-21T02:45:58.867363-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-21T09:36:20.444997-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-21T09:36:20.444997-08:00"}
{"id":"orch-go-55brc","title":"Change bug routing from architect to systematic-debugging","description":"## Context\nInvestigation orch-go-fkn0p found that bug→architect routing causes investigation over-production. ~50% of investigations from docker backend work were unnecessary.\n\n## Change\nOne-line change in pkg/daemon/skill_inference.go line 29-32:\n- Change: `return \"architect\", nil`\n- To: `return \"systematic-debugging\", nil`\n- Update comment to reflect new default\n\n## Escape Hatch\nPreserves `skill:architect` label for complex/recurring bugs that need architectural understanding.\n\n## Reference\n- Decision: .kb/decisions/2026-01-23-investigation-overhead-firefighting-mode.md\n- Investigation: .kb/investigations/2026-01-23-inv-so-many-investigations-created-root.md","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-23T19:45:50.703222-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-23T19:50:10.078551-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-23T19:50:10.078551-08:00","close_reason":"Phase: Complete - Changed bug routing from architect to systematic-debugging in pkg/daemon/skill_inference.go. Tests: go test ./pkg/daemon/... -run TestInferSkill - 4 test functions, all PASS. Escape hatch preserved via skill:architect label.","labels":["triage:ready"]}
