73673-08:00","close_reason":"Duplicate synthesis issue","labels":["triage:review"]}
{"id":"orch-go-599i","title":"orch complete --force bypasses repro verification for bugs","description":"--force flag skips ALL verification including repro check for bugs. This defeats the Bug Reproducibility Gates epic (jjd4).\n\n## Root cause\n--force sets a boolean that skips the entire verification flow, not granular checks.\n\n## Solution\n--force should only skip the blocking check (test evidence), not subsequent gates (repro verification). Or rename to --skip-test-evidence and keep repro gate mandatory.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-01-04T08:37:41.59-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-04T08:49:55.581622-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-04T08:49:55.581622-08:00","close_reason":"Fixed --force to only skip phase/liveness verification, not repro verification. Repro gate now always runs for bugs. Updated help text and error messages. Tests passing."}
{"id":"orch-go-59m3","title":"Daemon capacity count goes stale after initial spawn cycle","description":"Daemon correctly counts on startup but goes stale after spawning. Requires launchctl restart to pick up new work. Prior fix (orch-go-s2j7) filtered sessions by 30-min update time, but issue persists. Suspect: Reconcile() not being called on each poll, or untracked agents counting toward capacity incorrectly.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-12-26T14:23:30.693761-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-26T14:38:10.124849-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-26T14:38:10.124849-08:00","close_reason":"Fixed daemon capacity count to exclude untracked agents. Added extractBeadsIDFromSessionTitle() and isUntrackedBeadsID() functions to filter out sessions with -untracked- in beads ID. All tests pass.","labels":["P1","skill:systematic-debugging","triage:ready"]}
