{"id":"orch-go-5b9","title":"Fix: tmux spawn should not use --format json","description":"## Problem\n\nWhen spawning in tmux mode, the agent runs with `--format json` which outputs raw JSON instead of OpenCode's interactive TUI.\n\n## Current Behavior\n```\nopencode run --attach ... --format json --title ... \"prompt\"\n# Outputs raw JSON lines to terminal\n```\n\n## Expected Behavior\n```\nopencode run --attach ... --title ... \"prompt\"\n# Shows OpenCode's normal TUI\n```\n\n## Root Cause\n`pkg/tmux/tmux.go:BuildSpawnCommand()` hardcodes `--format json`.\n\n## Fix\n- Remove `--format json` from tmux spawn command\n- Keep `--format json` only for inline mode (needed to parse session ID)\n\n## Files\n- pkg/tmux/tmux.go line ~10","notes":"workspace: .orch/workspace/og-feat-fix-tmux-spawn-not-19dec","status":"closed","priority":0,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2025-12-19T21:20:12.770066-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-19T21:22:38.592507-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-19T21:22:38.592507-08:00"}
{"id":"orch-go-5bpcc","title":"Epic: Systemic Completion Integrity \u0026 Signal Detection","description":"## Understanding\n\nProblem: Systemic resource waste (~/spawn) from duplicate spawns of completed-but-unclosed work. Status-only gating fails to capture the 'completed awaiting review' state. Goal: Implement Signal-Aware Gating (Phase 1) that checks beads comments/artifacts/commits before spawning, then enable automated Light-Tier closure (Phase 2). Done when duplicate loops are eliminated and verification backlog is dashboard-visible.\n\n","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"epic","created_at":"2026-01-18T14:19:42.411879-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-26T21:35:30.364571-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-26T21:35:30.364571-08:00","close_reason":"Phase: Complete"}
