{"id":"orch-go-5iyp","title":"[orch-go] architect: Design the orchestrator completion lifecycle. T...","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-12-25T10:45:17.233157-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-25T22:14:42.985488-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-25T22:14:42.985488-08:00","close_reason":"Batch close from orch review"}
{"id":"orch-go-5j2hx","title":"Implement questions as first-class beads entities","description":"## Understanding\n\nProblem: Strategic questions (pre-epic, gate-worthy) have no entity representation - cannot track 'question asked but not investigated' state, cannot gate work on unanswered questions. Currently conflating questions (what we need to know) with investigations (how we find out).\n\nPrevious: Questions embedded in investigation files, no independent lifecycle. Epic orch-go-erdw created from 'How do we X?' without validating premise - had to be paused.\n\nConstraints: Must be lightweight (no assignee/estimate/verification). Must support dependencies. Must integrate with bd ready filtering.\n\nRisks: Entity inflation if guidance unclear on when to create question vs just document. Beads schema extension complexity unknown.\n\nDone: bd create --type question works, bd dep add links questions to epics, bd ready excludes question-blocked items, dashboard shows Questions view.\n\n","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"epic","created_at":"2026-01-18T11:49:13.753495-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-18T12:50:44.585381-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-18T12:50:44.585381-08:00","close_reason":"Epic complete. All 4 tasks shipped: question entity type (2dc8f7dc), lifecycle (d14cf911), gates (744af9cf), dashboard (7ad410a4). Integration tested."}
{"id":"orch-go-5j2m7","title":"Implement tmux session visibility in dashboard (from architect design)","description":"Implement the tmux visibility design from architect session og-arch-dashboard-add-tmux-18jan-3cc7.\n\n## Design Reference\n- Investigation: .kb/investigations/2026-01-18-design-dashboard-add-tmux-session-visibility.md\n- SYNTHESIS: .orch/workspace-archive/og-arch-dashboard-add-tmux-18jan-3cc7/SYNTHESIS.md\n\n## Implementation Phases\n\n### Phase 1: Beads Phase for Status (~50 lines)\n- In serve_agents.go, for tmux-only agents, look up Phase from batch-fetched beads data\n- Set status based on Phase: Complete\n\n### Phase 2: Pane Activity Detection (~130 lines)\n- Add GetPaneActivityAge() to pkg/tmux\n- Use 3-minute threshold for dead detection\n\n### Phase 3: Runtime from .spawn_time (~30 lines)\n- Read spawn_time from workspace for tmux agents\n- Calculate runtime display\n\n## Constraints\n- Claude CLI doesn't expose token usage (accept null tokens for tmux agents)\n- Keep tmux as fallback data source (not first-class)\n- Match Priority Cascade model for status resolution","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-01-18T15:35:36.370219-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-18T15:48:11.705312-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-18T15:48:11.705312-08:00","close_reason":"Tests: go test ./cmd/orch/... - 1.975s PASS. Implemented tmux session visibility: spawn time, runtime, and activity detection for tmux agents using workspace file modification times."}
{"id":"orch-go-5kms","title":"kb reflect needs semantic clustering - group by topic not keyword","description":"**From investigation:** 2025-12-28-inv-knowledge-fragmentation-433-investigations-days.md\n\n**Problem:** kb reflect --type synthesis groups by word frequency ('add' = 41, 'orch' = 36) not conceptual topic. This makes synthesis suggestions unhelpful - 41 'add' investigations aren't related, they just share a word.\n\n**Recommendation:** Cluster by semantic topic (dashboard, headless, daemon) not keyword. Simple topic extraction from titles may suffice - don't over-engineer.\n\n**Success criteria:** kb reflect --type synthesis shows semantic topics (dashboard UX, spawn modes, daemon lifecycle) not keyword groups (add, implement, orch)","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2025-12-30T11:45:12.303792-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-30T15:40:00.545735-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-30T15:40:00.545735-08:00","close_reason":"kb reflect semantic clustering - added tool name filtering"}
{"id":"orch-go-5m2f8","title":"Rebuild and deploy skills after constitutional additions","description":"## Context\n\nAfter adding constitutional constraints to worker-base and feature-impl, skills need to be rebuilt and deployed.\n\n## Task\n\n1. Build skills: `cd ~/orch-knowledge \u0026\u0026 skillc build`\n2. Deploy skills: `skillc deploy`\n3. Verify deployment succeeded\n4. Spot check that new sections appear in deployed SKILL.md files\n\n## Dependencies\n\nDepends on:\n- orch-go-kn4g6 (Hard Limits)\n- orch-go-ukrik (Constitutional Objection Protocol)\n- orch-go-kg2cq (Harm Assessment)\n\n## Reference\n\n- `.kb/decisions/2026-01-22-skill-constitutional-constraints.md`","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-22T04:17:04.672644976Z","updated_at":"2026-01-22T21:11:17.38741-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-22T21:11:17.38741-08:00","close_reason":"Skills rebuilt and deployed with constitutional additions (Hard Limits + Objection Protocol in worker-base)"}
