{"id":"orch-go-5mm7q","title":"Add semantic pattern matching to gap normalizeQuery","description":"The normalizeQuery function at pkg/spawn/learning.go:365-371 only does lowercase + whitespace normalization. Semantically related queries like 'synthesize orchestrator investigations' and 'synthesize spawn investigations' are treated as separate patterns, preventing recurrence detection. Implement template-based pattern matching to group related queries. See .kb/investigations/2026-01-07-inv-audit-recurring-gap-patterns-semantic.md for detailed findings.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-01-07T21:11:21.114824-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-07T21:17:32.05869-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-07T21:17:32.05869-08:00","close_reason":"Implemented semantic pattern matching in normalizeQuery with 12 patterns using 1-3 word wildcards. Related queries like 'synthesize X investigations' now group as single pattern. All tests pass. Leave it Better: kn-2b13d0 (decision on template-based approach)."}
{"id":"orch-go-5mv6","title":"Glass: Add hover capability and investigate other important interaction modes","description":"Glass currently supports click, type, navigate, screenshot. Missing hover which is important for: tooltips, dropdown menus, hover states. Should investigate what other interaction modes are commonly needed (drag-drop, right-click, keyboard shortcuts, scroll-into-view, wait-for-element, etc.)","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2025-12-30T09:55:29.425851-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-03T14:24:28.176081-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-03T14:24:28.176081-08:00","close_reason":"Already completed: Added hover capability to glass (daemon, MCP, CLI) using CDP Input.dispatchMouseEvent. Investigation"}
{"id":"orch-go-5oczv","title":"Orchestrator spawns should default to --tmux, not headless","description":"Per skill guidance: 'Orchestrators are visible in tmux so you can observe their progress, send guidance, and intervene if needed.'\n\nCurrently orchestrators default to headless like workers. They should default to --tmux.\n\n**Expected:** orch spawn orchestrator defaults to tmux mode\n**Actual:** Defaults to headless, requires explicit --tmux flag","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-01-18T13:49:59.128716-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-22T20:16:48.027702-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-22T20:16:48.027702-08:00","close_reason":"Already implemented: useTmux includes cfg.IsOrchestrator check since commit 96999985d (Jan 4). Skills with skill-type: policy/orchestrator auto-default to tmux."}
