{"id":"orch-go-5ubkd","title":"Decidability Graph Visualization","description":"## Understanding\n\n**Problem:** The decidability graph model exists conceptually but Dylan lacks understanding because there's no way to visualize it. The model stays abstract without interactive exploration.\n\n**Why previous approaches insufficient:** Current dashboard has swarm map (linear, no relationships) and beads lists (no graph structure). Neither shows WHY work is blocked or what resolving a question would unlock.\n\n**Key constraints:**\n1. Graph quality = orchestration quality (shows what orchestrator externalizes)\n2. Need full graph export (bd dep tree requires root issue)\n3. Real-time agent state overlay requires SSE integration\n4. Scale ceiling at 50+ nodes needs filtering\n\n**Risks:**\n1. Sparse graph if orchestrator doesn't create question nodes / add deps\n2. Layout jitter if agent state changes frequently\n3. Overwhelming at large scale without good filtering\n\n**Done looks like:**\n1. Interactive graph view in dashboard\n2. Nodes styled by type (work/question) and state (active/blocked/done)\n3. Click node → see details, blocking chain, quick actions\n4. Agent activity overlaid (pulsing = active, checkmark = complete)\n5. Dylan can explore and understand work structure visually\n\n","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"epic","created_at":"2026-01-23T09:48:41.734296-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-24T10:58:58.071314-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-24T10:58:58.071314-08:00"}
