{"id":"orch-go-60vb1","title":"Epic: Audit CLI error UX across orch ecosystem","description":"**Goal:** Review and improve error messages across bd, kb, orch, and skillc CLIs to reduce cognitive load for both human and AI users.\n\n**Principle:** CLI errors should reduce cognitive load, not add to it. See decision: ~/.kb/decisions/2026-01-08-cli-errors-reduce-cognitive-load.md\n\n**Scope:**\n- bd (beads) - issue tracking CLI\n- kb (knowledge base) - documentation CLI  \n- orch - orchestration CLI\n- skillc - skill compiler CLI\n\n**Approach:**\n1. Audit each CLI for error paths that fail without guidance\n2. Categorize by fix type: sensible default vs show corrected command vs guide discovery\n3. Prioritize by frequency (which errors do agents hit most?)\n4. Implement improvements\n\n**Success criteria:**\n- Every error message either fixes itself, shows the fix, or guides discovery\n- An agent with no memory of prior commands can recover from any error\n\n**Known issues to fold in:**\n- ok-9ph0: skillc deploy --target friction\n- Cross-repo beads issue resolution\n- bd commands in wrong directory\n\n**Not in scope:**\n- New features - this is UX polish on existing commands","status":"open","priority":3,"issue_type":"epic","created_at":"2026-01-08T07:06:55.793637-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-29T10:36:42.745457-08:00"}
{"id":"orch-go-6186n","title":"kb context and kb search don't include .kb/models/ in search paths","description":"kb context help says it searches '.kb/: investigations, decisions, guides' but NOT models. This breaks the model discovery mechanism described in orchestrator skill and models/README. Impact: orchestrators ask questions models answer (but don't see them), workers reinvestigate already-synthesized topics.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-01-14T14:27:21.081726-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-14T14:40:13.452458-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-14T14:40:13.452458-08:00","close_reason":"Fixed: kb context now includes MODELS section. Verified with 'kb context spawn' - all 15 models now surface alongside constraints/decisions/investigations."}
{"id":"orch-go-65pl","title":"Add orch abandon --reason flag for failure context","description":"From og-inv-failure-mode-artifacts-21dec: Successful agents produce SYNTHESIS.md, abandoned agents produce nothing. Add --reason flag to orch abandon that creates beads comment capturing why agent was abandoned. Also consider enhancing events.jsonl with failure_mode and last_phase fields.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-12-26T15:25:35.427678-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-26T15:29:35.529601-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-26T15:29:35.529601-08:00","close_reason":"Already implemented - orch abandon --reason flag exists with FAILURE_REPORT.md","labels":["skill:feature-impl","triage:ready"]}
