{"id":"orch-go-66e7b","title":"Synthesize model investigations (10)","description":"## Synthesis Needed\n\nTopic **model** has accumulated 10 investigations that may benefit from consolidation.\n\n### Investigations to synthesize:\n\n- 2025-12-20-inv-investigate-model-flexibility-arbitrage-orch.md\n- 2025-12-20-inv-research-gemini-model-arbitrage-alternatives.md\n- 2025-12-20-research-model-arbitrage-api-vs-max.md\n- 2025-12-21-inv-fix-buildspawncommand-pass-model-flag.md\n- 2025-12-21-inv-model-handling-conflicts-between-orch.md\n- 2025-12-22-inv-model-flexibility-phase-expand-model.md\n- 2025-12-23-inv-model-selection-issue-architect-agent.md\n- 2025-12-24-inv-model-provider-architecture-orch-vs.md\n- 2026-01-04-inv-implement-priority-cascade-model-dashboard.md\n- 2025-12-24-inv-test-gemini-flash-model-resolution.md\n\n### Chronicle Timeline\n\n```\n2025-12-20 [INV] Explore Tradeoffs for orch-go OpenCode Integration\n2025-12-20 [INV] Add Missing Spawn Flags\n2025-12-20 [INV] KB Search vs Grep Benchmark\n2025-12-20 [INV] Compare orch-cli (Python) vs orch-go Features\n2025-12-20 [INV] Fix Spawn to Use Standalone Mode with TUI\n... (run kb chronicle for full timeline)\n```\n\n### Suggested Action\n\n1. Run `kb chronicle \"model\"` to understand evolution\n2. Identify patterns and contradictions across investigations\n3. Create a synthesized decision or consolidated investigation\n","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-07T20:13:48.961502-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-07T22:47:00.198633-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-07T22:47:00.198633-08:00","close_reason":"Bulk close: kb reflect synthesis noise","labels":["triage:review"]}
{"id":"orch-go-66n","title":"Implement Synthesis Protocol (D.E.K.N. Schema \u0026 Verification Gate)","description":"Implement the Synthesis Protocol designed by Alpha/Beta agents.\n1. Create .orch/templates/SYNTHESIS.md with D.E.K.N. structure.\n2. Update pkg/verify/check.go to enforce SYNTHESIS.md existence during 'orch complete'.\n3. Update SPAWN_CONTEXT.md template in pkg/spawn/context.go to require SYNTHESIS.md before Phase: Complete.\n4. Ensure agents are instructed to use 'kn' for the Knowledge section.","status":"closed","priority":0,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-12-20T16:19:04.283481-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-20T16:29:12.663559-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-20T16:29:12.663559-08:00","labels":["triage:ready"]}
{"id":"orch-go-66rk","title":"[orch-go] writing-skills: Create kb-reflect skill for triaging kb reflect...","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-12-23T17:19:29.984118-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-23T22:29:09.899087-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-23T22:29:09.899087-08:00","close_reason":"Created kb-reflect skill with decision trees for all 5 finding types (synthesis, promote, stale, drift, open), scheduling guidance, and investigation closure procedure. Committed to both orch-go and skills repos."}
{"id":"orch-go-67gkh","title":"Orchestrator sessions need checkpoint discipline (max 2-3 hours)","description":"## Problem\n\nThe price-watch orchestrator session ran 09:32-14:45 (5+ hours) and ended with outcome 'partial'. Long sessions without checkpoints lead to:\n\n- Context exhaustion\n- Degraded output quality\n- Lost work if session dies\n- No opportunity for meta-orchestrator course correction\n\n## Proposed Solution\n\nOrchestrator checkpoint discipline:\n- At 2 hours: Write interim handoff, assess if continuing or fresh session\n- At 3 hours: Strongly consider handoff and fresh session\n- Never exceed 4 hours without handoff\n\n## Implementation Options\n\n1. **Skill guidance**: Add checkpoint discipline to orchestrator skill\n2. **Automated reminder**: Daemon or timer sends 'checkpoint reminder' at 2h mark\n3. **Workspace timestamp check**: orch status shows session duration, warns if \u003e2h\n\n## Evidence\n\n- pw-orch-resume-price-watch-06jan-bcd7: 5h session, partial outcome\n- Prior decision: 'Orchestrator sessions should transition at 75-80% context usage'\n- Pattern: Long sessions correlate with partial/degraded outcomes","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-06T15:16:55.985647-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-06T18:50:34.767422-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-06T18:50:34.767422-08:00","close_reason":"Implemented session checkpoint discipline (2h/3h/4h thresholds) with visual warnings in orch session status and advice in orch session end. Tests pass, CLI works."}
{"id":"orch-go-68afq","title":"Implement tiered stuck agent recovery","description":"## Summary\n\nImplement the stuck agent recovery mechanism designed in `.kb/investigations/2026-01-15-inv-design-stuck-agent-recovery-mechanism.md`.\n\n## Design (from design session)\n\n**Tiered approach:**\n1. **Auto-resume** (non-destructive) - For idle agents \u003e10min without Phase: Complete\n2. **Surface in dashboard** - If still stuck after 15min post-resume, show in Needs Attention\n\n**Principle:** Advisory recovery over automatic recovery (follows ghost visibility and stalled detection patterns)\n\n## Implementation Sequence\n\n1. **Stuck detection in daemon** - Identify idle \u003e10min without Phase: Complete\n2. **Auto-resume with rate limiting** - 1 resume/hour per agent max\n3. **Needs Attention integration** - Surface if still stuck 15min after resume attempt\n\n## Files to modify\n\n- `pkg/daemon/daemon.go` - Add recovery loop alongside poll-spawn-complete\n- `cmd/orch/resume.go` - May need rate limiting support\n- Dashboard integration for Needs Attention\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] Daemon detects stuck agents (idle \u003e10min, no Phase: Complete)\n- [ ] Auto-resume triggered with rate limiting\n- [ ] Failed resumes surface in dashboard Needs Attention\n- [ ] Resume doesn't perpetuate infinite loops (diagnostic check)\n\n## References\n\n- Design: `.kb/investigations/2026-01-15-inv-design-stuck-agent-recovery-mechanism.md`\n- SYNTHESIS: `.orch/workspace/og-work-design-stuck-agent-15jan-faa3/SYNTHESIS.md`","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-01-15T09:31:56.771276-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-18T12:18:58.627351-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-18T12:18:58.627351-08:00","close_reason":"Tiered stuck agent recovery verified complete. Added 16 comprehensive tests, all passing. Feature already implemented with daemon recovery loop, helper functions, dashboard integration. Deliverables: recovery_test.go (test suite), SYNTHESIS.md (documentation). Commit 425518f4.","labels":["triage:ready"]}
