{"id":"orch-go-6f8g3","title":"Synthesize orchestrator investigations (37)","description":"## Synthesis Needed\n\nTopic **orchestrator** has accumulated 37 investigations that may benefit from consolidation.\n\n### Investigations to synthesize:\n\n- 2025-12-21-inv-orchestrator-session-boundaries.md\n- 2025-12-23-inv-cleanup-after-orchestrator-skill-loading.md\n- 2025-12-23-inv-explore-value-orchestrator-worker-awareness.md\n- 2025-12-23-inv-orchestrator-skill-loading-workers-despite.md\n- 2025-12-23-inv-update-orchestrator-skill-reflect-headless.md\n- 2025-12-24-inv-orchestrator-skill-says-complete-agents.md\n- 2025-12-25-design-orchestrator-completion-lifecycle-two.md\n- 2025-12-25-inv-orchestrator-pre-spawn-context-gathering.md\n- 2025-12-25-inv-should-orchestrator-have-visibility-into.md\n- 2025-12-27-inv-capacity-utilization-workflow-orchestrator-proactively.md\n- 2025-12-27-inv-document-orch-patterns-command-orchestrator.md\n- 2025-12-27-inv-orchestrator-self-correction-mechanisms-problem.md\n- 2026-01-04-design-meta-orchestrator-architecture-spawnable-orchestrator.md\n- 2026-01-04-design-meta-orchestrator-role-definition.md\n- 2026-01-04-design-orchestrator-skill-spawnable-agent-gap.md\n- 2026-01-04-inv-meta-orchestrator-level-collapse-spawned.md\n- 2026-01-04-inv-phase-orchestrator-context-md-template.md\n- 2026-01-04-inv-spawnable-orchestrator-sessions-infrastructure-changes.md\n- 2026-01-04-inv-test-spawnable-orchestrator-infrastructure.md\n- 2026-01-04-inv-test-spawnable-orchestrator-tmux-default.md\n- 2026-01-05-debug-orch-complete-fails-orchestrator-sessions.md\n- 2026-01-05-debug-orchestrator-workspace-name-collision-bug.md\n- 2026-01-05-inv-design-orchestrator-session-lifecycle-without.md\n- 2026-01-05-inv-feat-038-unregister-orchestrator-sessions.md\n- 2026-01-05-inv-fix-orchestrator-context-md-contradiction.md\n- 2026-01-05-inv-orchestrator-worker-bidirectional-communication-interaction.md\n- 2026-01-05-inv-orchestrator-workspaces-clear-visual-distinction.md\n- 2026-01-05-inv-update-meta-orchestrator-skill-session.md\n- 2026-01-06-inv-detect-orchestrator-frame-collapse-doing.md\n- 2026-01-06-inv-diagnose-orchestrator-skill-18-completion.md\n- 2026-01-06-inv-interactive-orchestrator-sessions-don-create.md\n- 2026-01-06-inv-orchestrator-sessions-checkpoint-discipline-max.md\n- 2026-01-06-inv-orchestrator-sessions-spawned-via-tmux.md\n- 2026-01-07-design-orch-stats-miscounts-orchestrator-meta.md\n- 2026-01-07-inv-add-principles-quick-reference-orchestrator.md\n- 2026-01-07-inv-implement-follow-orchestrator-dashboard-filtering.md\n- 2026-01-07-inv-update-orchestrator-skill-add-dashboard.md\n\n### Chronicle Timeline\n\n```\n2025-12-19 [INV] CLI orch complete Command Implementation\n2025-12-19 [INV] CLI orch spawn Command Implementation\n2025-12-19 [INV] Set beads issue status to in_progress on spawn\n2025-12-20 [INV] Explore Tradeoffs for orch-go OpenCode Integration\n2025-12-20 [INV] Synthesis Protocol Design for Agent Handoffs\n... (run kb chronicle for full timeline)\n```\n\n### Suggested Action\n\n1. Run `kb chronicle \"orchestrator\"` to understand evolution\n2. Identify patterns and contradictions across investigations\n3. Create a synthesized decision or consolidated investigation\n","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-07T22:46:05.212752-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-07T22:46:43.374004-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-07T22:46:43.374004-08:00","close_reason":"Bulk close: kb reflect synthesis issues are noise until detection is fixed","labels":["triage:review"]}
{"id":"orch-go-6g1r","title":"Implement orch patterns for action outcome tracking","description":"## Problem\n\nThe orchestrator doesn't self-correct when repeatedly making the same mistake because action outcomes are ephemeral and untracked. Knowledge of correct behavior doesn't prevent incorrect behavior.\n\n## Evidence\n\n1. **Investigation 2025-12-27-inv-orchestrator-self-correction-mechanisms** found:\n   - All existing mechanisms track knowledge state, not action outcomes\n   - Tool failures are ephemeral - no 'session action log'\n   - Pattern 'action → outcome → pattern detection → adjustment' is broken at step 2\n\n2. **Session ses_474f** showed orchestrator:\n   - Tried `orch abandon` - failed\n   - Tried `orch complete` - failed  \n   - Tried manual jq edits - failed\n   - None of this is tracked; next session will retry same futile actions\n\n## Solution (from investigation)\n\nImplement action outcome logging + pattern surfacing:\n\n1. **Action logging subsystem** - Create `~/.orch/action-log.jsonl` tracking tool invocations with outcomes (success/empty/error)\n2. **Pattern analyzer** - Detect 'repeated action with same outcome' patterns\n3. **Surfacing mechanism** - `orch patterns` command to show detected behavioral patterns\n\nExample output:\n```\nDetected patterns:\n  ⚠️  Read SYNTHESIS.md on light-tier agents: 3 empty results (light-tier doesn't produce SYNTHESIS.md)\n  ⚠️  orch abandon on untracked agents: 2 failures (use orch clean --untracked instead)\n```\n\n## Principle\n\n**Track Actions, Not Just State** - 'The system captures what's known but not what's done. Knowledge of correct behavior doesn't prevent incorrect behavior.'\n\n## Prior Art\n\n- `pkg/verify/attempts.go` implements retry pattern detection for spawn/abandon cycles\n- `events.jsonl` pattern exists for lifecycle events\n- Investigation has full implementation details","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-01-04T14:25:57.371684-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-04T14:33:00.062818-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-04T14:33:00.062818-08:00","close_reason":"Already implemented. orch patterns command exists with action-log.jsonl (11K entries) and pkg/patterns/analyzer.go. Feature survived the Jan 2 rollback."}
{"id":"orch-go-6g2mf","title":"Cannot query OpenCode sessions from other projects","description":"## Problem\n\nOpenCode sessions are project-scoped. The server on port 4096 only shows orch-go sessions. Price-watch sessions are on a different server (port 55450 or spawned differently).\n\nThis means meta-orchestrator can't:\n- Message orchestrator sessions from other projects\n- Query session state across projects\n- Resume cross-project orchestrators\n\n## Discovery\n\nTried to message pw-orch-resume-price-watch-06jan-bcd7 to ask why it didn't use --mcp playwright. Session wasn't in the orch-go OpenCode server. Had to check multiple ports to find sessions were scattered.\n\n## Possible Solutions\n\n1. **Central session registry**: Single source of truth for all sessions across projects\n2. **Cross-project API**: Query sessions by workspace name regardless of project\n3. **Session federation**: Meta-orchestrator knows which server has which project\n\n## Severity\n\nP3 - Inconvenient but workaround exists (check multiple servers manually). Becomes more important as cross-project orchestration increases.\n\n## Related\n\n- Cross-project daemon design (orch-go-g7hax)\n- Workspace-session architecture investigation","status":"closed","priority":3,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-06T15:17:09.172821-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-06T17:40:35.80394-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-06T17:40:35.80394-08:00","close_reason":"Cross-project session query implementation"}
