{"id":"orch-go-6hhaa","title":"Bug: orch status --json output contains warning line that breaks JSON parsing","description":"The 'orch status --json' command outputs a warning line '⚠️  Auto-rebuild failed: rebuild already in progress' before the JSON, causing jq and other JSON parsers to fail. This breaks automation that depends on JSON output. Need to either suppress the warning for JSON output or redirect warnings to stderr.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-09T13:17:02.809178-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-09T18:14:52.421214-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-09T18:14:52.421214-08:00","close_reason":"Fixed auto-rebuild warning contamination of JSON output. Tests: go test ./cmd/orch - all tests passing (1.867s), TestHasJSONFlag verified flag detection works correctly. Smoke test: orch status --json produces clean JSON without warnings."}
