{"id":"orch-go-6kpp","title":"[beads] investigation: Beads fork analysis - evaluate divergence from ...","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-12-30T08:19:30.842879-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-30T08:32:42.26177-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-30T08:32:42.26177-08:00","close_reason":"Fresh rebase recommended. 5/8 code fixes already upstreamed (PRs #683, #684, #686, #688 with Dylan co-author). Fork served its purpose for investigation + contribution. 70K line divergence not worth maintaining for 3 daemon commits. Leave it Better: kn not available, decision documented in investigation. Supersedes prior investigation that missed upstream PRs."}
{"id":"orch-go-6lwiw","title":"Add orch stats command to aggregate events.jsonl metrics","description":"## Problem\n\nThe orchestration system captures extensive telemetry in events.jsonl (4145+ events, 27 types) but doesn't aggregate it for decision support. Orchestrators must run multiple commands or analyze raw JSONL to understand system health.\n\nCurrent state:\n- events.jsonl tracks spawns (1522), completions (1452), abandonments (77), daemon activity (420)\n- Completion rate is 95.4%, abandonment rate is 5.1% - but these aren't surfaced anywhere\n- Existing analytical commands (history, hotspot, retries, reconcile) are fragmented\n\n## Solution\n\nCreate `orch stats` command that aggregates events.jsonl to surface:\n\n**Core metrics:**\n1. Completion rate (overall and by skill)\n2. Abandonment rate (with trend)\n3. Session duration (avg, p50, p90 from spawn→complete timestamps)\n4. Skill breakdown (spawns and completion rates per skill)\n5. Spawn mode analysis (headless vs tmux effectiveness)\n6. Daemon health (spawn count, auto-completion rate)\n\n**Friction indicators:**\n- Frame collapse frequency (context exhaustion abandonments)\n- Wait timeout ratio (agent.wait.timeout / agent.wait.complete)\n- Zombie rate (reconcile needed frequency)\n\n**Flags:**\n- `--days N` - Time window (default: 7)\n- `--json` - Machine-readable output\n- `--skill NAME` - Filter to specific skill\n\n## Evidence\n\nInvestigation: `.kb/investigations/2026-01-06-inv-orch-stats-command-if-so.md`\n\nEvent types available:\n```\nsession.spawned: 1522\nagent.completed: 1452\nagent.abandoned: 77\ndaemon.spawn: 420\nagent.wait.complete: 42\nagent.wait.timeout: 11\nspawn.telemetry: 317\n```\n\n## Implementation Notes\n\n- Parse events.jsonl efficiently (stream, don't load all)\n- Timestamps are Unix seconds (not milliseconds)\n- Some early events lack session_id - handle gracefully\n- Follow existing patterns from history.go, hotspot.go","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-01-06T15:49:40.556071-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-06T16:04:02.601207-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-06T16:04:02.601207-08:00","close_reason":"Implemented orch stats command that aggregates events.jsonl to surface orchestration metrics (completion rates, skill effectiveness, daemon health). Includes --days, --json, --verbose flags. Tests passing. Committed c50a4a94."}
{"id":"orch-go-6m57t","title":"Update orchestrator skill with session resume system documentation","description":"The orchestrator skill mentions session end but doesn't explain the automatic session resume system implemented in Jan 2026.\n\nOrchestrators need to know:\n- Handoffs are automatic (injected via hooks at session start)\n- File structure: .orch/session/latest/SESSION_HANDOFF.md (project-specific)\n- How it works: Hooks call 'orch session resume --for-injection'\n- Your responsibility: Just run 'orch session end', system handles creation/injection\n\nCurrent gaps:\n- References outdated SESSION_CONTEXT.md at ~/.orch/session/{date}/\n- Doesn't explain automatic injection via hooks\n- Missing the 'don't manually read handoffs' guidance\n\nReference: .kb/guides/session-resume-protocol.md has full details to synthesize into skill","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-13T11:14:55.668543-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-13T11:47:29.631397-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-13T11:47:29.631397-08:00","close_reason":"Cross-repo modification: changes committed in orch-knowledge (09c4c16) and ~/.claude (91e82a6), verified via git log"}
