{"id":"orch-go-6pn2g","title":"Synthesize orchestrator investigations (33)","description":"## Synthesis Needed\n\nTopic **orchestrator** has accumulated 33 investigations that may benefit from consolidation.\n\n### Investigations to synthesize:\n\n- 2025-12-21-inv-orchestrator-session-boundaries.md\n- 2025-12-23-inv-cleanup-after-orchestrator-skill-loading.md\n- 2025-12-23-inv-explore-value-orchestrator-worker-awareness.md\n- 2025-12-23-inv-orchestrator-skill-loading-workers-despite.md\n- 2025-12-23-inv-update-orchestrator-skill-reflect-headless.md\n- 2025-12-24-inv-orchestrator-skill-says-complete-agents.md\n- 2025-12-25-design-orchestrator-completion-lifecycle-two.md\n- 2025-12-25-inv-orchestrator-pre-spawn-context-gathering.md\n- 2025-12-25-inv-should-orchestrator-have-visibility-into.md\n- 2025-12-27-inv-capacity-utilization-workflow-orchestrator-proactively.md\n- 2025-12-27-inv-document-orch-patterns-command-orchestrator.md\n- 2025-12-27-inv-orchestrator-self-correction-mechanisms-problem.md\n- 2026-01-04-design-meta-orchestrator-architecture-spawnable-orchestrator.md\n- 2026-01-04-design-meta-orchestrator-role-definition.md\n- 2026-01-04-design-orchestrator-skill-spawnable-agent-gap.md\n- 2026-01-04-inv-meta-orchestrator-level-collapse-spawned.md\n- 2026-01-04-inv-phase-orchestrator-context-md-template.md\n- 2026-01-04-inv-spawnable-orchestrator-sessions-infrastructure-changes.md\n- 2026-01-04-inv-test-spawnable-orchestrator-infrastructure.md\n- 2026-01-04-inv-test-spawnable-orchestrator-tmux-default.md\n- 2026-01-05-debug-orch-complete-fails-orchestrator-sessions.md\n- 2026-01-05-debug-orchestrator-workspace-name-collision-bug.md\n- 2026-01-05-inv-design-orchestrator-session-lifecycle-without.md\n- 2026-01-05-inv-feat-038-unregister-orchestrator-sessions.md\n- 2026-01-05-inv-fix-orchestrator-context-md-contradiction.md\n- 2026-01-05-inv-orchestrator-worker-bidirectional-communication-interaction.md\n- 2026-01-05-inv-orchestrator-workspaces-clear-visual-distinction.md\n- 2026-01-05-inv-update-meta-orchestrator-skill-session.md\n- 2026-01-06-inv-detect-orchestrator-frame-collapse-doing.md\n- 2026-01-06-inv-diagnose-orchestrator-skill-18-completion.md\n- 2026-01-06-inv-interactive-orchestrator-sessions-don-create.md\n- 2026-01-06-inv-orchestrator-sessions-checkpoint-discipline-max.md\n- 2026-01-06-inv-orchestrator-sessions-spawned-via-tmux.md\n\n### Chronicle Timeline\n\n```\n2025-12-19 [INV] CLI orch complete Command Implementation\n2025-12-19 [INV] CLI orch spawn Command Implementation\n2025-12-19 [INV] Set beads issue status to in_progress on spawn\n2025-12-20 [INV] Explore Tradeoffs for orch-go OpenCode Integration\n2025-12-20 [INV] Synthesis Protocol Design for Agent Handoffs\n... (run kb chronicle for full timeline)\n```\n\n### Suggested Action\n\n1. Run `kb chronicle \"orchestrator\"` to understand evolution\n2. Identify patterns and contradictions across investigations\n3. Create a synthesized decision or consolidated investigation\n","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-06T21:38:01.046982-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-07T06:56:20.590661-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-07T06:56:20.590661-08:00","close_reason":"Duplicate of orch-go-5kjlw","labels":["triage:review"]}
{"id":"orch-go-6qsq","title":"Agent card should reflect processing state after orch send","description":"Gap: After orch send, the agent card still shows 'Complete' phase with no indication it's processing a follow-up. The session.send event appears in Agent Lifecycle log, but the card doesn't update. Expected: Card should show processing indicator (yellow pulse) when agent is responding to a follow-up. May need to: 1) Have orch send trigger a status refresh, 2) SSE events from response should update is_processing, 3) Phase could show 'Follow-up' or similar.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-12-24T09:33:20.766377-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-24T10:31:31.408251-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-24T10:31:31.408251-08:00","close_reason":"Added SSE-driven is_processing state with yellow pulse indicator. Agent cards now visually distinguish active processing (yellow border/pulse) from idle Complete phase. Changes: agents.ts (SSE event handling), agent-card.svelte (visual styling). Commit 3f5c75d.","labels":["triage:ready"]}
{"id":"orch-go-6sle3","title":"Synthesize beads investigations (18)","description":"## Synthesis Needed\n\nTopic **beads** has accumulated 18 investigations that may benefit from consolidation.\n\n### Investigations to synthesize:\n\n- 2025-12-19-inv-set-beads-issue-status-progress.md\n- 2025-12-20-inv-scaffold-beads-ui-v2-bun.md\n- 2025-12-21-inv-beads-kb-workspace-relationships-how.md\n- 2025-12-21-inv-beads-oss-relationship-fork-vs.md\n- 2025-12-21-inv-orch-complete-closes-beads-issue.md\n- 2025-12-22-inv-beads-multi-repo-hydration-why.md\n- 2025-12-24-inv-add-beads-stats-dashboard-stats.md\n- 2025-12-24-inv-add-fallback-beads-close-reason.md\n- 2025-12-25-inv-beads-database-pollution-orch-go.md\n- 2025-12-25-inv-design-beads-integration-strategy-orch.md\n- 2025-12-25-inv-implement-pkg-beads-go-rpc.md\n- 2025-12-26-inv-implement-pkg-beads-rpc-client.md\n- 2026-01-03-inv-fix-short-beads-id-resolution.md\n- 2026-01-03-inv-recover-priority-beads-deduplication-abstraction.md\n- 2026-01-05-inv-fix-beads-type-field-showing.md\n- 2026-01-07-inv-consider-auto-starting-beads-daemon.md\n- 2026-01-04-debug-orch-review-timeout-beads-api.md\n- 2026-01-04-inv-remove-beads-tracking-orchestrator-meta.md\n\n### Chronicle Timeline\n\n```\n2025-12-19 [INV] CLI orch complete Command Implementation\n2025-12-19 [INV] CLI orch spawn Command Implementation\n2025-12-19 [INV] Set beads issue status to in_progress on spawn\n2025-12-19 [INV] Update README with current CLI commands and usage\n2025-12-19 [INV] Fix comment ID parsing - Comment.ID type mismatch\n... (run kb chronicle for full timeline)\n```\n\n### Suggested Action\n\n1. Run `kb chronicle \"beads\"` to understand evolution\n2. Identify patterns and contradictions across investigations\n3. Create a synthesized decision or consolidated investigation\n","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-07T22:46:06.193575-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-07T22:46:42.912981-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-07T22:46:42.912981-08:00","close_reason":"Bulk close: kb reflect synthesis issues are noise until detection is fixed","labels":["triage:review"]}
{"id":"orch-go-6su0","title":"Add /api/daemon endpoint to orch serve","description":"New endpoint returns daemon health: read ~/.orch/daemon-status.json + launchd process check. Stall detection: if ready_count \u003e 0 and last_spawn \u003e 2x poll_interval, status=stalled. Follow /api/servers pattern. Depends on daemon status file (feat-014).","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-12-26T09:34:07.197071-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-26T15:29:35.391188-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-26T15:29:35.391188-08:00","close_reason":"Already implemented - /api/daemon endpoint exists","labels":["skill:feature-impl","triage:ready"]}
{"id":"orch-go-6tdr","title":"orch status hangs/crashes with exit code 137 (SIGKILL)","description":"## Problem\n\n`orch status` and `orch complete` commands hang and get killed (exit 137 = SIGKILL).\n\n## Evidence\n\n```bash\n~/bin/orch status 2\u003e\u00261 || echo \"exit code: $?\"\n# Output: exit code: 137\n\ntimeout 10 ~/bin/orch complete orch-go-9e15.3 2\u003e\u00261\n# Output: Timed out or failed\n```\n\n## Impact\n\n- Can't use CLI to check agent status\n- Can't use CLI to complete agents\n- Have to manually close via `bd close`\n\n## Likely cause\n\nSomething in the status/complete command is blocking indefinitely - possibly:\n- HTTP request to OpenCode hanging\n- File lock contention\n- Infinite loop in reconciliation","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2025-12-23T15:55:59.189783-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-23T16:13:27.895275-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-23T16:13:27.895275-08:00","close_reason":"Root cause: stale binary at ~/bin/orch. Fixed by force reinstalling from cmd/orch build. Not a code bug."}
{"id":"orch-go-6u94","title":"Improve orch abandon cross-project error messages","description":"From multi-project architecture design. When orch abandon fails due to cross-project beads ID, provide helpful error: 'Issue X not found in current project (Y). This appears to be from project Z. To abandon, run: cd /path/to/Z \u0026\u0026 orch abandon X'. Use extractProjectFromBeadsID() to detect mismatch.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-12-26T16:20:48.293737-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-26T18:02:38.817404-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-26T18:02:38.817404-08:00","close_reason":"Added --workdir flag to orch abandon and improved cross-project error messages with helpful hints. Build and tests pass.","labels":["skill:feature-impl","triage:ready"]}
{"id":"orch-go-6uli","title":"Epic: Orch Ecosystem Consolidation (6-month)","description":"Consolidate 8 repos to 4 functional units. See .kb/investigations/2025-12-24-inv-full-ecosystem-audit-scope-simplify.md for full analysis.\n\n## Success Criteria\n- Single knowledge CLI (kb) instead of two\n- orch-go as only orchestration CLI  \n- All skill references point to valid tools\n- beads interaction via abstraction layer\n\n## Evidence\n- orch-go: 37k LoC, 334 skill refs\n- kb+kn: 231 combined skill refs, conceptual overlap\n- agentlog: only 14 skill refs (orphaned)\n- Python orch-cli: ~80% parity achieved","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"epic","created_at":"2025-12-27T18:08:35.435575-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-03T14:25:32.754314-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-03T14:25:32.754314-08:00","close_reason":"Stale 6-month roadmap epic - closing, can reopen if needed"}
{"id":"orch-go-6uli.1","title":"Phase 1: kb absorbs kn (Month 1)","description":"## Scope\nAdd kb quick subcommand with kn semantics, migrate .kn entries to .kb format, deprecate kn binary.\n\n## Tasks\n1. Design kb quick subcommand interface (match kn decide/tried/constrain/question)\n2. Implement kb quick command with all kn entry types\n3. Create migration script: .kn/*.jsonl → .kb/knowledge/\n4. Add deprecation warning to kn binary (point to kb quick)\n5. Update skill references from 'kn' to 'kb quick'\n6. Test migration on real .kn directories\n\n## Success Criteria  \n- kb quick matches kn command behavior\n- All existing .kn entries migratable\n- kn commands print deprecation warnings","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-12-27T18:08:45.872672-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-28T10:19:26.309069-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-28T10:19:26.309069-08:00","close_reason":"Investigation produced: Phase 1 is 90% done. Tasks 1-4 complete, Task 5 scope minimal (only global CLAUDE.md), Task 6 has test data. Recommend: single implementation spawn to finish (~1 hour work).","labels":["triage:review"]}
{"id":"orch-go-6uli.2","title":"Phase 2: orch-go Python parity (Month 2-3)","description":"## Scope\nPort remaining Python features to orch-go, add deprecation warnings to Python orch-cli, update skill references.\n\n## Missing Features to Port\n- synthesis - Synthesize recent activity\n- transcript - Session transcript management\n- friction - Analyze agent friction points  \n- stale - Show stale beads issues\n- doc-check/doc-gen - Documentation management\n- lint - CLAUDE.md size checking\n- logs - Command logging viewer\n- history - Agent history with analytics\n\n## Tasks\n1. Audit Python orch-cli for complete feature list\n2. Prioritize features by skill reference count\n3. Port each feature (separate issues per feature recommended)\n4. Add deprecation warnings to Python binary\n5. Update skill references from Python orch to orch-go\n6. E2E test parity on real workflows\n\n## Success Criteria\n- All Python features available in orch-go\n- Python orch-cli prints deprecation warnings\n- Skills use orch-go exclusively","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-12-27T18:08:55.686346-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-03T14:25:32.778059-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-03T14:25:32.778059-08:00","close_reason":"Stale 6-month roadmap epic - closing, can reopen if needed","labels":["triage:review"]}
{"id":"orch-go-6uli.3","title":"Phase 3: beads abstraction layer (Month 4)","description":"## Scope\nCreate pkg/beads/client.go interface to reduce direct bd CLI calls and enable mock testing.\n\n## Tasks\n1. Audit current bd CLI calls in orch-go codebase\n2. Design beads client interface (create, close, comment, list, etc.)\n3. Implement CLI-backed client (wraps bd commands)\n4. Add mock implementation for testing\n5. Refactor orch-go commands to use client interface\n6. Add integration tests with mock beads\n\n## Why Abstraction Needed\n- beads is external dependency (stevey's project)\n- Direct CLI coupling makes testing hard\n- API stability not guaranteed\n- Enables potential direct beads-lib integration later\n\n## Success Criteria\n- pkg/beads/client.go interface exists\n- All orch-go commands use client interface\n- Mock client enables unit testing without bd binary","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-12-27T18:09:04.683674-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-03T14:25:32.799597-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-03T14:25:32.799597-08:00","close_reason":"Stale 6-month roadmap epic - closing, can reopen if needed","labels":["triage:review"]}
{"id":"orch-go-6uli.4","title":"Phase 4: Final cleanup (Month 5-6)","description":"## Scope\nArchive Python orch-cli, evaluate agentlog, consider skillc integration.\n\n## Tasks\n\n### Python orch-cli Archive\n1. Verify all features ported to orch-go\n2. Final deprecation announcement\n3. Archive repository (GitHub archive)\n4. Remove from PATH in user configs\n\n### agentlog Evaluation  \n- Current state: 14 skill references (low adoption)\n- Options:\n  a) Archive (low value, maintenance cost)\n  b) Integrate into orch-go (orch log subcommand)\n  c) Revive with spawn integration\n- Decision needed before action\n\n### skillc Integration (Optional)\n- Currently: Standalone binary, works well\n- Option: Add 'orch skill build/deploy' subcommands\n- Decision: Likely keep separate (build tool pattern works)\n\n## Success Criteria\n- Python orch-cli archived\n- agentlog decision made and executed\n- skillc integration decision documented","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-12-27T18:09:15.31664-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-03T14:25:32.819763-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-03T14:25:32.819763-08:00","close_reason":"Stale 6-month roadmap epic - closing, can reopen if needed","labels":["triage:review"]}
{"id":"orch-go-6uli.5","title":"Phase 5: Integration verification and documentation","description":"## Purpose\nPer constraint: 'Epics with parallel component work must include a final integration child issue'\n\n## Integration Verification Tasks\n1. E2E workflow test: spawn → monitor → complete cycle with unified tooling\n2. Verify all skill references point to valid tools (no dead commands)\n3. Test kb context works across all knowledge formats (former kn + kb)\n4. Verify beads abstraction doesn't break existing spawn workflows\n5. Smoke test overnight daemon batch processing\n\n## Documentation Updates\n1. Update ~/.orch/ECOSYSTEM.md with new 4-repo structure\n2. Update orchestrator skill with consolidated tool references\n3. Update all worker skills referencing deprecated tools\n4. Archive/remove references to Python orch-cli\n5. Document migration path for users\n\n## Success Criteria\n- Full orchestration cycle works with consolidated tools\n- No skill references to deprecated binaries (kn, Python orch)\n- Documentation reflects actual tool landscape\n- User migration guide available","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-12-27T18:09:26.97709-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-03T14:25:32.839758-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-03T14:25:32.839758-08:00","close_reason":"Stale 6-month roadmap epic - closing, can reopen if needed","labels":["triage:review"]}
