{"id":"orch-go-6vmr","title":"[orch-go] systematic-debugging: Web UI not loading - svelte-check shows 'Expect...","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-12-31T18:21:22.444815-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-31T18:27:02.377761-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-31T18:27:02.377761-08:00","close_reason":"Fixed TypeScript error in theme.ts where thinkingOpacity (number) was incorrectly cast to Record\u003cstring, ColorValue\u003e. svelte-check now passes with 0 errors."}
{"id":"orch-go-6vr6","title":"Fix headless spawn race condition - add message verification after SendPrompt","description":"Root cause identified in orch-go-tulk investigation: SendPrompt is called immediately after CreateSession with no delay/verification in headless mode, while tmux mode has 1-second delay. Fix: After calling SendPrompt, poll GetMessages until message count \u003e 0 (or timeout after 5s). If verification fails, retry SendPrompt once. See: .kb/investigations/2025-12-30-inv-headless-spawn-silent-failures-agents.md","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2025-12-30T09:57:48.789171-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-30T10:06:39.263911-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-30T10:06:39.263911-08:00","close_reason":"Fixed headless spawn race condition by adding message verification after SendPrompt. WaitForMessage polls GetMessages until count \u003e 0 (5s timeout, 300ms interval). SendPromptWithVerification retries once if verification fails. All unit tests passing. Changes committed in 155e1771."}
{"id":"orch-go-6w1f8","title":"/api/agents endpoint fixed - 32s to 627ms","description":"## Completed\nFixed /api/agents performance issue (32s → 627ms, 50x improvement).\n\n## Root Causes Fixed\n1. O(n²) investigation discovery - cached directory listings\n2. beadsFetchThreshold regression (24h → 2h restored)\n\n## Commit\nf87bedf4 - 'perf: fix /api/agents O(n²) investigation discovery + restore 2h threshold'\n\n## Reference\n- .kb/investigations/2026-01-07-inv-dashboard-api-agents-performance-synthesis.md","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-07T10:41:45.692624-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-07T10:42:00.73552-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-07T10:42:00.73552-08:00","close_reason":"Already completed - commit f87bedf4"}
{"id":"orch-go-6wga","title":"feat-036: Skip beads issue creation for orchestrator spawns","description":"Modify spawn to skip beads issue creation when spawning orchestrator-type skills.\n\n## Context\nDecision 2026-01-05-orchestrator-lifecycle-without-beads.md establishes that orchestrators should not use beads. Currently beads issues are created but then ignored (vestigial).\n\n## Implementation\n- In pkg/spawn/ or cmd/orch/spawn_cmd.go\n- When IsOrchestrator=true, skip bd create call\n- Instead, register session in session registry (feat-035)\n- Preserve all other spawn behavior (tmux window, workspace creation, context generation)\n\n## Current Code Path\nBeads issue is created somewhere in the spawn flow for orchestrators. Find and conditionally skip.\n\n## Success Criteria\n- Orchestrator spawns create NO beads issue\n- Orchestrator spawns register in session registry\n- Worker spawns unchanged (still create beads issues)\n- Tests verify both paths\n\n## Dependencies\n- feat-035 (session registry) must be implemented first\n\n## References\n- Decision: .kb/decisions/2026-01-05-orchestrator-lifecycle-without-beads.md","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-01-05T11:04:35.732921-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-05T11:35:29.09341-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-05T11:35:29.09341-08:00","close_reason":"Implemented feat-036: Orchestrator spawns now skip beads issue creation and register in session registry instead. Added registerOrchestratorSession helper called from all spawn modes (inline, headless, tmux). Workers unchanged - still use beads. Added 8 tests verifying both paths.","labels":["skill:feature-impl","triage:daemon"]}
{"id":"orch-go-6wxxt","title":"Update opencode fork plugin for Opus 4.5 auth bypass","description":"Investigation: 2026-01-09-inv-explore-opencode-github-issue-7410.md\n\nContext: Opus 4.5 restricted to Claude Code via auth gate. Community fix exists in opencode-anthropic-auth@0.0.7 that spoofs claude-cli identity.\n\nCurrent state: Built-in plugin in opencode fork is v0.0.5 (outdated).\n\nRecommendation: Update plugin version and rebuild opencode, noting ban risk to Dylan.\n\nTrade-off: Utility of Opus 4.5 vs risk of account suspension (confirmed bans on Reddit).\n\nEvidence: GitHub issue #7410 shows v0.0.7 adds ?beta=true flag and User-Agent spoofing to bypass gate.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-01-18T01:56:06.652192-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-29T10:37:18.646619-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-29T10:37:18.646619-08:00"}
{"id":"orch-go-6x36","title":"Add multi-provider model routing (OpenRouter/DeepSeek)","description":"## Problem\n\nWhen trying to use non-Claude models (Gemini 2.5 Flash, DeepSeek), the system doesn't handle them cleanly. Model aliases only cover Anthropic models currently.\n\n## Solution\n\nAdd model aliases for additional providers to `pkg/model/model.go`:\n\n### Phase 1: Gemini aliases\n- `flash` → `google/gemini-2.5-flash-preview-05-20`\n- `pro` → `google/gemini-2.5-pro-preview-05-06`\n\n### Phase 2: DeepSeek aliases (if API key configured)\n- `deepseek` → `deepseek/deepseek-chat`\n- `deepseek-r1` → `deepseek/deepseek-reasoner`\n\n### Phase 3: OpenRouter passthrough\n- `openrouter/\\*` format passthrough\n\n## Evidence\n\n- Investigation: `.kb/investigations/2025-12-24-inv-model-provider-architecture-orch-vs.md`\n- Current aliases in `pkg/model/model.go:46-83`\n- Architecture confirmed: orch owns aliases, OpenCode owns auth\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `orch spawn --model flash` works with Gemini\n- [ ] `orch spawn --model deepseek` works (if API key configured)\n- [ ] Existing Claude aliases unchanged","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-12-23T08:44:28.071191-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-25T22:14:51.517423-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-25T22:14:51.517423-08:00","close_reason":"Batch close from orch review","labels":["enhancement","triage:review"]}
