{"id":"orch-go-70bn6","title":"[orch-go] feature-impl: Add agent.completed event emission to bd close ...","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-08T06:12:32.657588-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-08T06:27:19.16383-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-08T06:27:19.16383-08:00","close_reason":"Added orch emit command and .beads/hooks/on_close script. When issues are closed via 'bd close', the hook emits agent.completed events to ~/.orch/events.jsonl. All tests pass. Full flow validated: bd close triggers hook which calls orch emit, event appears in events.jsonl with source=bd_close_hook."}
{"id":"orch-go-70ld","title":"OpenCode health endpoint returns 'redirected too many times' error","description":"curl http://127.0.0.1:4096/health returns UnknownError with 'The response redirected too many times'. Doesn't block daemon spawning but indicates something wrong with OpenCode server. Prior investigation (orch-go-zz42) found it's NOT auth-related - OpenCode handles OAuth refresh. Root cause still unclear.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-12-26T13:10:27.799948-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-26T18:06:54.072927-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-26T18:06:54.072927-08:00","close_reason":"Confirmed prior investigation findings. OpenCode does not have a /health endpoint (only /session). orch-go correctly uses ListSessions() to check OpenCode health. The 'redirected too many times' error occurs because /health is not a valid OpenCode route. No fix needed - this is expected behavior for non-existent endpoints.","labels":["skill:systematic-debugging","triage:ready"]}
