{"id":"orch-go-71pa","title":"Detect and handle agents that exhaust context with uncommitted work","description":"## Problem\n\nAgent orch-go-wj8n (spawn_cmd.go extraction) completed the implementation but exhausted context (76.6K tokens, 5 messages) before committing or writing SYNTHESIS.md. The work was done but 'landing' was incomplete.\n\n## Observed Pattern\n\n1. Agent does implementation work (files created/modified, tests pass)\n2. Agent exhausts context before 'Leave it Better' phase\n3. Session goes idle with uncommitted changes\n4. Orchestrator has to manually commit and close\n\n## Evidence\n\n- orch-go-wj8n: 76.6K tokens, spawn_cmd.go created but no commit\n- orch-go-poit: 21.7K tokens, completed normally (smaller task)\n\n## Potential Solutions\n\n1. **Detection**: Alert when agent goes idle with uncommitted changes in working directory\n2. **Checkpointing**: Add intermediate commits during implementation (not just at end)\n3. **Scope management**: Warn or split tasks estimated to exceed context budget\n4. **Graceful degradation**: If context pressure detected, prioritize commit over synthesis\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] System detects agents idle with uncommitted work\n- [ ] Orchestrator is alerted to incomplete landings\n- [ ] Consider: automatic recovery (commit on behalf of agent)","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-01-03T18:30:16.562165-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-03T20:22:52.597921-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-03T20:22:52.597921-08:00","close_reason":"Context exhaustion detection: RISK column with uncommitted work detection","labels":["triage:ready"]}
