{"id":"orch-go-74fvq","title":"tmux follower should find tmux in common locations, not rely on PATH","description":"## Problem\n\nThe `/api/context` endpoint fails with 'executable file not found in $PATH' when `orch serve` is started from a context without tmux in PATH (e.g., launchd, certain terminal contexts).\n\n```\n{\"error\":\"failed to get tmux cwd: exec: \\\"tmux\\\": executable file not found in $PATH\"}\n```\n\nThis causes the 'Following' toggle in the dashboard to spam errors every 2 seconds.\n\n## Root Cause\n\n`pkg/tmux/follower.go:237` uses `exec.Command(\"tmux\", ...)` which relies on PATH lookup:\n```go\ncmd := exec.Command(\"tmux\", \"display-message\", \"-t\", sessionName, \"-p\", \"#{pane_current_path}\")\n```\n\n## Proposed Fix\n\n1. **Find tmux at startup** - Check common locations in order:\n   - `/opt/homebrew/bin/tmux` (macOS ARM)\n   - `/usr/local/bin/tmux` (macOS Intel, Linux)\n   - `/usr/bin/tmux` (Linux system)\n   - Fall back to PATH lookup\n\n2. **Cache the found path** - Store in package-level var, reuse for all calls\n\n3. **Graceful degradation** - If tmux not found:\n   - Return structured error with `following_available: false`\n   - Dashboard can hide/disable Following toggle\n   - Don't spam logs\n\n## Files to Change\n\n- `pkg/tmux/follower.go` - Add tmux path resolution\n- `pkg/tmux/tmux.go` - Share resolution across all tmux calls\n- `cmd/orch/serve_context.go` - Return `following_available: false` on error","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-01-07T15:01:23.835923-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-07T15:13:15.580143-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-07T15:13:15.580143-08:00","close_reason":"Fixed in 7a883d3b - findTmux() now checks common locations before PATH"}
{"id":"orch-go-74o00","title":"Add tool experience prompts to orchestrator/investigation skills","description":"When selecting tools or approaches, prompt Dylan: 'Have you used [tool] before? What's your experience with [approach]?' System doesn't know Dylan's tool history (foreman, Docker, etc.) and should ask instead of assuming.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-09T16:13:25.39281-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-10T15:17:16.243325-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-10T15:17:16.243325-08:00","close_reason":"Tool experience prompts added to orchestrator (line 617) and investigation (line 56) skills. Changes committed to orch-knowledge repo (43c899a). SYNTHESIS.md created. Addresses trust calibration meta-pattern."}
