{"id":"orch-go-78gk","title":"kb reflect should auto-create synthesis issues at threshold","description":"When kb reflect detects 10+ investigations on a topic, auto-create a beads issue:\n- Title: 'Synthesize {topic} investigations ({count})'\n- Label: triage:review (orchestrator decides priority)\n- Link to relevant investigations\n- Description includes kb chronicle output snippet\n\nThis connects reflection output to the work pipeline without requiring manual initiative. Preserves orchestrator judgment (they prioritize) while creating pressure (issue exists, visible, doesn't disappear).\n\nImplements: Gate Over Remind principle\nImplements: Pressure Over Compensation principle\n\nRelated: kb-reflect skill exists for the actual synthesis work.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2025-12-31T17:41:47.977107-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-03T14:24:27.811191-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-03T14:24:27.811191-08:00","close_reason":"Already completed: Fixed kb reflect --create-issue PATH resolution. Added beads.go helper in kb-cli that finds bd binar"}
{"id":"orch-go-78jw","title":"Daemon should show rejection reasons in preview","description":"## Problem\n\nWhen issues have `triage:ready` label but daemon reports 'no spawnable', there's no feedback explaining WHY:\n- Missing type?\n- Wrong status?\n- Capacity limit?\n- Cooldown period?\n\n## Evidence (session ses_474f)\n\nOrchestrator spent ~15 turns debugging why daemon wouldn't spawn labeled issues. The actual cause (null type in JSON) was invisible. Eventually daemon DID spawn - the debugging was unnecessary because the orchestrator couldn't see what was happening.\n\n## Solution\n\n`orch daemon preview` should show rejection reasons per issue, not just 'no spawnable'.\n\nExample output:\n```\nSpawnable issues:\n  orch-go-abc1: feature-impl (type: feature)\n\nRejected issues:\n  orch-go-xyz2: missing type (required for skill inference)\n  orch-go-xyz3: status is in_progress (must be open)\n  orch-go-xyz4: cooldown (spawned 2min ago, min 5min)\n```\n\n## Principle\n\n**Gate Over Remind** - daemon silently accepted malformed issues, then silently rejected them. Should fail loudly.\n**Surfacing Over Browsing** - orchestrator shouldn't need to debug internal state; system should surface why.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-01-04T14:25:09.062199-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-04T14:46:12.865413-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-04T14:46:12.865413-08:00","close_reason":"Daemon preview now shows per-issue rejection reasons (missing type, wrong status, missing label, blocked). Tests: go test ./pkg/daemon/... -run 'TestDaemon_Preview_Shows' - 2 passed. Smoke test: orch daemon preview shows rejection reasons as expected."}
