{"id":"orch-go-7azwt","title":"Evaluate dashboard cache TTLs (30s/15s) against polling patterns","description":"## Question\nAre the current TTLs optimal for dashboard polling?\n- /api/beads (stats): 30s TTL\n- /api/beads/ready: 15s TTL\n\n## Context\nTTLs were chosen somewhat arbitrarily during the performance fix. Dashboard polls endpoints but we don't know at what interval.\n\n## To Investigate\n1. What is the dashboard's actual polling interval?\n2. If polling every 5s but TTL is 30s, user sees stale data for 25s\n3. If polling every 30s but TTL is 15s, we're doing 2x the work needed\n\n## Ideal State\nTTL should be slightly longer than polling interval:\n- polling: 5s → TTL: 10s\n- polling: 10s → TTL: 15s\n\n## Reference\n- .kb/investigations/2026-01-07-inv-api-beads-endpoint-takes-5s.md\n- web/src/routes/ (check SSE or polling logic)","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-07T11:02:12.806785-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-09T18:14:52.449977-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-09T18:14:52.449977-08:00","close_reason":"Evaluated dashboard cache TTLs (30s/15s) and found them appropriately configured for high-frequency access patterns (SSE + context following). No changes needed. Investigation and synthesis committed."}
