{"id":"orch-go-7ejo","title":"Fix launchd plist PATH to include homebrew and npm paths","description":"orch servers init generates plists with incomplete PATH. Servers fail to start because go/npm not found.\n\nCurrent PATH in plist:\n/Users/dylanconlin/bin:/Users/dylanconlin/.local/bin:/usr/local/bin:/usr/bin:/bin\n\nMissing:\n- /opt/homebrew/bin (go)\n- ~/.npm-global/bin (npm)\n\nFix: Detect actual binary paths during plist generation, or inherit from current shell PATH.\n\nRelated: cmd/orch/servers.go, pkg/servers/detect.go","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2025-12-28T09:09:50.481799-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-28T09:22:53.423856-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-28T09:22:53.423856-08:00","close_reason":"Fixed launchd plist PATH inheritance. DefaultPlistOptions() now uses os.Getenv(\"PATH\") instead of hardcoded path, ensuring npm/go are found at /opt/homebrew/bin and ~/.asdf/shims. All tests passing."}
