{"id":"orch-go-7hzx","title":"UI viewport mismatch: Playwright dimensions should match user's actual viewport","description":"Agent renders at different dimensions than user views, causing literal visual drift. Screenshots show different layouts. Fix: configure Playwright viewport in spawn context to match user's working dimensions.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-12-26T08:16:24.362321-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-27T14:16:14.370363-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-27T14:16:14.370363-08:00","close_reason":"Added Playwright MCP server to opencode.jsonc with --viewport-size=1440x900 to match user display dimensions. Committed as df36ee8 in dotfiles repo.","labels":["skill:feature-impl","triage:ready","triage:review"]}
{"id":"orch-go-7iibr","title":"Update meta-orchestrator skill: orchestrators require SOTA reasoning model","description":"Meta-orchestrator skill should document that orchestrator spawns require SOTA reasoning models (Opus 4.5, Gemini 3 Flash Preview, GPT 5.2, etc.), not Sonnet. Current skill doesn't specify model requirements for orchestrator spawns. Add to spawn guidance section.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-18T12:10:14.060138-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-18T12:10:14.060138-08:00","labels":["skill"]}
{"id":"orch-go-7iis","title":"orch serve CPU runaway - deeper fix needed","description":"Previous fix (ed772bac - removing IsProcessing HTTP calls, 500ms debounce) didn't hold. CPU hit 124% again after ~15 min. Need deeper investigation: goroutine leaks, unbounded SSE client connections, missing cleanup on disconnect, or other feedback loops. Consider pprof profiling. Blocking dashboard usability.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-12-25T22:25:59.399089-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-25T22:51:02.694898-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-25T22:51:02.694898-08:00","close_reason":"Fixed CPU runaway: implemented workspace cache reducing O(n*m) file ops to O(m)+O(n). 5-minute stress test shows CPU at 4-7% (down from 124%). Added pprof at /debug/pprof/ for diagnostics. Investigation and SYNTHESIS.md committed.","labels":["P1","skill:systematic-debugging","triage:ready"]}
