{"id":"orch-go-7lvi2","title":"Bug: git_diff gate parses event type names as file paths","description":"Parser in pkg/verify/git_diff.go is too naive. Needs heuristics:\n- Must contain / or start with .\n- Must have file extension  \n- Exclude known non-file patterns\n\nRoot cause: Any word in SYNTHESIS.md that looks vaguely like a path gets flagged.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-01-08T11:21:41.348824-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-08T11:52:27.991597-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-08T11:52:27.991597-08:00","close_reason":"Phase: Complete - Fixed git_diff gate parser by validating against known file extensions. Event type names (session.created, agent.spawned) and version numbers (v0.33.2) are no longer incorrectly matched as file paths.","labels":["triage:ready"]}
