{"id":"orch-go-7nmw","title":"Dashboard: Pulsing gold border persists on completed agents in Recent section","description":"Agent cards that were previously 'processing' retain the pulsing gold border animation even after moving to the Recent section with 'completed' status. \n\nExample: orch-go-erdw.1 shows 'completed' + 'Complete' badges but still has the gold pulsing border.\n\nThe border style should be cleared when agent status changes from active/processing to completed.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-12-25T20:48:32.409926-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-26T09:29:27.757838-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-26T09:29:27.757838-08:00","close_reason":"Fixed pulsing gold border persistence by adding status === 'active' check to SSE event handlers. Late SSE events were incorrectly setting is_processing=true on completed agents.","labels":["skill:systematic-debugging","triage:ready"]}
{"id":"orch-go-7ocqx","title":"Implement mode-aware status command","description":"Update 'orch status' to query tmux windows (claude mode) or HTTP API (opencode mode). Unified output format regardless of backend.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-09T11:55:44.960588-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-09T12:54:26.855726-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-09T12:54:26.855726-08:00","close_reason":"Implemented mode-aware status command - reads agent mode from registry and routes to tmux or HTTP API accordingly. Status output now shows mode column."}
