{"id":"orch-go-7qkh","title":"orch complete fails with EOF when agent still running in non-interactive context","description":"When completing an agent that's still running, 'Proceed anyway? [y/N]' prompt fails with 'failed to read response: EOF' in non-interactive contexts. Had to use --force. Fix: detect non-interactive stdin and either auto-decline or require --force flag explicitly.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-12-25T21:39:58.949083-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-26T14:21:21.419357-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-26T14:21:21.419357-08:00","close_reason":"Fixed orch complete EOF error by detecting non-interactive stdin using term.IsTerminal(). Liveness check now returns clear error with --force suggestion; follow-up prompts are skipped with a note.","labels":["skill:systematic-debugging","triage:ready"]}
