{"id":"orch-go-7rgz","title":"Add periodic kb reflect to daemon","description":"Daemon should run kb reflect --type synthesis --create-issue periodically (hourly?) to auto-surface synthesis opportunities.\n\nThis closes the automation loop:\n- Daemon runs kb reflect\n- kb reflect creates triage:review issues for 10+ investigation topics\n- Orchestrator sees issues in bd ready\n- Orchestrator (or daemon) spawns kb-reflect agent\n- Agent produces decisions/archives\n\nImplementation options:\n1. Add to daemon poll loop with cycle counter (every 60 cycles = hourly)\n2. Separate goroutine with ticker\n3. New daemon subcommand: orch daemon reflect\n\nShould probably be configurable (enable/disable, frequency) in ~/.orch/config.yaml","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2025-12-31T18:13:50.813839-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-06T11:00:40.253617-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-06T11:00:40.253617-08:00","close_reason":"Added periodic kb reflect to daemon with configurable interval (--reflect-interval, default 60m) and issue creation (--reflect-issues, default true). Runs kb reflect --type synthesis --create-issue when interval elapses. Config also available in ~/.orch/config.yaml under reflect section. All 28 new tests pass.","labels":["skill:feature-impl"]}
