{"id":"orch-go-7w1dv","title":"Expose decidability fields in beads CLI","description":"Beads schema has ResolutionType, Domain, Authority fields that aren't exposed via CLI.\n\n## Required Changes\n\n1. **bd create** - Add `--resolution-type` (factual/judgment/framing) and `--domain` flags\n2. **bd dep add** - Add `--authority` flag (daemon/orchestrator/human)\n3. **bd ready** - Add `--authority` filter for daemon-safe frontier queries\n\n## Context\n\nPer decision 2026-01-22-accountability-architecture-beads-first.md, the accountability architecture implementation is beads-first - expose existing schema rather than build new infrastructure.\n\n## Open Questions\n\n- Should `bd ready` default to `--authority daemon` for safety?\n- Backfill strategy for existing issues without resolution_type?\n- Does `answered` status need wiring to unblock dependencies?\n\n## References\n\n- Reconciliation: .kb/investigations/2026-01-22-inv-reconcile-architect-accountability-architecture-proposal.md\n- Decision: .kb/decisions/2026-01-22-accountability-architecture-beads-first.md","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-01-22T15:19:40.899543-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-22T17:54:46.927782-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-22T17:54:46.927782-08:00","close_reason":"Phase: Complete - Exposed decidability fields in beads CLI. Added --resolution-type and --domain to bd create, --authority filter to bd ready. Changes in beads repo (commit 30b3d443), investigation in orch-go repo (commit 776c9cab). Build/test needed (no Go in sandbox).","labels":["triage:ready"]}
{"id":"orch-go-7wvhx","title":"[orch-go] feature-impl: Backend sends last activity in /api/agents resp...","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-08T06:26:29.002821-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-08T06:39:34.056245-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-08T06:39:34.056245-08:00","close_reason":"Added current_activity and last_activity_at fields to /api/agents response. Backend now extracts activity from OpenCode session messages for active agents. Build and tests pass."}
{"id":"orch-go-7ww9r","title":"Propagate self-healing binary pattern to other CLIs","description":"Copy the autorebuild.go pattern from orch-go to: kb-cli, beads, skillc, glass, agentlog. Each CLI needs:\n\n1. Copy cmd/orch/autorebuild.go (adapt package name)\n2. Add ldflags to Makefile: -X main.sourceDir=$(SOURCE_DIR) -X main.gitHash=$(GIT_HASH)\n3. Call maybeAutoRebuild() at top of main()\n4. Add ORCH_NO_AUTOREBUILD check (or CLI-specific env var)\n\nPattern reference: orch-go/cmd/orch/autorebuild.go\n\nThis eliminates stale binary bugs across the ecosystem - binaries auto-detect staleness and rebuild themselves.\n\nSee: .kb/principles.md (Self-Describing Artifacts example), ~/.orch/ECOSYSTEM.md (CLI Binaries section)","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-08T17:39:13.055823-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-08T20:09:35.493718-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-08T20:09:35.493718-08:00","close_reason":"Propagated self-healing binary pattern to 5 CLIs (kb-cli, beads, skillc, glass, agentlog). Each CLI now auto-detects staleness and rebuilds itself. All verified working."}
