{"id":"orch-go-7xmdc","title":"Synthesize opencode investigations (18)","description":"## Synthesis Needed\n\nTopic **opencode** has accumulated 18 investigations that may benefit from consolidation.\n\n### Investigations to synthesize:\n\n- 2025-12-19-inv-client-opencode-session-management.md\n- 2025-12-19-simple-opencode-poc-spawn-session-via.md\n- 2025-12-20-design-explore-tradeoffs-orch-opencode-integration.md\n- 2025-12-20-inv-refactor-orch-tail-use-opencode.md\n- 2025-12-20-research-opencode-native-context-loading.md\n- 2025-12-21-inv-implement-verify-opencode-disk-session.md\n- 2025-12-23-debug-opencode-api-redirect-loop.md\n- 2025-12-23-inv-oc-command-opencode-dev-wrapper.md\n- 2025-12-24-inv-addendum-ecosystem-audit-opencode.md\n- 2025-12-24-inv-fix-orch-clean-verify-opencode.md\n- 2025-12-25-inv-opencode-crashes-no-user-message.md\n- 2025-12-26-inv-can-we-auto-refresh-opencode.md\n- 2025-12-26-inv-investigate-opencode-session-accumulation-causing.md\n- 2025-12-26-inv-opencode-health-endpoint-returns-redirected.md\n- 2025-12-26-inv-opencode-theme-selection-system.md\n- 2025-12-26-inv-port-full-opencode-theme-system.md\n- 2026-01-06-inv-cannot-query-opencode-sessions-other.md\n- 2026-01-06-inv-implement-opencode-session-cleanup-mechanism.md\n\n### Chronicle Timeline\n\n```\n2025-12-19 [INV] CLI orch spawn Command Implementation\n2025-12-19 [INV] CLI Orch Status Command\n2025-12-19 [INV] CLI Project Scaffolding and Build Setup\n2025-12-19 [INV] OpenCode Client Package Session Management\n2025-12-19 [INV] SSE Event Monitoring Client\n... (run kb chronicle for full timeline)\n```\n\n### Suggested Action\n\n1. Run `kb chronicle \"opencode\"` to understand evolution\n2. Identify patterns and contradictions across investigations\n3. Create a synthesized decision or consolidated investigation\n","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-07T14:43:42.561168-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-07T15:32:44.888927-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-07T15:32:44.888927-08:00","close_reason":"Synthesis is orchestrator work per decision 2026-01-07. Opportunities now surfaced via orch status.","labels":["triage:review"]}
{"id":"orch-go-7xqbg","title":"Diagnose January abandonment spike","description":"A recent synthesis (orch-go-4tven.4) revealed that January abandonment rates spiked 4.8x (4.4% → 21.0%).","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-01-17T12:28:53.158234-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-17T12:37:39.14719-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-17T12:37:39.14719-08:00","close_reason":"Phase: Complete - Root cause identified: Infrastructure instability (245 service crashes Jan vs 0 Dec) from overmind crash loop. Recovery verified: 7.4% post-Jan-14 rate (down from 21.0%). Tests: jq analysis on events.jsonl - 245 crashes counted, 14/189 post-Jan-14 abandonments verified.","labels":["triage:ready"]}
{"id":"orch-go-7yrh","title":"Epic: Harden bd CLI integration against load-related failures","description":"After dashboard feature increased bd CLI usage 10x, we hit multiple bugs: daemon race condition, unbounded concurrency, CLI flag misuse. This epic covers merging existing fixes and adding structural improvements to prevent recurrence.\n\n## Context\n- Dashboard polls every 2-5 seconds, batches 10-50+ agents\n- 19 exec.Command bd calls throughout codebase\n- Beads daemon fix on branch, not merged to main\n\n## Success Criteria\n- Daemon fix merged to beads main\n- All batch bd operations have concurrency limits\n- Load testing validates 50+ agent scenarios\n- No CPU spikes under normal dashboard usage","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"epic","created_at":"2025-12-25T07:18:48.700326-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-26T13:46:18.968001-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-26T13:46:18.968001-08:00","close_reason":"All 8 children complete - beads RPC client implemented, load testing done, concurrency audited"}
{"id":"orch-go-7yrh.10","title":"Design: Go client for beads vs shell exec","description":"Currently shell out to bd CLI 19 times. This is fragile - no type safety, CLI flag surprises, process overhead, hard to mock.\n\n## Options to evaluate\n1. Keep shelling out + defensive wrappers\n2. Import beads as Go module\n3. beads HTTP API\n4. Shared SQLite access\n\n## Deliverable\nRecommendation with tradeoffs","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-12-25T07:19:41.311074-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-25T22:14:42.657408-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-25T22:14:42.657408-08:00","close_reason":"Batch close from orch review"}
{"id":"orch-go-7yrh.11","title":"Implement pkg/beads Go RPC client","description":"Create pkg/beads/client.go with connection management to beads daemon socket.\n\n## Context\nReplacing bd CLI subprocess calls with native RPC to eliminate process overhead, get type safety, and avoid CLI quirks.\n\n## Implementation\n- Pattern after beads internal/rpc/client.go\n- Connect to .beads/bd.sock Unix domain socket\n- Include health checks, reconnect logic\n- Types from beads/internal/rpc/protocol.go\n- Support 7 operations: ready, show, list, stats, comments, close, create\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- Client can connect to beads daemon\n- All 7 operations work\n- Fallback behavior when daemon unavailable\n- Unit tests with mock socket","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-12-25T07:43:41.363239-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-25T07:53:14.697382-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-25T07:53:14.697382-08:00","close_reason":"Implemented pkg/beads Go RPC client with 7 operations (ready, show, list, stats, comments, close, create), Unix socket connection to .beads/bd.sock, health check on connect, reconnect logic, and CLI fallback functions. All 14 tests pass, full test suite passes. Committed as 9657cd9."}
{"id":"orch-go-7yrh.12","title":"Migrate daemon.ListReadyIssues to beads RPC","description":"Replace pkg/daemon/daemon.go:ListReadyIssues() subprocess call with pkg/beads client.\n\n## Context  \nThis is the highest-frequency bd call - daemon polls every few seconds.\n\n## Implementation\n- Use OpReady operation from new pkg/beads client\n- Fallback to CLI if daemon unavailable\n- Update error handling\n\n## Dependencies\n- Requires orch-go-7yrh.11 (pkg/beads client)","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-12-25T07:43:49.035322-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-25T10:15:47.953658-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-25T10:15:47.953658-08:00","close_reason":"Completed in 71d6f4f - daemon.ListReadyIssues uses beads RPC"}
{"id":"orch-go-7yrh.13","title":"Migrate verify.GetComments to beads RPC","description":"Replace pkg/verify/check.go:GetComments() and GetCommentsBatch() with pkg/beads client.\n\n## Context\nGetCommentsBatch is the only concurrent bd caller - currently uses semaphore. RPC will be cleaner.\n\n## Implementation\n- Use OpCommentList operation\n- Remove semaphore (RPC handles serialization)\n- Update GetIssue to use OpShow\n\n## Dependencies\n- Requires orch-go-7yrh.11 (pkg/beads client)","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-12-25T07:43:52.729377-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-25T07:59:06.041674-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-25T07:59:06.041674-08:00","close_reason":"Migrated verify.GetComments and GetCommentsBatch to use beads RPC client with CLI fallback. Type alias maintains backward compatibility. Removed semaphore pattern."}
{"id":"orch-go-7yrh.14","title":"Migrate serve.go beads calls to RPC","description":"Replace cmd/orch/serve.go handleBeadsStats() subprocess call with pkg/beads client.\n\n## Context\nDashboard polls beads stats every few seconds.\n\n## Implementation\n- Use OpStats operation\n- Update BeadsAPIResponse to match RPC types\n\n## Dependencies\n- Requires orch-go-7yrh.11 (pkg/beads client)","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-12-25T07:43:55.447008-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-25T10:15:46.272869-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-25T10:15:46.272869-08:00","close_reason":"Completed in f72dc16 - all serve.go beads calls migrated to RPC"}
{"id":"orch-go-7yrh.5","title":"Merge beads daemon race condition fix to main","description":"CRITICAL: The daemon race fix (commit aa401428) is on fix-repo-empty-config branch, 15 commits ahead of main. If anyone rebuilds bd from main, CPU spike bug returns.\n\n## What to do\n1. cd ~/Documents/personal/beads\n2. git checkout main\n3. git merge fix-repo-empty-config (or cherry-pick aa401428)\n4. Rebuild and install bd\n\n## The fix\nkillDuplicateDaemons() sanity check after acquiring flock - prevents process accumulation.\n\n## Risk if not done\nHigh - next bd rebuild from main reintroduces CPU overload bug.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-12-25T07:19:22.221185-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-25T07:21:25.584028-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-25T07:21:25.584028-08:00","close_reason":"Merged fix-repo-empty-config to main (15 commits including aa401428 daemon race fix). Fixed minor build issue (SourceRepo field) and rebuilt bd v0.33.2.","labels":["P0"]}
{"id":"orch-go-7yrh.7","title":"Add load test for dashboard with 50+ agents","description":"Bugs emerged because production load \u003e\u003e dev testing. Need load test to catch concurrency issues.\n\n## Test scenario\n- 50+ beads issues in various states\n- Dashboard polling at normal rate (2-5s)\n- Monitor: CPU usage, bd process count, response times\n\n## Success criteria\n- No CPU spikes, bd process count \u003c 15, API response \u003c 500ms","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-12-25T07:19:27.190229-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-26T09:21:52.47571-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-26T09:21:52.47571-08:00","close_reason":"Added 13 comprehensive Playwright load tests for dashboard with 50+ agents. Tests use HTTP API mocking to simulate large agent counts and verify: rendering without errors, filter responsiveness (\u003c2s for 50 agents), scroll performance (\u003c500ms), API response time (\u003c500ms), and stress handling with 100 agents. Commit: 12da8eb2","labels":["skill:feature-impl","triage:ready"]}
{"id":"orch-go-7yrh.9","title":"Audit all bd exec calls for concurrency safety","description":"19 exec.Command bd calls exist in codebase. Most are single calls, but some may batch or be called in loops.\n\n## Scope\n- List all bd exec sites\n- Identify which can be called concurrently or in rapid succession\n- Flag any missing concurrency controls\n- Check for -s flag misuse patterns\n\n## Files to check\n- cmd/orch/serve.go, handoff.go, swarm.go\n- pkg/verify/check.go, pkg/daemon/daemon.go\n\n## Deliverable\nList of sites needing protection + recommended fixes","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-12-25T07:19:39.083628-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-25T22:14:46.87768-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-25T22:14:46.87768-08:00","close_reason":"Batch close from orch review"}
