{"id":"orch-go-82r4","title":"Auto-generate kn tried entries from severe patterns","description":"When orch patterns detects a critical-severity pattern (e.g., 10+ futile actions), optionally auto-create a 'kn tried' entry to persist the learning. This closes the loop: action-log detects pattern → kn tried externalizes it → future agents see it in kb context. Could be triggered by: 1) orch patterns --learn flag, 2) daemon periodic check, or 3) session end hook. Use existing SuggestKnEntry() in pkg/action.","status":"closed","priority":3,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2025-12-29T17:23:48.437676-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-14T14:13:40.117986-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-14T14:13:40.117986-08:00","close_reason":"Stale 15+ days, deprioritized"}
