{"id":"orch-go-87rn","title":"Spawn context should include related prior investigations","description":"Spawn context generation should surface 2-3 most recent investigations matching task topic. Currently agents have no visibility into prior work on same topic, leading to disconnected knowledge graph (0 lineage references across 500 investigations). Discovered in orch-go-s03z.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2025-12-28T15:02:54.279234-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-28T15:16:07.029909-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-28T15:16:07.029909-08:00","close_reason":"Spawn context now includes D.E.K.N. Delta (key finding) for up to 3 most recent related investigations. Tests pass, committed.","labels":["triage:ready"]}
{"id":"orch-go-881b","title":"bd show --json returns array, breaks orch-go parsing","description":"bd show --json now returns an array [{...}] but orch-go expects a single object {...}. This broke daemon spawning from 20:15-20:39 with error: 'json: cannot unmarshal array into Go value of type beads.Issue'. Fix: update pkg/beads/client.go to handle array response, extract first element.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2025-12-26T21:54:32.3409-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-26T22:16:47.595248-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-26T22:16:47.595248-08:00","close_reason":"Fixed Client.Show() to handle both array and single object JSON formats from bd show. Root cause: CLI returns arrays, but RPC client expected single object. Added test and committed fix.","labels":["skill:systematic-debugging","triage:ready"]}
