{"id":"orch-go-89y0","title":"kb reflect semantic clustering - replace keyword grouping with topic clustering","description":"Currently kb reflect --type synthesis groups by keyword (e.g., 'add' = 41 unrelated investigations). Should cluster by semantic topic (dashboard, headless, daemon) to surface actually related investigations. Discovered in orch-go-s03z knowledge fragmentation investigation.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2025-12-28T15:02:52.125479-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-28T15:15:35.642416-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-28T15:15:35.642416-08:00","close_reason":"Implemented semantic topic clustering in kb reflect. Investigations now cluster by domain (dashboard/daemon/spawn) instead of action verbs (add/fix/implement). Changes committed to kb-cli. All tests pass.","labels":["triage:ready"]}
{"id":"orch-go-8a03c","title":"Session registry doesn't update when orchestrator workspaces are archived","description":"## Problem\n\n`~/.orch/sessions.json` tracks orchestrator sessions with status field, but nothing updates the status when:\n1. Workspace is moved to workspace-archive/\n2. SESSION_HANDOFF.md is written (session complete)\n3. Session is abandoned\n\nResult: `orch status` shows stale 'active' sessions that are actually completed/archived.\n\n## Evidence\n\nFound 5 sessions in registry all marked 'active', but 3 were:\n- Already archived (workspace in workspace-archive/)\n- Had SESSION_HANDOFF.md (completed)\n- No longer relevant\n\nHad to manually edit sessions.json to fix:\n```bash\njq '.sessions |= map(if .workspace_name == \"...\" then .status = \"completed\" else . end)'\n```\n\n## Expected Behavior\n\nSession status should be updated when:\n1. `orch complete` archives a workspace → status = 'completed'\n2. SESSION_HANDOFF.md is detected → status = 'completed'\n3. `orch abandon` is run → status = 'abandoned'\n\n## Related\n\nThis is the registry population issue mentioned in .kb/investigations/2026-01-06-inv-workspace-session-architecture.md (Gap #4)","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-01-06T14:54:53.638958-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-06T15:30:54.648172-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-06T15:30:54.648172-08:00","close_reason":"Fixed session registry not updating on complete/abandon. Changed complete_cmd.go to use Update() instead of Unregister(). Added registry Update() to abandon_cmd.go (was completely missing). Tests: go test ./pkg/session/... - 23 passed, 0 failed","labels":["triage:ready"]}
{"id":"orch-go-8b09d","title":"orch status shows 'idle' for actively running agents","description":"## Problem\n`orch status` shows agents as 'idle' when they are actively running (visible activity in tmux pane).\n\n## Evidence\nThree agents shown as 'idle' in `orch status --all`:\n- ok-k16g: Actually running - 'Exploring all content areas...' visible in tmux\n- ok-od0l: Actually crashed - 'Killed' in tmux output  \n- pw-ww8p: Actually running - 'Billowing...' visible, running render-api\n\n## Impact\n- Misleading status makes it hard to know actual swarm state\n- Can't distinguish running from crashed from truly idle\n- Daemon capacity may be affected by wrong status\n\n## Likely cause\nStatus detection logic (idle vs running) not checking:\n1. Tmux pane activity timestamp\n2. Process state in container\n3. Claude CLI status indicators\n\n## Related\n- orch-go-xfue0 (daemon capacity tracking)","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-01-22T09:48:54.460964-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-22T10:29:09.610066-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-22T10:29:09.610066-08:00","close_reason":"Phase: Complete - Fixed idle status for tmux-based agents by adding tmux pane activity detection. Commit: 6fa627c5. Build verification needed on host (Go not available in sandbox).","labels":["triage:ready"]}
{"id":"orch-go-8b5e","title":"orch review reports SYNTHESIS.md missing when it exists","description":"Observed: orch review orch-go-4kwt.8 reported 'SYNTHESIS.md (missing)' but file exists at .orch/workspace/og-inv-reflection-checkpoint-pattern-21dec/SYNTHESIS.md (4141 bytes). Likely path resolution issue - review command may be looking in wrong location or using wrong workspace name mapping.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-12-21T16:57:28.191603-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-25T22:14:45.361878-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-25T22:14:45.361878-08:00","close_reason":"Batch close from orch review"}
{"id":"orch-go-8c36q","title":"Synthesize status investigations (12)","description":"## Synthesis Needed\n\nTopic **status** has accumulated 12 investigations that may benefit from consolidation.\n\n### Investigations to synthesize:\n\n- 2025-12-20-inv-enhance-status-command-swarm-progress.md\n- 2025-12-21-inv-investigate-orch-status-showing-stale.md\n- 2025-12-21-inv-orch-status-showing-stale-sessions.md\n- 2025-12-22-debug-orch-status-stale-sessions.md\n- 2025-12-22-inv-update-orch-status-use-islive.md\n- 2025-12-23-inv-orch-status-can-detect-active.md\n- 2025-12-23-inv-orch-status-shows-active-agents.md\n- 2025-12-23-inv-orch-status-takes-11-seconds.md\n- 2025-12-24-inv-fix-status-filter-test-expects.md\n- 2026-01-05-debug-fix-orch-status-showing-different.md\n- 2026-01-06-inv-orch-status-shows-completed-agents.md\n- 2026-01-07-inv-orch-status-surface-drift-metrics.md\n\n### Chronicle Timeline\n\n```\n2025-12-19 [INV] CLI orch complete Command Implementation\n2025-12-19 [INV] CLI orch spawn Command Implementation\n2025-12-19 [INV] CLI Orch Status Command\n2025-12-19 [INV] CLI Project Scaffolding and Build Setup\n2025-12-19 [INV] OpenCode Client Package Session Management\n... (run kb chronicle for full timeline)\n```\n\n### Suggested Action\n\n1. Run `kb chronicle \"status\"` to understand evolution\n2. Identify patterns and contradictions across investigations\n3. Create a synthesized decision or consolidated investigation\n","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-07T21:38:50.666683-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-07T22:46:46.441782-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-07T22:46:46.441782-08:00","close_reason":"Bulk close: kb reflect synthesis issues are noise until detection is fixed","labels":["triage:review"]}
{"id":"orch-go-8d3dw","title":"Cross-project daemon: poll multiple beads directories","description":"## Problem\n\nThe orch daemon only polls the working directory's beads database. Orchestrators in other projects (e.g., price-watch) can create `triage:ready` issues, but the daemon never sees them.\n\nCurrent architecture:\n- Daemon runs from orch-go with `WorkingDirectory=/Users/dylanconlin/Documents/personal/orch-go`\n- `bd ready` only returns issues from `.beads/` in current directory\n- Containerized orchestrators in other projects have no spawn path\n\n## Desired Behavior\n\nDaemon polls ALL registered projects for `triage:ready` issues and spawns agents in the correct project context.\n\n## Prior Art / Context\n\n- Daemon guide mentioned `--cross-project` flag but it was never implemented\n- kb has project registration (`kb project list`) - could reuse this registry\n- Beads has `bd repo` commands but they're buggy (see kb constraints)\n\n## Design Questions for Architect\n\n1. **Project registry** - Where should the list of projects live?\n   - Reuse kb's project registry?\n   - New `~/.orch/projects.yaml`?\n   - Scan for `.beads/` directories under known roots?\n\n2. **Polling strategy** - How to poll multiple projects?\n   - Sequential: poll each project in turn\n   - Parallel: goroutines per project\n   - Unified: aggregate all issues then filter\n\n3. **Spawn context** - How to spawn in correct project?\n   - Change working directory before spawn?\n   - Pass `--project` flag to orch work?\n   - Use `bd --db` flag to specify database?\n\n4. **Capacity management** - Per-project or global?\n   - Global pool (current): 3 agents total across all projects\n   - Per-project pools: 3 agents per project\n   - Weighted: priority projects get more slots\n\n## Constraints\n\n- Must work with containerized orchestrators (Docker spawn path)\n- Must respect per-project .orch/config.yaml settings\n- Should not require running multiple daemon processes\n\n## Deliverables\n\n- Architecture decision document\n- If straightforward: implementation plan with steps\n- If complex: break into sub-issues","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-01-21T20:20:24.476657338Z","updated_at":"2026-01-21T12:23:49.654798-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-21T12:23:49.654798-08:00","close_reason":"Phase: Complete - Architecture decision documented: Use kb projects list for registry, sequential iteration over projects, global capacity pool shared across projects, --cross-project flag for opt-in activation. Implementation is additive (no breaking changes). Investigation file committed.","labels":["architect"]}
{"id":"orch-go-8dgt","title":"Update orchestrator skill: daemon-first as default workflow for batch work","description":"Current skill implies manual spawning. Update to reflect daemon-first pattern: 1) Label issues triage:ready + skill:X, 2) Daemon auto-spawns, 3) Orchestrator focuses on triage/labeling/synthesis/review. Manual orch spawn only for single urgent items.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-12-25T14:11:39.653228-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-25T15:05:45.529304-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-25T15:05:45.529304-08:00","close_reason":"Completed in orch-knowledge commit 4c9403c","labels":["parent:orch-go-b9mm","skill:feature-impl"]}
{"id":"orch-go-8dhhg","title":"CI: Deduplicate beads guidance across injection sources","description":"Remove redundant beads guidance from bd prime hook when running in spawned contexts.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-01-17T11:25:53.651116-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-17T12:16:31.29234-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-17T12:16:31.29234-08:00","close_reason":"Phase: Complete - Fixed bd prime duplication in spawned contexts. Added isSpawnedContext() detection, verified with manual and unit tests. Beads repo commit: 12031e17","labels":["triage:ready"]}
{"id":"orch-go-8e4uk","title":"Implement Phase: Complete check before spawn","description":"Pre-spawn Phase: Complete check is documented but NOT implemented in code. Allows respawning completed work, wasting agent capacity.\n\n**Fix:** Add check in spawn flow: if beads issue has Phase: Complete comment, skip spawn.\n\n**Reference:** .kb/investigations/2026-01-22-inv-strategic-audit-daemon-reliability-multiple.md","repro":"Spawn an issue, let agent complete with Phase: Complete comment. bd close the issue. Try to spawn same issue again - it will respawn instead of being skipped.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-01-23T16:35:40.230203-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-23T16:48:06.425923-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-23T16:48:06.425923-08:00","close_reason":"Fixed: Phase check was nested incorrectly, now runs unconditionally"}
