son":"Bulk close - synthesis tasks are orchestrator work, not spawnable","labels":["triage:review"]}
{"id":"orch-go-8hdpi","title":"Add model impact reflection to orchestrator handoff template","description":"## Problem\n\nOrchestrators complete work that changes system architecture, but handoffs don't prompt for model updates. Today we closed the entire Verification System Overhaul epic (5 issues) but `completion-verification.md` model wasn't updated.\n\n## Context\n\n- Discussed whether model staleness is a problem → yes, for architectural changes\n- Decided: models track architecture, not implementation\n- Orchestrators are best positioned to notice architectural changes (they review what shipped)\n- But current handoff template doesn't prompt for this\n\n## Solution\n\nAdd to `SESSION_HANDOFF.template.md` under Knowledge section:\n\n```markdown\n### Model Impact\n- Did any work this session change system architecture? (not just implementation)\n- If yes, which models in `.kb/models/` need updating?\n- If unsure, check: would an agent reading the model tomorrow be misled?\n```\n\n## Why not decision-navigation dependency?\n\n- Orchestrator skill already at 139.6% token budget\n- This is targeted at the specific gap\n- Handoff template is actively used (right location)\n- Follows 'reduce before adding'\n\n## Provenance\n\nMeta-orchestrator session 2026-01-14, discussion with Dylan after reviewing that 3 orchestrator sessions shipped verification work without noting model impact.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-14T22:20:46.254726-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-15T07:30:23.938697-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-15T07:30:23.938697-08:00","close_reason":"Added Model Impact section to SESSION_HANDOFF.template.md (lines 100-103) with three prompts for orchestrators to consider model staleness after architectural work. Committed as 7d18e47f.","labels":["triage:ready"]}
{"id":"orch-go-8hxsr","title":"[orch-go] investigation: Verify worker metrics: perform 10 tool calls (e...","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-17T10:50:34.566947-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-17T10:59:29.540251-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-17T10:59:29.540251-08:00","close_reason":"Phase: Complete - Verified caching fix IS implemented, but discovered light-tier spawns bypass worker detection because context is injected into prompt instead of read from SPAWN_CONTEXT.md. Zero worker-specific metrics exist. Recommendation: Force all spawns to read SPAWN_CONTEXT.md for detection."}
{"id":"orch-go-8ijh","title":"Investigation: What signals predict which surfaced work gets acted on?","description":"Research question from closed epic orch-go-idmr. The system surfaces patterns, gaps, issues - but presents them as equally worthy. Hypotheses to test: blocking count, cost (tokens/time), trend (accelerating vs stable), resolution status. Method: instrument signals, collect data on what orchestrator acts on vs ignores, identify predictive patterns. Outcome: Decision on whether to build evaluation layer, and if so, what signals to use.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-12-30T13:11:51.758422-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-03T14:24:28.037578-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-03T14:24:28.037578-08:00","close_reason":"Already completed: Investigation found signal infrastructure is mature (focus alignment, priority, trend, retry pattern"}
