adictions across investigations\n3. Create a synthesized decision or consolidated investigation\n","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-01T10:35:50.607074-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-01T10:57:00.398724-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-01T10:57:00.398724-08:00","close_reason":"Synthesis complete (spawned with wrong skill before fix)"}
{"id":"orch-go-8uoh","title":"Dashboard Ops/History toggle doesn't switch views","description":"The ⚡ Ops / 📦 History buttons are rendered but clicking them doesn't change the view content. dashboardMode store exists and buttons call dashboardMode.set() but conditional rendering isn't switching. Introduced in og-work-dashboard-two-modes-27dec.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-12-27T11:37:20.470197-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-27T14:04:01.658594-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-27T14:04:01.658594-08:00","close_reason":"Fixed SSR/hydration mismatch in dashboard mode store. Root cause: store initialized at module level before browser context. Fix: added init() method called from onMount using browser from $app/environment. Build passes, Playwright test created.","labels":["triage:ready"]}
{"id":"orch-go-8uzl","title":"Enhanced error visibility for headless spawns (optional)","description":"## Context\n\nOptional enhancement identified during headless readiness investigation (orch-go-0r2q).\n\nCurrent state: Basic error handling exists - HTTP API errors propagate, SSE reconnects automatically.\n\nGap: User messaging for spawn failures could be clearer, retry logic not implemented.\n\n## Task\n\nEnhance error visibility and recovery for headless spawn mode.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] Spawn failures show clear error messages (not just generic HTTP errors)\n- [ ] SSE connection failures logged and visible to user\n- [ ] Optional: Retry logic for transient failures (network issues)\n- [ ] Optional: Better error recovery guidance (\"try again\", \"check OpenCode server\")\n\n## Priority\n\nLow - current error handling is functional. This is polish/UX improvement, not blocker.\n\n## Related\n\n- Epic orch-go-9e15 (Make headless default) - not blocked by this\n- Investigation .kb/investigations/2025-12-22-inv-headless-spawn-mode-readiness-what.md","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-12-22T20:38:38.854006-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-26T18:12:01.849895-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-26T18:12:01.849895-08:00","close_reason":"Added SpawnError types with clear messages and recovery guidance, retry logic for transient failures (3 attempts with exponential backoff), comprehensive tests. All acceptance criteria met.","labels":["skill:feature-impl","triage:ready","triage:review"]}
{"id":"orch-go-8wwgw","title":"Beads sqlite DB gets corrupted in Claude Code sandbox","description":"## Problem\n\nAgents running in Claude Code sandbox encounter corrupted beads sqlite database:\n\n```\nError: failed to open database: failed to enable WAL mode: sqlite3: database disk image is malformed\n```\n\nThis prevents agents from:\n- Writing Phase: Complete comments\n- Updating issue status\n- Any beads write operations\n\n## Evidence\n\nFrom orch-go-ngsok agent investigating capacity leak:\n```\nbd comments add orch-go-ngsok \"Phase: Complete - ...\"\nℹ️  Sandbox detected, using direct mode\nError: failed to open database: failed to enable WAL mode: sqlite3: database disk image is malformed\n```\n\n## Likely cause\n\nWAL mode + sandbox filesystem isolation = corruption. The sandbox may:\n- Have stale/partial copy of .beads/*.db files\n- Have WAL/SHM files out of sync with main DB\n- Be mounting read-only or copy-on-write\n\n## Impact\n\n- Agents can't report completion → capacity counter stays inflated\n- Compounds the daemon capacity leak issue (orch-go-ngsok)\n- Forces manual completion from host\n\n## Potential fixes\n\n1. **Disable WAL in sandbox** - Use `PRAGMA journal_mode=DELETE` when sandbox detected\n2. **Use JSONL-only in sandbox** - Skip sqlite entirely, read/append JSONL directly\n3. **Rebuild DB on corruption** - Auto-recover from JSONL when DB malformed\n4. **Mount .beads/ read-only in sandbox** - Prevent writes, force daemon communication\n\nOption 2 (JSONL-only) aligns with existing \"direct mode\" detection.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-01-23T12:58:04.045989-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-23T13:42:00.060781-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-23T13:42:00.060781-08:00","close_reason":"Closed","labels":["triage:ready"]}
