{"id":"orch-go-8zfz","title":"orch complete should check for unfiled discovered work in investigations","description":"**Problem:** Investigations complete with 'Discovered Work Check' tables listing follow-up issues to create, but those issues never get filed. Knowledge evaporates.\n\n**Evidence:** 2025-12-28-inv-knowledge-fragmentation-433-investigations-days.md had 3 recommendations in Discovered Work Check table, issue was closed, none were created. Only found 2 days later by accident.\n\n**Recommendation:** Add verification step to orch complete for investigation skill:\n1. Parse investigation file for 'Discovered Work Check' or similar section\n2. If found with 'Create beads issue' actions, warn: 'Investigation has N unfiled discovered work items'\n3. Either block completion or prompt orchestrator to file them\n\n**Design question (applying Design-First Gate):** Why do investigations have a Discovered Work section that's not enforced? Should discovered work auto-create issues, or is the human review valuable?\n\n**Success criteria:** Investigations with discovered work can't silently close without issues being filed.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2025-12-30T11:45:40.155198-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-30T13:33:00.12491-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-30T13:33:00.12491-08:00","close_reason":"Verified: Tests pass (19 tests in pkg/verify). Discovered work gate implemented in pkg/verify/discovered_work.go. Commit c4e117a7."}
