{"id":"orch-go-91a","title":"Investigate model flexibility and arbitrage for orch-go","description":"Port model flexibility and account management from Python orch-cli to orch-go, with Gemini support baked in.\n\n## Scope\n\n1. **Model selection on spawn**\n   - Add `--model` flag to `orch spawn`\n   - Support provider format: `anthropic/opus`, `gemini/gemini-2.5-flash`\n   - Add model aliases: `opus`, `sonnet`, `haiku`, `flash`\n   - Pass model to OpenCode via `opencode run --model`\n\n2. **Account management**\n   - Add `orch account` command (save/switch/list/remove)\n   - Read/write `~/.orch/accounts.yaml` (same format as Python)\n   - Token sources: OpenCode auth file, macOS Keychain\n   - Auto-switch when rate-limited (future)\n\n3. **Usage tracking**\n   - Add `orch usage` command (port from Python)\n   - Support multi-account usage display\n   - Warning thresholds for rate limits\n\n## Reference\n- Python implementation: `orch-cli/src/orch/accounts.py`, `usage.py`, `backends/opencode.py`\n- Model resolution: `opencode.py:140-168` (OPENCODE_MODEL_ALIASES)\n- Config format: `~/.orch/accounts.yaml`\n\n## Why\nRate-limiting pain: spawning workers maxed out Claude Max limits. Needed Gemini fallback but spawn failed due to Anthropic API key assumption. This enables orchestrator to manage model/account selection.","notes":"workspace: .orch/workspace/og-feat-inv-model-flexibility-20dec","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-12-20T13:50:25.4143-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-20T14:07:58.242996-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-20T14:07:58.242996-08:00"}
{"id":"orch-go-91qze","title":"Dashboard API is slow again: 623 OpenCode sessions causing 5-7s load times","description":"## Problem\n\nDashboard /api/agents takes 5-7 seconds to load. This is the third time we've hit this performance issue.\n\n## Evidence\n\n```\ntime curl -s 'http://localhost:5188/api/agents' \u003e /dev/null\n# 5.4s first request\n# 7.2s second request (cache not helping)\n\ncurl -s 'http://localhost:4096/session' | jq 'length'\n# 623 sessions\n\nls .orch/workspace | wc -l\n# 178 workspaces\n```\n\n## Root Cause Hypothesis\n\nThe handler iterates through 623 OpenCode sessions. Even with caching, the iteration is O(n) on session count.\n\n## Prior Fixes (didn't stick)\n\n- orch-go-50hv: Fixed getCompletionsForReview scanning 303 workspaces\n- orch-go-yw1q: Fixed findWorkspaceByBeadsID reading 702 workspace dirs\n\n## Potential Solutions\n\n1. **Prune old sessions** - Delete sessions older than X days\n2. **Pagination** - Only fetch recent sessions\n3. **Background indexing** - Build session→workspace map in background, serve from cache\n4. **Session cleanup on complete** - Delete OpenCode session when agent completes\n\n## This is a systemic issue\n\nWe keep fixing symptoms. Need to address the root cause: unbounded accumulation of sessions and workspaces.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-01-06T14:33:42.730058-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-06T15:30:54.428323-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-06T15:30:54.428323-08:00","close_reason":"Fixed dashboard API slowness (5-7s → 200-500ms) by filtering sessions older than 2 hours from beads lookups. Tests: go test ./cmd/orch/... - all tests pass. Self-review passed - no discovered work.","labels":["triage:ready"]}
