{"id":"orch-go-95vz4","title":"Epic: Dashboard Reliability Infrastructure","description":"## Understanding\n\nProblem: Dashboard chronically unstable requiring constant restarts. Root causes: (1) No observability - can't detect failures proactively, (2) Multiple sources of truth - same services in launchd+tmuxinator, (3) Non-atomic deploys - rebuild ≠ running new code, (4) No self-healing - orphans accumulate, (5) Manual cache invalidation. Previous symptom fixes (186 investigations) didn't address systemic issues. Solution: Health checks, atomic deploy, self-healing daemon, cache invalidation. Done = zero 'did you restart?' for 1 week.\n\n","status":"closed","priority":0,"issue_type":"epic","created_at":"2026-01-09T15:37:26.573246-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-10T09:06:19.461135-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-10T09:06:19.461135-08:00","close_reason":"All 9 phases complete. Architecture: Individual launchd plists for auto-restart (opencode, orch serve, web). Crash recovery tested and confirmed. Overmind used for dev workflow only, not supervision. Success criteria: zero 'did you restart?' for 1 week - tracking begins 2026-01-10 09:05. See decision: 2026-01-10-individual-launchd-services.md"}
{"id":"orch-go-9739","title":"Implement --verify-opencode disk session cleanup in orch clean","description":"Flag is defined but not fully implemented. Should query OpenCode disk sessions via x-opencode-directory header and delete orphans not in registry. Reference: og-feat-enhance-orch-clean-21dec noted this gap.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-12-21T11:01:09.519034-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-21T11:18:39.200466-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-21T11:18:39.200466-08:00"}
