or full timeline)\n```\n\n### Suggested Action\n\n1. Run `kb chronicle \"agent\"` to understand evolution\n2. Identify patterns and contradictions across investigations\n3. Create a synthesized decision or consolidated investigation\n","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-01T10:35:50.557704-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-01T10:57:00.298341-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-01T10:57:00.298341-08:00","close_reason":"Synthesis complete (spawned with wrong skill before fix)"}
{"id":"orch-go-9e15","title":"Epic: Make headless spawn mode the default","description":"## Goal\n\nMake headless spawn mode the default for orch-go, with tmux as opt-in via --tmux flag.\n\n## Context\n\nInvestigation (.kb/investigations/2025-12-22-inv-headless-spawn-mode-readiness-what.md) verified all requirements are met:\n- ✅ Status detection works for both modes\n- ✅ Completion detection via SSE monitor\n- ✅ Wait command works via beads comments\n- ✅ Error handling exists at HTTP API layer\n- ✅ User visibility equivalent to tmux\n\nHeadless is production-ready. Daemon already uses it exclusively. Only work needed is flipping the default and updating documentation.\n\n## Scope\n\n**In Scope:**\n- Change default spawn mode from tmux to headless\n- Add --tmux flag for opt-in tmux mode\n- Update CLAUDE.md documentation (project and global)\n- Update command help text and examples\n- Update orchestrator skill documentation\n\n**Out of Scope:**\n- Enhanced error visibility (retry logic, better messaging) - can be separate epic\n- Daemon integration testing - already designed for headless\n- Breaking changes to existing spawns - backward compatibility maintained\n\n## Success Criteria\n\n- [ ] `orch spawn SKILL \"task\"` spawns headless by default\n- [ ] `orch spawn --tmux SKILL \"task\"` spawns in tmux window\n- [ ] All documentation reflects new default\n- [ ] Orchestrator skill references updated\n- [ ] No breaking changes to existing workflows","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"epic","created_at":"2025-12-22T20:37:53.223226-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-26T13:46:17.589494-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-26T13:46:17.589494-08:00","close_reason":"All 4 children complete - headless is now default spawn mode"}
{"id":"orch-go-9e15.1","title":"Flip default spawn mode to headless with --tmux opt-in","description":"## Context\n\nPart of orch-go-9e15: Make headless spawn mode the default\n\n## Task\n\nChange the spawn command default behavior to use headless mode instead of tmux mode.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] Default spawn behavior (no flags) uses runSpawnHeadless\n- [ ] Add --tmux flag to enable tmux mode (opt-in)\n- [ ] Remove --headless flag (no longer needed - it's the default)\n- [ ] Maintain --inline flag for blocking TUI mode\n- [ ] Update spawn command help text to reflect new default\n- [ ] All tests pass\n\n## Implementation Notes\n\nFile to modify: cmd/orch/main.go (around line 1031-1043)\n\nCurrent logic:\n```go\nif inline {\n    return runSpawnInline(...)\n}\nif headless {\n    return runSpawnHeadless(...)\n}\n// Default: Tmux mode\nreturn runSpawnTmux(...)\n```\n\nNew logic:\n```go\nif inline {\n    return runSpawnInline(...)\n}\nif tmux {\n    return runSpawnTmux(...)\n}\n// Default: Headless mode\nreturn runSpawnHeadless(...)\n```","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-12-22T20:38:10.603325-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-22T20:59:15.543104-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-22T20:59:15.543104-08:00","close_reason":"Flipped default spawn mode to headless with --tmux opt-in flag. Code changes, help text, and investigation file committed. kn decision recorded.","labels":["skill:feature-impl","triage:ready"]}
{"id":"orch-go-9e15.2","title":"Update project CLAUDE.md to reflect headless default","description":"## Context\n\nPart of orch-go-9e15: Make headless spawn mode the default\n\nInvestigation found CLAUDE.md incorrectly states 'headless by default' when tmux was actually default. Now that headless IS default, ensure documentation is accurate.\n\n## Task\n\nUpdate /Users/dylanconlin/Documents/personal/orch-go/CLAUDE.md to reflect new spawn mode default.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] 'Spawn Flow' section updated (currently line 111)\n- [ ] 'Common Commands' section updated (currently line 184)\n- [ ] All examples show headless as default with --tmux opt-in\n- [ ] Remove references to --headless flag\n- [ ] Add --tmux flag examples where appropriate\n\n## Files to Update\n\n- CLAUDE.md:111 (Spawn Flow section)\n- CLAUDE.md:184-189 (Common Commands examples)","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-12-22T20:38:15.426403-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-22T21:05:07.204447-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-22T21:05:07.204447-08:00","close_reason":"Updated CLAUDE.md with three improvements: added --tmux mode to Spawn Flow section, clarified tail command requires --tmux spawn, added --tmux example to Common Commands. All changes committed in c0d8502.","labels":["skill:feature-impl","triage:ready"]}
{"id":"orch-go-9e15.3","title":"Update orchestrator skill to reflect headless default","description":"## Context\n\nPart of orch-go-9e15: Make headless spawn mode the default\n\nOrchestrator skill provides spawning guidance that needs to reflect new default spawn mode.\n\n## Task\n\nUpdate ~/.claude/skills/policy/orchestrator/SKILL.md to document headless as default spawn mode.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] Spawning Checklist section updated\n- [ ] Spawn modes section reflects: Default (headless), --tmux (opt-in), --inline (blocking)\n- [ ] Examples updated to show headless as default\n- [ ] Headless Swarm Pattern section updated (currently mentions 'headless is now the default')\n- [ ] Any references to --headless flag removed\n\n## Sections to Update\n\n- Spawning Checklist (spawn modes)\n- Headless Swarm Pattern\n- Common Commands examples","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-12-22T20:38:19.960243-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-23T15:53:17.494731-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-23T15:53:17.494731-08:00","close_reason":"Complete: Verified orchestrator skill already reflects headless default. Fixed outdated skill path in CLAUDE.md. Commit fd4bac6.","labels":["skill:feature-impl","triage:ready"]}
{"id":"orch-go-9e15.4","title":"Update spawn command help text and examples","description":"## Context\n\nPart of orch-go-9e15: Make headless spawn mode the default\n\nCommand help text and examples need to reflect new default spawn mode.\n\n## Task\n\nUpdate spawn command's help text, flag descriptions, and usage examples.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] Short description reflects headless default\n- [ ] Long description explains three modes: default (headless), --tmux (opt-in), --inline (blocking)\n- [ ] Flag descriptions updated (add --tmux, remove --headless)\n- [ ] Examples section shows correct usage\n- [ ] Related command help (work, daemon) updated if they reference spawn modes\n\n## Files to Update\n\n- cmd/orch/main.go (spawn command definition, around line 570-650)\n- cmd/orch/daemon.go (if it references spawn modes)\n- cmd/orch/work.go (if it references spawn modes)","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-12-22T20:38:24.353695-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-22T21:05:07.452961-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-22T21:05:07.452961-08:00","close_reason":"Updated spawn command help text to reflect headless as default mode. Changed Short description, reorganized Long description with mode hierarchy, grouped examples by mode, and clarified flag descriptions. All changes committed.","labels":["skill:feature-impl","triage:ready"]}
{"id":"orch-go-9ec7","title":"[orch-go] feature-impl: Build orch experiment subcommand for behavioral...","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-12-28T16:01:15.257881-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-28T16:17:43.09651-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-28T16:17:43.09651-08:00","close_reason":"Implemented orch experiment subcommand with 5 commands (create, list, run, status, analyze), pkg/experiment package, and tests. All tests pass, code compiles."}
{"id":"orch-go-9es5","title":"Stats bar requires horizontal scroll at 666px width - critical info hidden","description":"## Problem\n\nAt 666px width (half MacBook Pro screen), the stats bar overflows and requires horizontal scrolling. Critical info like beads ready count (173) and blocked count (17) are cut off.\n\n## Evidence\n\nScreenshot shows stats bar at 666px with horizontal scroll bar. Items visible:\n- archive, 0 errors, focused, 3/24 servers, 173 ready, (17 blocked)\nBut the 'D' button is cut off, indicating more content hidden.\n\n## Constraint\n\nNew constraint: Dashboard must be fully usable at 666px width. No horizontal scrolling. This is the minimum width for side-by-side orchestrator CLI + dashboard workflow on MacBook Pro.\n\n## Options\n\n1. **Wrap to 2 rows** - Stats bar becomes 2-line on narrow screens\n2. **Collapse/group** - Combine related stats (e.g., 'ready/blocked' as one item)\n3. **Progressive disclosure** - Show fewer items, expand on hover/click\n4. **Responsive icons** - Replace labels with icons at narrow widths\n5. **Priority ordering** - Most important stats first, others overflow to menu\n\n## Recommendation\n\nOption 1 or 2 - wrapping or grouping maintains visibility of all stats without hiding information.\n\n## Files\n- web/src/routes/+page.svelte - stats bar layout","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2025-12-24T14:43:53.67122-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-24T14:59:11.981794-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-24T14:59:11.981794-08:00","close_reason":"Stats bar now uses flex-wrap with grouped items (agent counts, secondary indicators) that wrap gracefully at 666px width instead of horizontal scrolling. Tests pass."}
{"id":"orch-go-9f46","title":"UI completion gate: Require screenshot + human approval before completing UI tasks","description":"Agents self-certify visual correctness they can't verify. Current flow: agent renders → thinks done → human discovers wrong. Fix: checkpoint gate requiring screenshot + explicit human approval before UI tasks can complete.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-12-26T08:16:26.392539-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-26T22:06:30.306378-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-26T22:06:30.306378-08:00","close_reason":"Implemented human approval requirement for UI completion gate. Agents now need --approve flag or explicit approval comment (✅ APPROVED, UI APPROVED, etc.) before UI tasks can complete. Added HasHumanApproval() function, --approve flag to orch complete, and comprehensive tests. Commit: f020a646","labels":["skill:feature-impl","triage:ready","triage:review"]}
{"id":"orch-go-9h7","title":"Expose Strategic Alignment commands (focus/drift/next)","description":"Wire up the existing pkg/focus implementation to the CLI.\n1. orch focus 'goal' [-p project]\n2. orch drift (check alignment)\n3. orch next (suggest focus-aligned work)","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-12-20T15:51:55.978952-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-20T16:53:39.041233-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-20T16:53:39.041233-08:00","labels":["triage:ready"]}
{"id":"orch-go-9hasd","title":"Session handoff content injected into worker sessions","description":"## Problem\n\nOpenCode worker sessions are receiving orchestrator session handoff content:\n\n```\n*Session Resumed** # Session Handoff\n**Orchestrator:** interactive-2026-01-14-131811\n**Focus:** Session tooling polish: resume fix, progressive capture, standalone validate\n**Duration:** 2026-01-14 13:18 →\n```\n\nThis content should ONLY appear in:\n- Interactive orchestrator sessions\n- Meta-orchestrator sessions resuming previous work\n\nWorkers should ONLY receive SPAWN_CONTEXT.md content.\n\n## Impact\n\n- **Token waste:** ~1-2k tokens on irrelevant handoff content\n- **Role confusion:** Worker may act like orchestrator\n- **Context pollution:** Worker sees wrong task/focus\n\n## Likely cause\n\nSession-context hook or plugin injects handoff without checking session type.\n\n## Fix\n\nInjection logic should check:\n```go\nif sessionType == \"worker\" || hasSpawnContext(session) {\n    // Skip handoff injection - worker has SPAWN_CONTEXT.md\n    return\n}\n// Only inject handoff for interactive/orchestrator sessions\n```\n\n## Files to investigate\n\n- `.opencode/plugin/session-context/` (if exists)\n- OpenCode session startup hooks\n- `orch spawn` context generation\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n- [ ] Spawned workers do NOT receive session handoff content\n- [ ] Interactive sessions still receive handoff when resuming\n- [ ] SPAWN_CONTEXT.md is the only injected context for workers","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-01-15T08:31:36.986211-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-15T09:32:50.037228-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-15T09:32:50.037228-08:00","close_reason":"Phase: Complete - Fixed plugin to check .orch/workspace/*/SPAWN_CONTEXT.md pattern. Detection logic verified. See SYNTHESIS.md in og-arch-session-handoff-content-15jan-5fc9.","labels":["triage:ready"]}
{"id":"orch-go-9hld","title":"Epic: Fix completion lifecycle state synchronization","description":"## Goal\n\nFix the state synchronization gaps in the agent completion lifecycle that cause:\n- 49 zombie in_progress issues (no active agent working on them)\n- triage:ready labels persisting after spawn\n- NEEDS_REVIEW completions showing for already-closed issues\n- 712 accumulated workspaces\n\n## Scope\n\n- Remove triage:ready label when issue transitions to in_progress\n- Add reconciliation command to detect and fix orphaned in_progress issues\n- Filter closed issues from orch review\n- Add workspace cleanup for stale workspaces\n\n## Out of Scope\n\n- Real-time state machine (event-driven sync)\n- Automatic cleanup without user confirmation\n- Daemon-side reconciliation\n\n## Success Criteria\n\n- [ ] After spawn, issue has in_progress status and no triage:ready label\n- [ ] orch reconcile identifies zombie issues and offers to fix\n- [ ] orch review doesn't show NEEDS_REVIEW for closed issues\n- [ ] orch clean --workspaces removes old workspace directories\n\n## Related\n\n- Investigation: .kb/investigations/2025-12-29-inv-completion-lifecycle-broken-49-zombie.md\n- Prior design: .kb/investigations/2025-12-25-design-orchestrator-completion-lifecycle-two.md","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"epic","created_at":"2025-12-29T08:35:27.398173-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-03T20:37:05.368936-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-03T20:37:05.368936-08:00","close_reason":"All 4 children complete: label removal, reconcile command, review filter, workspace cleanup"}
{"id":"orch-go-9hld.1","title":"Remove triage:ready label after spawn transitions issue to in_progress","description":"## Context\n\nPart of orch-go-9hld: Fix completion lifecycle state synchronization\n\n## Task\n\nAfter updating beads issue status to in_progress (cmd/orch/main.go:1315), remove the triage:ready label if present.\n\n## Implementation\n\nIn cmd/orch/main.go around line 1318, after the UpdateIssueStatus call, add:\n\n```go\n// Remove triage:ready label now that issue is being worked on\nif err := beads.FallbackRemoveLabel(beadsID, \"triage:ready\"); err != nil {\n    // Don't block spawn on label removal failure - just warn\n    fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"Warning: failed to remove triage:ready label: %v\\n\", err)\n}\n```\n\nMay need to add FallbackRemoveLabel helper in pkg/beads/cli_client.go similar to other Fallback* functions.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] After spawn, issue no longer has triage:ready label\n- [ ] Spawn doesn't fail if label removal fails\n- [ ] Test with issue that has triage:ready label\n- [ ] Test with issue that doesn't have triage:ready label","status":"closed","priority":0,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-12-29T08:35:38.672386-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-29T09:17:58.283855-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-29T09:17:58.283855-08:00","close_reason":"Added FallbackRemoveLabel to beads/client.go, RemoveTriageReadyLabel to verify/check.go, and call in spawn command after UpdateIssueStatus. Prevents triage:ready label from persisting after spawn.","labels":["triage:review"]}
{"id":"orch-go-9hld.2","title":"Add orch reconcile command to detect and fix zombie in_progress issues","description":"## Context\n\nPart of orch-go-9hld: Fix completion lifecycle state synchronization\n\n## Task\n\nAdd a new command `orch reconcile` that:\n1. Lists all in_progress issues from beads\n2. Gets all active OpenCode sessions\n3. Identifies issues that have no matching active agent (zombies)\n4. Offers to either:\n   - Reset issue status to 'open' (for re-spawn)\n   - Close issue with reason 'orphaned - no active agent'\n\n## Implementation\n\nCreate cmd/orch/reconcile.go with:\n- `orch reconcile` - Preview mode, shows zombies without action\n- `orch reconcile --fix` - Interactive mode, prompts for each zombie\n- `orch reconcile --reset-all` - Batch reset all zombies to open\n- `orch reconcile --close-all` - Batch close all zombies\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `orch reconcile` shows list of zombie issues\n- [ ] `orch reconcile --fix` prompts for action on each\n- [ ] Status updates work correctly\n- [ ] Test with current 44 zombies","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-12-29T08:35:44.091457-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-29T09:17:58.592222-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-29T09:17:58.592222-08:00","close_reason":"Added orch reconcile command (cmd/orch/reconcile.go) that detects zombie in_progress issues with no active agent and offers interactive fix options (reset to open or close). Includes tests, JSON output, project/age filtering.","labels":["triage:review"]}
{"id":"orch-go-9hld.3","title":"Filter closed issues from orch review NEEDS_REVIEW output","description":"## Context\n\nPart of orch-go-9hld: Fix completion lifecycle state synchronization\n\n## Task\n\nModify `orch review` to check if the beads issue is already closed before showing NEEDS_REVIEW status.\n\nCurrently, review.go processes workspaces and shows verification results without checking if the underlying beads issue has been closed. This causes stale NEEDS_REVIEW entries for work that's already complete.\n\n## Implementation\n\nIn cmd/orch/review.go, before displaying a completion item:\n1. Check if beads issue exists and its status\n2. If status is 'closed', either:\n   - Mark as OK (closed overrides NEEDS_REVIEW)\n   - Add a 'CLOSED' status indicator\n   - Filter out entirely from the default view\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] Closed issues don't show as NEEDS_REVIEW\n- [ ] Clear indication when issue state differs from workspace state\n- [ ] `--all` flag still shows everything for debugging\n- [ ] Test with orch-go-ptvu (closed but shows NEEDS_REVIEW)","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-12-29T08:35:54.946183-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-29T09:17:59.093871-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-29T09:17:59.093871-08:00","close_reason":"Added filterClosedIssues() to review.go that batch-fetches issue statuses and filters closed/deferred/tombstone issues from NEEDS_REVIEW output. Build and tests pass. Leave it Better: kn-2d701f.","labels":["triage:review"]}
{"id":"orch-go-9hld.4","title":"Add workspace cleanup option to orch clean command","description":"## Context\n\nPart of orch-go-9hld: Fix completion lifecycle state synchronization\n\n## Task\n\nAdd `--workspaces` flag to `orch clean` that removes workspace directories for completed/closed issues.\n\nCurrently 712 workspaces have accumulated in .orch/workspace/, causing:\n- Slow orch status (reads all workspaces)\n- Disk space consumption\n- Stale verification data\n\n## Implementation\n\nAdd to cmd/orch/clean.go:\n- `orch clean --workspaces` - Remove workspaces for closed issues\n- `orch clean --workspaces --older-than 7d` - Remove workspaces older than N days\n- `orch clean --workspaces --dry-run` - Show what would be removed\n\nLogic:\n1. List all workspace directories\n2. For each, check if linked beads issue is closed\n3. If closed (or older than threshold), mark for removal\n4. Prompt for confirmation unless --force\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `orch clean --workspaces --dry-run` shows cleanable workspaces\n- [ ] Workspaces for closed issues are removed\n- [ ] Workspaces for open/in_progress issues are preserved\n- [ ] --older-than flag works with day specification\n- [ ] Confirmation prompt before removal","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-12-29T08:36:00.15963-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-29T09:46:14.486442-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-29T09:46:14.486442-08:00","close_reason":"Added workspace cleanup to orch clean: --workspaces removes old workspace dirs (default \u003e7 days), --older-than N configures threshold, --force skips confirmation, skips workspaces with active sessions. Tests passing, committed.","labels":["triage:review"]}
{"id":"orch-go-9i2q","title":"Recover Priority 3: Infrastructure (pkg/shell, symlink, doctor improvements)","description":"Recover infrastructure improvements from Dec 27 - Jan 2 commits. Manual extraction approach.\n\nCommits to recover:\n- 7e3bd2fc: feat: pkg/shell package\n- 68b9cb5a: feat: symlink pattern\n- ce33d291: feat(doctor): stale binary detection\n- 1dee45f4: feat(doctor): failed-to-start detection\n\nReference: .kb/investigations/2026-01-03-inv-analyze-commits-between-fb0af37f-dec.md","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-03T12:08:11.418179-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-03T13:28:34.597894-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-03T13:28:34.597894-08:00","close_reason":"Recovered all Priority 3 infrastructure: pkg/shell (commit 3d8f2656 by parallel agent), Makefile symlink pattern, doctor stale binary detection (--stale-only flag), doctor stalled session detection. All committed in 96ebf9a2. Investigation updated.","labels":["skill:feature-impl"]}
{"id":"orch-go-9k1l","title":"Pre-spawn token estimation to prevent context overflow","description":"## Problem\n\nSpawn can fail with 'prompt is too long: 207879 tokens \u003e 200000 maximum' after creating workspace and session. No warning before spawn.\n\n## Evidence\n\norch-go-iq2h failed with 207k tokens. SPAWN_CONTEXT.md was only 534 lines (~19KB). The overflow came from combined context (system prompt + CLAUDE.md + skill + spawn context + kb context).\n\n## Solution\n\nBefore spawning, estimate total tokens:\n1. Count SPAWN_CONTEXT.md tokens (rough: chars/4)\n2. Add skill size estimate\n3. Add CLAUDE.md sizes (global + project)\n4. Add OpenCode system prompt overhead (~10-20k tokens)\n5. Warn or abort if approaching 200k limit\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] Pre-spawn token estimation\n- [ ] Warning at 150k+ estimated tokens\n- [ ] Abort at 180k+ with explanation\n- [ ] Suggest mitigations (skip kb context, use smaller skill)","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2025-12-23T16:00:45.337485-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-25T11:02:23.399703-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-25T11:02:23.399703-08:00","close_reason":"Implemented pre-spawn token estimation with warning at 100k tokens and error at 150k tokens. See pkg/spawn/tokens.go","labels":["triage:ready"]}
{"id":"orch-go-9kfwg","title":"[orch-go] feature-impl: Create a cross-compile script that rebuilds Lin...","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-20T15:19:10.831039-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-20T15:58:06.295712-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-20T15:58:06.295712-08:00","close_reason":"Phase: Complete - Created cross-compile script (scripts/cross-compile-linux.sh) for building Linux binaries (bd, orch, kb), updated docker.go PATH to prefer ~/.local/bin/linux-amd64, added Makefile targets cross-compile-linux and cross-compile-linux-orch. Tests: bash -n scripts/cross-compile-linux.sh - syntax valid; make help - targets visible."}
{"id":"orch-go-9khz5","title":"Bug: System auto-creating duplicate synthesis issues","description":"## Problem\n\nThe ready queue contains duplicate synthesis issues. For example:\n- 'Synthesize status investigations (10)' - orch-go-kkg60, orch-go-1nf10\n- 'Synthesize api investigations (11)' - orch-go-ygl3s, orch-go-qr1og, orch-go-2qiig\n- 'Synthesize tmux investigations (12)' - orch-go-i31dq, orch-go-lctt2, orch-go-8f42p\n\n## Root Cause Investigation Needed\n\n1. What is creating these synthesis issues? (daemon? orch hotspot? manual?)\n2. Why isn't it checking for existing open issues before creating?\n3. Where is the deduplication logic missing?\n\n## Immediate Fix\n\nClose duplicate issues, keeping one of each.\n\n## Long-term Fix\n\nAdd deduplication check before creating synthesis issues.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-01-06T19:56:11.683623-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-06T20:24:31.628878-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-06T20:24:31.628878-08:00","close_reason":"Fixed duplicate synthesis issues by changing deduplication check from open-only to all-statuses with 7-day cooldown. Fix implemented in kb-cli (125339a), tested and verified."}
{"id":"orch-go-9koc","title":"Agents should report BLOCKED status instead of going idle silently","description":"## Problem\n\nWhen agents hit technical walls (e.g., need browser tools but don't have them), they go idle silently. No beads comment indicating blocked status. Orchestrator has to infer from lack of progress.\n\n## Evidence\n\nFrom batch spawn failure analysis (pw-oq32.3):\n- Agent reached 'visual verification' step\n- No browser tools available\n- Agent went idle - no further comments\n- Orchestrator didn't know agent was stuck vs still working\n\n## Solution\n\nAdd BLOCKED comment pattern for stuck agents.\n\n**Skill guidance update:**\n- Add to worker skills: 'If blocked on external dependency, report via beads comment'\n- Pattern: `bd comment \u003cid\u003e 'BLOCKED: \u003creason\u003e'`\n- Examples:\n  - 'BLOCKED: Cannot verify UI - no browser tools available'\n  - 'BLOCKED: Test requires database connection - not configured'\n  - 'BLOCKED: Waiting for human decision on API design'\n\n**orch status enhancement:**\n- Parse beads comments for 'BLOCKED:' prefix\n- Show blocked agents with different indicator: '⚠️ BLOCKED' vs 'idle'\n- Include block reason in status output\n\n**Optional: bd block command**\n- `bd block \u003cid\u003e 'reason'` - sets blocked status with reason\n- Cleaner than comment pattern, enables filtering\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] Worker skill documentation updated with BLOCKED pattern\n- [ ] orch status detects BLOCKED comments and shows indicator\n- [ ] Block reason displayed in status output\n- [ ] Optional: bd block command for explicit blocking\n\n## References\n\n- Source: .kb/investigations/2025-12-29-inv-batch-spawn-failure-analysis.md","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2025-12-29T13:09:30.576765-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-29T13:27:14.74423-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-29T13:27:14.74423-08:00","close_reason":"Implemented BLOCKED status detection in orch status. Agents can now report 'BLOCKED: reason' via bd comment and orchestrator sees '🚫 blocked' indicator. Tests pass, skill documentation updated in orch-knowledge repo."}
{"id":"orch-go-9kq84","title":"Synthesize extract investigations (13)","description":"## Synthesis Needed\n\nTopic **extract** has accumulated 13 investigations that may benefit from consolidation.\n\n### Investigations to synthesize:\n\n- 2026-01-03-inv-extract-serve-agents-go-serve.md\n- 2026-01-03-inv-extract-serve-learn-go-serve.md\n- 2026-01-03-inv-extract-serve-system-go-serve.md\n- 2026-01-03-inv-extract-shared-go-utility-functions.md\n- 2026-01-03-inv-extract-status-cmd-go-main.md\n- 2026-01-04-inv-extract-clean-cmd-go-main.md\n- 2026-01-04-inv-extract-small-commands-send-tail.md\n- 2026-01-04-inv-phase-extract-serve-agents-cache.md\n- 2026-01-04-inv-phase-extract-serve-agents-events.md\n- 2026-01-04-inv-phase-extract-statsbar-component-extract.md\n- 2026-01-06-inv-extract-activitytab-component-part-orch.md\n- 2026-01-06-inv-extract-synthesistab-component-part-orch.md\n- 2025-12-26-inv-implement-kb-extract-command-cross.md\n\n### Chronicle Timeline\n\n```\n2025-12-19 [INV] OpenCode Client Package Session Management\n2025-12-19 [INV] SSE Event Monitoring Client\n2025-12-19 [INV] Desktop Notifications on Completion\n2025-12-19 [INV] Fix SSE parsing - event type inside JSON data\n2025-12-19 [INV] OpenCode POC - Spawn Session Via Go\n... (run kb chronicle for full timeline)\n```\n\n### Suggested Action\n\n1. Run `kb chronicle \"extract\"` to understand evolution\n2. Identify patterns and contradictions across investigations\n3. Create a synthesized decision or consolidated investigation\n","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-07T10:39:36.164644-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-07T11:40:21.793394-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-07T11:40:21.793394-08:00","close_reason":"Bulk close: auto-created synthesis issues disabled - synthesis is strategic orchestrator work, not spawnable work","labels":["triage:review"]}
