{"id":"orch-go-9w5je","title":"kb-cli: Fix reflect dedup to fail-safe (return exists=true on error)","description":"From investigation 2026-01-07-design-recurring-problem-duplicate-synthesis-issues: The deduplication check in kb reflect returns false (doesn't exist) when errors occur, causing duplicate issue creation. Should fail-safe by returning true (assume exists) on errors, with logging for diagnosis. This caused 48 duplicate synthesis issues. Fix is in kb-cli repo.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-01-07T15:33:12.218406-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-08T10:26:46.205652-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-08T10:26:46.205652-08:00","close_reason":"Fixed kb-cli reflect dedup to fail-safe (return true on error). Changed synthesisIssueExists and openIssueExists in reflect.go, updated tests. Commit cf2a08a in kb-cli."}
