{"id":"orch-go-9xwt8","title":"Calculate 'would unblock' for blocked issues","description":"Dependency traversal to show what completing a blocked issue would unlock.\n\n**Input:** A blocked issue ID\n**Output:** List of issues that would become unblocked, with counts\n\n**Example:**\n```\norch-go-ajxm1 → unblocks: orch-go-kz7zr (epic, 4 children)\n```\n\n**Algorithm:**\n1. Find all issues where this issue is a blocker\n2. For each, check if this is the ONLY blocker\n3. If yes, it would unblock; recursively check what that unblocks\n4. Return sorted by leverage (most downstream impact first)\n\n**Location:** pkg/beads/ or new pkg/frontier/\n\nUsed by `orch frontier` to prioritize what to show.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-24T08:14:47.172745-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-29T11:02:39.874577-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-29T11:02:39.874577-08:00"}
{"id":"orch-go-9y7xp","title":"Wire up project config to spawn defaults","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-19T23:23:51.964627-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-20T14:48:30.261641-08:00"}
{"id":"orch-go-9zcc4","title":"Add disabled_backends config option to prevent docker auto-selection","description":"## Problem\n\nDocker backend was auto-selected despite global config having `backend: claude`. Dylan's docker-associated Claude subscription is cancelled, so docker mode should never be used.\n\n## Solution\n\nAdd `disabled_backends` config option to ~/.orch/config.yaml that prevents specific backends from being selected, even via auto-selection logic.\n\nExample:\n```yaml\nbackend: claude\ndisabled_backends:\n  - docker\n```\n\n## Constraint\n\n`kb quick constrain \"Docker backend disabled - subscription cancelled\" --reason \"Dylan's docker-associated Claude subscription was cancelled Jan 2026\"` (kb-992d68)\n\n## Tasks\n\n1. Investigate where docker gets auto-selected (spawn_cmd.go backend resolution)\n2. Add `disabled_backends` field to userconfig.Config\n3. Update resolveBackend() in backend.go to check disabled list\n4. Error if --backend flag specifies a disabled backend\n5. Update config_cmd.go to support setting disabled_backends","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-01-23T18:17:43.44972-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-23T18:53:58.66816-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-23T18:53:58.66816-08:00","close_reason":"Implemented disabled_backends config option with 12 new tests. Tests: go test ./cmd/orch/... -run Backend - 33 passed, 0 failed"}
{"id":"orch-go-9zf6","title":"Migrate serve beads calls to RPC","description":"Replace cmd/orch/serve.go handleBeads() subprocess call with pkg/beads client.\nUse OpStats operation. Update BeadsAPIResponse to match.\n\nDepends on: pkg/beads Go RPC client implementation\nSource: orch-go-7yrh.10 investigation SYNTHESIS.md","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-12-26T12:00:36.97875-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-26T18:03:47.575456-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-26T18:03:47.575456-08:00","close_reason":"Fixed handleIssues RPC fallback logic bug. All serve.go beads calls were already migrated to RPC via verify package; only bug was in handleIssues where fallback logic was incorrect (checked 'issue == nil \u0026\u0026 err == nil' instead of properly falling through on RPC error).","labels":["skill:feature-impl","triage:ready"]}
