{"id":"orch-go-ae6j6","title":"Add hook to warn on slow find ~/Documents commands","description":"## Problem\n\nClaude autonomously generates `find ~/Documents` commands that take ~32 seconds each. This is a constant friction point that adds up (68 occurrences in action log = 36+ min cumulative).\n\n## Evidence\n\n- Timed: `find ~/Documents -name \"*sp-orch-ship-spec-extractors*\"` = 32.4s\n- Timed: `find ~/Documents -name \"*pw-orch-continue-observability*\"` = 32.9s\n- Direct path lookup: 0.014s (2000x faster)\n- Action log shows 68 broad find calls, ongoing pattern (most recent today)\n\n## Proposed Solution\n\nAdd a PreToolUse hook that detects `find ~/Documents` (or `find ~/` or `find ~`) without maxdepth and injects a warning:\n\n\u003e \"⚠️ Broad find is slow (~30s). Consider: project-scoped path, maxdepth, or `orch locate`\"\n\nThis applies pressure (Gate Over Remind) rather than compensating. Works for both Claude Code and OpenCode since both trigger Bash hooks.\n\n## Future Evolution\n\n- Could add `orch locate \u003cworkspace\u003e` command for O(1) workspace lookup via project registry\n- Could escalate from warn to block if pattern persists\n- Could track \"find avoided\" metrics to measure effectiveness","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-01-18T12:28:27.427203-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-18T14:29:03.749542-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-18T14:29:03.749542-08:00","close_reason":"Created slow-find-warn.ts plugin with Context Injection pattern, tested with 11 test cases, committed with investigation and SYNTHESIS.md","labels":["triage:ready"]}
