{"id":"orch-go-ag8i","title":"kb reflect --type skill-candidate: detect kn clusters warranting skill updates","description":"Pattern observed: multiple kn entries on same topic (e.g., daemon constraints/decisions) should trigger skill update consideration. Add reflection type that clusters kn entries by topic and surfaces candidates for skill consolidation. Example from Dec 25: 3+ daemon-related kn entries → orchestrator skill updates (launchd docs, daemon-first workflow).","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2025-12-25T14:34:43.565237-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-28T09:22:51.820579-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-28T09:22:51.820579-08:00","close_reason":"kb reflect --type skill-candidate is fully implemented. Prior agent completed: kb-cli clusters kn entries by topic (3+ threshold) with temporal RecentCount, orch-go has matching type definitions. All tests passing.","labels":["triage:ready"]}
{"id":"orch-go-agukq","title":"Add SpawnWorkForProject() to issue_adapter.go","description":"## Context\n\nPart of cross-project daemon implementation. See parent investigation:\n`.kb/investigations/2026-01-21-inv-cross-project-daemon-poll-multiple.md`\n\nDepends on: orch-go-00zsx (project-aware listing)\n\n## Task\n\nAdd project-aware spawn function to `pkg/daemon/issue_adapter.go`.\n\n## Implementation\n\n```go\n// SpawnWorkForProject spawns an agent for a beads issue in a specific project\nfunc SpawnWorkForProject(beadsID string, projectPath string) error {\n    // 1. Build command: orch work \u003cbeadsID\u003e --workdir \u003cprojectPath\u003e\n    // 2. Execute spawn\n    // 3. Include project name in log messages for visibility\n}\n```\n\n## Changes to existing SpawnWork\n\nOption A: Add projectPath parameter to existing SpawnWork()\nOption B: Create new function, have SpawnWork() call it with cwd\n\nRecommend Option B for backward compatibility.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] Function spawns agent with correct --workdir\n- [ ] Log messages include project name\n- [ ] Existing SpawnWork() continues to work (backward compatible)\n- [ ] Unit test verifying --workdir is passed","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-21T20:27:26.275243218Z","updated_at":"2026-01-21T20:43:25.476195375Z","closed_at":"2026-01-21T20:43:25.476195375Z","close_reason":"Phase: Complete - SpawnWorkForProject() with --workdir. Tests pass.","labels":["triage:ready"]}
