{"id":"orch-go-aj93a","title":"Add decision linkage to investigation template","description":"Investigation template should prompt 'Does this patch/extend a prior decision?' with path reference. Creates traceable chain from decision → patches, enabling review triggers.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-09T16:06:04.771714-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-17T15:06:54.978119-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-17T15:06:54.978119-08:00","close_reason":"Phase: Complete - Added Patches-Decision field to investigation template in both hardcoded (kb-cli) and override (~/.kb/templates/) locations. Template verified working via test creation. Investigation and SYNTHESIS.md committed.","labels":["triage:ready"]}
{"id":"orch-go-ajxm1","title":"Gap detection in orch complete: cross-check agent questions against existing kb","description":"After verifying agent work, cross-check SYNTHESIS.md 'open questions' against existing kb knowledge. If agent surfaced questions that kb already answers → log as surfacing gap.\n\n**Why:** Undetected knowledge gaps compound. This makes gaps visible so we can iterate on surfacing (better keywords, injection tier promotion, spawn context improvements).\n\n**Implementation:**\n1. Parse SYNTHESIS.md for 'Unexplored Questions' or 'Open Questions' section\n2. Extract key terms from each question\n3. Run kb context with those terms\n4. If existing decisions/constraints match → report gap\n5. Log gaps to ~/.orch/knowledge-gaps.jsonl for analysis\n\n**Success criteria:**\n- Gaps are detected and logged\n- Can review gap patterns over time (which knowledge keeps getting missed?)\n- Informs decisions about what to promote to spawn-time injection\n\n**Provenance:** Emerged from discussion about intra-task authority and knowledge surfacing, 2026-01-23. Related constraints: kb-768886, kb-86ccf7.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-01-23T16:19:39.200491-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","updated_at":"2026-01-23T16:19:39.200491-08:00"}
{"id":"orch-go-akhff","title":"Epic: Dashboard Agent Detail Pane Tabbed Interface","description":"## Goal\n\nRedesign the agent detail pane with a tabbed interface that provides focused views based on agent state:\n- Activity tab for active agents (live SSE feed)\n- Investigation tab for completed agents (workspace artifact viewer)\n- Synthesis tab for completed agents (D.E.K.N. display)\n\n## Scope\n\n- Tab navigation infrastructure with state-driven visibility\n- Panel width adjustment to 80-85% viewport\n- Three tab components extracted from monolithic panel\n- Maintain existing Quick Copy and Quick Commands sections\n\n## Out of Scope\n\n- Workspace file API endpoints (separate task if needed)\n- Mobile-specific layouts\n- Tab state persistence between sessions\n\n## Success Criteria\n\n- [ ] Panel works at 666px width with all tabs functional\n- [ ] Active agents show Activity tab by default\n- [ ] Completed agents show Synthesis tab by default\n- [ ] Tab switching is instant (\u003c50ms)\n- [ ] Existing functionality preserved (Quick Copy, Commands)\n- [ ] No layout shift on tab change\n\n## Design Reference\n\nSee .kb/investigations/2026-01-06-inv-orch-go-hmj61-dashboard-agent.md for detailed design specification.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"epic","created_at":"2026-01-06T14:19:02.878082-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-07T13:43:26.496881-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-07T13:43:26.496881-08:00","close_reason":"Complete. All tab components implemented (ActivityTab, SynthesisTab, InvestigationTab, TabButton). Panel refactored from 523 to 244 lines. State-driven tab visibility working. Quick Copy/Commands removed as intended."}
