{"id":"orch-go-akhff.9","title":"Extract SynthesisTab component","description":"Part of orch-go-akhff. Extract Synthesis section into SynthesisTab.svelte with D.E.K.N. section headers, outcome badges, Create Issue buttons, and close_reason fallback.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-06T14:20:17.494607-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-06T19:59:07.883136-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-06T19:59:07.883136-08:00","close_reason":"Created SynthesisTab.svelte (195 lines) with D.E.K.N. section headers, outcome badges, Create Issue buttons, and close_reason fallback. Component exported from index.ts and builds successfully. Ready for integration into agent-detail-panel.svelte (task orch-go-akhff.11)."}
{"id":"orch-go-akrcw","title":"Registry population issues - orch status shows sessions but registry.json appears empty","description":"## Problem\n`~/.orch/registry.json` appears empty but `orch status` shows sessions.\n\n## Impact\nUnclear source of truth for orchestrator sessions. Can't detect zombies reliably.\n\n## Investigation Needed\n- Where does `orch status` get orchestrator session data?\n- Is registry.json being populated correctly?\n- Should registry.json be the single source of truth?\n\n## Reference\n.kb/investigations/2026-01-06-inv-workspace-session-architecture.md (Gap #4)","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-01-06T10:56:41.192307-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-07T20:12:14.50083-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-07T20:12:14.50083-08:00","close_reason":"Resolved: filename misconception. sessions.json is the correct file and now has a self-describing schema."}
{"id":"orch-go-allmc","title":"[opencode] feature-impl: Implement session metadata exposure to plugins\n...","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-17T13:51:48.054674-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-17T14:02:18.244629-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-17T14:02:18.244629-08:00","close_reason":"Session metadata exposure implemented: Session.create accepts metadata, server processes x-opencode-env-* headers, plugin hooks receive session.metadata. 611 tests pass."}
{"id":"orch-go-amfa","title":"Epic: Unified Orchestrator Session Model","description":"## Goal\n\nUnify orchestrator session management with worker session patterns, giving orchestrators explicit session boundaries, tracking, resume capability, and reflection.\n\n## Context\n\nInvestigation .kb/investigations/2025-12-29-inv-unified-session-model-design.md found:\n- Workers have complete lifecycle (spawn → track → resume → reflect)\n- Orchestrators have fragile ad-hoc flow (76 'where were we?' requests)\n- session-transition skill never used (wrong abstraction)\n- 'Focus block' is the orchestrator session unit\n\n## Scope\n\n**In scope:**\n- `orch session start/status/end` commands (MVP)\n- Session state persistence (~/.orch/session.json)\n- Integration with existing focus/handoff commands\n- Retire session-transition skill\n\n**Out of scope:**\n- Beads tracking for orchestrator sessions (use focus tracking instead)\n- Automatic session detection (explicit boundaries preferred)\n- Full session history (Phase 2)\n\n## Success Criteria\n\n- [ ] Orchestrator sessions have explicit start/end boundaries\n- [ ] Session status shows duration, spawns, and focus\n- [ ] Session end produces handoff document automatically\n- [ ] session-transition skill retired\n- [ ] 'Where were we?' friction reduced (qualitative)","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"epic","created_at":"2025-12-29T10:40:59.832945-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-29T11:14:01.410413-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-29T11:14:01.410413-08:00","close_reason":"All 5 children complete: orch session start/status/end commands implemented, spawn tracking added, session-transition skill retired"}
{"id":"orch-go-amfa.1","title":"Implement orch session start command","description":"## Context\n\nPart of orch-go-amfa: Epic: Unified Orchestrator Session Model\n\n## Task\n\nImplement `orch session start [\"goal\"]` command that:\n1. Sets focus (via existing focus.New/Set)\n2. Records session start time to ~/.orch/session.json\n3. Creates session ID (for tracking spawns)\n4. Outputs confirmation with session ID and goal\n\n## Design Notes\n\nSession state file (~/.orch/session.json):\n```json\n{\n  \"id\": \"sess_20251229_103000\",\n  \"started\": \"2025-12-29T10:30:00Z\",\n  \"goal\": \"Ship snap MVP\",\n  \"focus_id\": \"focus_xyz\",\n  \"spawns\": []\n}\n```\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `orch session start \"goal\"` creates session state file\n- [ ] Session integrates with existing `orch focus` (reuse focus store)\n- [ ] Session ID generated (for spawn tracking)\n- [ ] Command outputs session ID and start time\n- [ ] Existing `orch focus` continues to work independently","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-12-29T10:41:11.975932-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-29T11:00:15.20449-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-29T11:00:15.20449-08:00","close_reason":"Implemented orch session start command (commit 2424381b)","labels":["triage:review"]}
{"id":"orch-go-amfa.2","title":"Implement orch session status command","description":"## Context\n\nPart of orch-go-amfa: Epic: Unified Orchestrator Session Model\n\n## Task\n\nImplement `orch session status` command that shows:\n1. Session ID and start time\n2. Duration (how long session has been running)\n3. Current focus/goal\n4. Spawns in this session (count + beads IDs)\n5. Active agents (from OpenCode/tmux)\n\n## Design Notes\n\nOutput format:\n```\nSession: sess_20251229_103000\nStarted: 2025-12-29 10:30 (2h 15m ago)\nGoal: Ship snap MVP\n\nSpawns this session: 5\n  - orch-go-xyz (complete)\n  - orch-go-abc (in_progress)\n  - ...\n\nActive agents: 2\n  Run `orch status` for details.\n```\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] Shows session duration and goal\n- [ ] Lists spawns created during this session\n- [ ] Integrates with existing `orch status` for agent details\n- [ ] Handles no-active-session gracefully (\"No active session\")","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-12-29T10:41:22.099591-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-29T11:13:42.210081-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-29T11:13:42.210081-08:00","close_reason":"Implemented orch session status with compact output format, spawns with status (complete/in_progress), active agents count from OpenCode API, and reference to orch status","labels":["triage:review"]}
{"id":"orch-go-amfa.3","title":"Implement orch session end command","description":"## Context\n\nPart of orch-go-amfa: Epic: Unified Orchestrator Session Model\n\n## Task\n\nImplement `orch session end` command that:\n1. Runs `orch handoff` to generate SESSION_HANDOFF.md\n2. Prompts for D.E.K.N. Knowledge and Next sections (required)\n3. Saves handoff to session workspace\n4. Clears session state file\n5. Optionally offers cleanup (tmux sessions, stale workspaces)\n\n## Design Notes\n\nWorkflow:\n```\n$ orch session end\nSession sess_20251229_103000 ending...\nDuration: 4h 30m\nSpawns: 8 (6 complete, 2 in_progress)\n\n⚠️  2 agents still running. Continue? (y/n)\n\nGenerating handoff...\n[D.E.K.N. prompts for Knowledge and Next]\n\nHandoff saved to: ~/.orch/session/2025-12-29/SESSION_HANDOFF.md\nSession ended.\n```\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] Generates handoff document with session context\n- [ ] Prompts for synthesis sections (Knowledge, Next)\n- [ ] Warns about in-progress agents before ending\n- [ ] Saves handoff to session directory\n- [ ] Clears session state after successful end","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-12-29T10:41:33.746833-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-29T11:13:44.280408-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-29T11:13:44.280408-08:00","close_reason":"Implemented orch session end with handoff integration: warns about in-progress agents, prompts for D.E.K.N. Knowledge/Next sections, saves handoff to ~/.orch/session/{date}/SESSION_HANDOFF.md, adds --no-handoff and --force flags","labels":["triage:review"]}
{"id":"orch-go-amfa.4","title":"Track spawns in session state","description":"## Context\n\nPart of orch-go-amfa: Epic: Unified Orchestrator Session Model\n\n## Task\n\nModify `orch spawn` to record spawns in session state:\n1. Check if active session exists\n2. Append spawn info (beads ID, workspace, timestamp) to session.json\n3. Make recording optional (spawns work without active session)\n\n## Design Notes\n\nSession state update:\n```json\n{\n  \"id\": \"sess_20251229_103000\",\n  \"spawns\": [\n    {\"beads_id\": \"orch-go-xyz\", \"workspace\": \"og-inv-foo\", \"spawned\": \"...\"},\n    {\"beads_id\": \"orch-go-abc\", \"workspace\": \"og-feat-bar\", \"spawned\": \"...\"}\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `orch spawn` records spawn in active session (if exists)\n- [ ] Spawning works normally without active session\n- [ ] Session status shows spawns from this session\n- [ ] No breaking changes to existing spawn behavior","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-12-29T10:41:43.880197-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-29T11:00:24.078193-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-29T11:00:24.078193-08:00","close_reason":"Implemented spawn tracking in session state (commit 205d6e02)","labels":["triage:review"]}
{"id":"orch-go-amfa.5","title":"Retire session-transition skill","description":"## Context\n\nPart of orch-go-amfa: Epic: Unified Orchestrator Session Model\n\n## Task\n\nRemove the unused session-transition skill:\n1. Delete ~/.claude/skills/session-transition/ directory\n2. Update any references in other skills or docs\n3. Document the replacement (`orch session` commands)\n\n## Design Notes\n\nThe session-transition skill was designed for generic Claude Code sessions but:\n- Uses .claude/ paths instead of .orch/\n- Doesn't understand orchestrator context (agents, focus, beads)\n- Has never been used (per task description)\n\nReplacement: `orch session start/status/end` commands provide orchestrator-specific session management.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] session-transition skill directory removed\n- [ ] No broken references in other skills\n- [ ] orchestrator skill updated to reference `orch session` commands\n- [ ] skillc rebuild succeeds","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-12-29T10:41:53.935736-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-29T11:13:45.760579-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-29T11:13:45.760579-08:00","close_reason":"Retired session-transition skill. Deleted 3 duplicate directories + symlink from ~/.claude/skills/. Updated orchestrator skill to reference orch session commands. Removed source from orch-knowledge. Leave it Better: recorded decision kn-cc7aa3.","labels":["triage:review"]}
{"id":"orch-go-aml6f","title":"Implement kb archive --synthesized-into command","description":"Move investigations to .kb/investigations/synthesized/{guide-name}/ subdirectory after synthesis. See design: 2026-01-07-design-post-synthesis-investigation-archival.md. Implementation: add to kb-cli, create synthesized/ directory, optionally add Sources section to guide.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-01-08T14:59:57.819985-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-08T20:09:26.546967-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-08T20:09:26.546967-08:00","close_reason":"kb archive --synthesized-into command verified working and test suite added (7 tests). Fixed unused import bug. Implementation follows design doc at 2026-01-07-design-post-synthesis-investigation-archival.md."}
{"id":"orch-go-an0","title":"Scaffold beads-ui v2 (Bun + SvelteKit 5 + shadcn-svelte)","description":"Scaffold the new beads-ui architecture.\n1. Initialize Bun + SvelteKit 5 project.\n2. Configure Tailwind CSS.\n3. Install shadcn-svelte and basic components (Card, Button, Badge).\n4. Set up the basic layout for the 'Headless Swarm Dashboard'.\n5. Ensure it can connect to the orch-go SSE stream.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-12-20T17:35:22.107007-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-25T22:14:51.865436-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-25T22:14:51.865436-08:00","close_reason":"Batch close from orch review","labels":["triage:ready"]}
{"id":"orch-go-anos","title":"Dashboard shows 0 active when CLI shows running agents","description":"API returns status='idle' for agents that CLI shows as 'running'. Root cause: API uses time-based DetermineStatusFromSession() which marks agents as idle after 10min without update, but CLI uses IsSessionProcessing() which checks actual OpenCode session state. Need to either: (1) have API call IsSessionProcessing for non-completed agents, or (2) have frontend treat 'idle' as still-visible in Active Agents section.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2025-12-28T14:04:46.918692-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-28T14:42:37.593998-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-28T14:42:37.593998-08:00","close_reason":"Fix verified working. API returns correct status (2 active matching CLI), dashboard displays agents correctly. All verification tests pass: no idle+Complete edge cases, no status mismatches. Fix committed in 3a834ac0.","labels":["triage:ready"]}
{"id":"orch-go-ao6nf","title":"Add infrastructure work detection to triage/spawn","description":"Auto-detect when work targets critical infrastructure (OpenCode server, orch CLI, daemon) and auto-apply --backend claude --tmux flags. Pattern detection: paths like ~/Documents/personal/opencode/, keywords like 'opencode server', 'plugin system'. Prevents agents from killing themselves by restarting their own dependencies.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-01-11T18:34:48.318077-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-11T22:35:13.781843-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-11T22:35:13.781843-08:00","close_reason":"Infrastructure work detection implemented with keyword matching, auto-applies --backend claude --tmux flags. Tests added, investigation documented, code committed (4d3e9abb)."}
