{"id":"orch-go-aop1z","title":"Synthesize api investigations (12)","description":"## Synthesis Needed\n\nTopic **api** has accumulated 12 investigations that may benefit from consolidation.\n\n### Investigations to synthesize:\n\n- 2025-12-20-inv-add-api-agentlog-endpoint-serve.md\n- 2025-12-20-inv-poc-port-python-standalone-api.md\n- 2025-12-24-inv-add-api-usage-endpoint-serve.md\n- 2025-12-26-inv-add-api-errors-endpoint-error.md\n- 2025-12-26-inv-api-endpoint-api-agents-hangs.md\n- 2025-12-26-inv-evaluate-building-api-proxy-layer.md\n- 2025-12-27-inv-api-agents-endpoint-takes-19s.md\n- 2026-01-03-inv-add-api-changelog-endpoint-orch.md\n- 2026-01-03-inv-map-serve-go-api-handler.md\n- 2026-01-05-inv-pending-reviews-api-times-out.md\n- 2026-01-07-inv-api-beads-endpoint-takes-5s.md\n- 2025-12-26-add-api-reflect-endpoint-expose.md\n\n### Chronicle Timeline\n\n```\n2025-12-19 [INV] CLI Orch Status Command\n2025-12-19 [INV] SSE Event Monitoring Client\n2025-12-19 [INV] Desktop Notifications on Completion\n2025-12-19 [INV] OpenCode POC - Spawn Session Via Go\n2025-12-19 [INV] Fix comment ID parsing - Comment.ID type mismatch\n... (run kb chronicle for full timeline)\n```\n\n### Suggested Action\n\n1. Run `kb chronicle \"api\"` to understand evolution\n2. Identify patterns and contradictions across investigations\n3. Create a synthesized decision or consolidated investigation\n","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-07T22:39:39.235753-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-07T22:46:44.284626-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-07T22:46:44.284626-08:00","close_reason":"Bulk close: kb reflect synthesis issues are noise until detection is fixed","labels":["triage:review"]}
{"id":"orch-go-appsr","title":"Graph filter controls","description":"Filter and scope the graph view.\n\n**Filters:**\n- By epic (scope to one epic's subgraph)\n- By type (show/hide questions, tasks, etc.)\n- By status (show/hide closed)\n- By authority (highlight human-required edges)\n\n**Why:** Graph with 50+ nodes is overwhelming. Filters make it usable at scale.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-01-23T09:49:06.077023-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-24T09:06:22.21858-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-24T09:06:22.21858-08:00","close_reason":"Pivot: readable frontier over graph visualization (decision 2026-01-24). Graph is optional deep-dive, not primary interface.","dependencies":[{"issue_id":"orch-go-appsr","depends_on_id":"orch-go-5ubkd","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-01-24T00:34:49.550138-08:00","created_by":"dylanconlin","authority":"daemon"}]}
{"id":"orch-go-apzui","title":"[orch-go] architect: Backend selection logic in spawn_cmd.go has acc...","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-20T10:20:25.614571-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-20T10:30:13.559649-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-20T10:30:13.559649-08:00","close_reason":"Phase: Complete - Designed resolveBackend() function with clean priority chain (flags \u003e project config \u003e global config \u003e default opencode) and advisory-only infrastructure detection. Added feat-051 for implementation."}
{"id":"orch-go-aq6u","title":"Dashboard shows 'Waiting for activity' for cross-project agents - SSE only streams current project","description":"**Symptom:** Cross-project agent (pw-t0go) appears in dashboard but shows 'Waiting for activity...' with no real-time updates.\n\n**Root cause:** handleEvents in serve.go only sets x-opencode-directory for the current project (sourceDir). Events from other projects aren't streamed.\n\n**Location:** cmd/orch/serve.go:1147-1149\n\n**Fix options:**\n1. Open multiple SSE connections (one per discovered project) and multiplex\n2. Query OpenCode for a cross-project SSE endpoint (may not exist)\n3. Poll /api/agents periodically as fallback for cross-project agents\n\n**Related:** orch-go-h3nh fixed visibility, this is the SSE counterpart","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2025-12-29T10:52:00.407508-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-29T10:59:25.278829-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-29T10:59:25.278829-08:00","close_reason":"Implemented SSE multiplexing in handleEvents to stream events from all discovered project directories. Uses discoverAllProjectDirs() to find all projects with OpenCode sessions, opens concurrent SSE connections via goroutines, and forwards all events to the client. Limits to 10 connections to prevent resource exhaustion. Cross-project agents will now show real-time activity in dashboard."}
{"id":"orch-go-aqo8","title":"Fix orchestrator skill: replace Claude Code hook references with OpenCode plugin system","description":"The orchestrator skill (~/.claude/skills/meta/orchestrator/SKILL.md) references Claude Code hooks (SessionStart, ~/.claude/hooks/, cdd-hooks.json) but we use OpenCode which has a different plugin system (.opencode/plugin/, JS/TS modules, session.created events). This caused an agent to implement the wrong platform's hooks. Need to: 1) Audit skill for all Claude Code references 2) Replace with OpenCode plugin equivalents 3) Document the distinction clearly","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-12-29T12:31:52.480661-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-29T12:58:11.327657-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-29T12:58:11.327657-08:00","close_reason":"Replaced all Claude Code hook references in orchestrator skill with OpenCode plugin equivalents. Updated ~/.claude/skills/meta/orchestrator/SKILL.md, ~/.claude/skills/policy/orchestrator/SKILL.md, and ~/.claude/CLAUDE.md. Added OpenCode plugins section to Config File Locations. Mapping: SessionStart → session.created, PreToolUse → tool.execute.before, PostToolUse → tool.execute.after. Investigation artifact created at .kb/investigations/2025-12-29-inv-fix-orchestrator-skill-replace-claude.md. Leave it Better: recorded kn constrain about platform distinction."}
{"id":"orch-go-aqrgd","title":"Synthesize orchestrator investigations (31)","description":"## Synthesis Needed\n\nTopic **orchestrator** has accumulated 31 investigations that may benefit from consolidation.\n\n### Investigations to synthesize:\n\n- 2025-12-21-inv-orchestrator-session-boundaries.md\n- 2025-12-23-inv-cleanup-after-orchestrator-skill-loading.md\n- 2025-12-23-inv-explore-value-orchestrator-worker-awareness.md\n- 2025-12-23-inv-orchestrator-skill-loading-workers-despite.md\n- 2025-12-23-inv-update-orchestrator-skill-reflect-headless.md\n- 2025-12-24-inv-orchestrator-skill-says-complete-agents.md\n- 2025-12-25-design-orchestrator-completion-lifecycle-two.md\n- 2025-12-25-inv-orchestrator-pre-spawn-context-gathering.md\n- 2025-12-25-inv-should-orchestrator-have-visibility-into.md\n- 2025-12-27-inv-capacity-utilization-workflow-orchestrator-proactively.md\n- 2025-12-27-inv-document-orch-patterns-command-orchestrator.md\n- 2025-12-27-inv-orchestrator-self-correction-mechanisms-problem.md\n- 2026-01-04-design-meta-orchestrator-architecture-spawnable-orchestrator.md\n- 2026-01-04-design-meta-orchestrator-role-definition.md\n- 2026-01-04-design-orchestrator-skill-spawnable-agent-gap.md\n- 2026-01-04-inv-meta-orchestrator-level-collapse-spawned.md\n- 2026-01-04-inv-phase-orchestrator-context-md-template.md\n- 2026-01-04-inv-spawnable-orchestrator-sessions-infrastructure-changes.md\n- 2026-01-04-inv-test-spawnable-orchestrator-infrastructure.md\n- 2026-01-04-inv-test-spawnable-orchestrator-tmux-default.md\n- 2026-01-05-debug-orch-complete-fails-orchestrator-sessions.md\n- 2026-01-05-debug-orchestrator-workspace-name-collision-bug.md\n- 2026-01-05-inv-design-orchestrator-session-lifecycle-without.md\n- 2026-01-05-inv-feat-038-unregister-orchestrator-sessions.md\n- 2026-01-05-inv-fix-orchestrator-context-md-contradiction.md\n- 2026-01-05-inv-orchestrator-worker-bidirectional-communication-interaction.md\n- 2026-01-05-inv-orchestrator-workspaces-clear-visual-distin