{"id":"orch-go-azgvy","title":"/api/beads/ready endpoint takes 5.2s - profile and fix","description":"The /api/beads/ready endpoint takes 5.2 seconds to respond.\n\n## Context\nThis endpoint should be fast - it just lists ready issues. But it's taking 5+ seconds.\n\nDuring the Jan 7 dashboard performance investigation, we fixed /api/agents but found this endpoint is also slow.\n\n## What to investigate\n1. Profile the endpoint\n2. Check if it's calling bd ready or bd list multiple times\n3. Check if there's unnecessary enrichment happening\n4. Consider caching (ready issues don't change frequently)\n\n## Reference\n- .kb/investigations/2026-01-07-inv-dashboard-api-agents-performance-synthesis.md","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-07T10:36:11.844037-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-07T10:55:04.841822-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-07T10:55:04.841822-08:00","close_reason":"Fixed by same caching implementation as orch-go-fwae6. ~16ms vs 5.2s before.","labels":["triage:ready"]}
{"id":"orch-go-azlv2","title":"Evaluate OpenAI models for orchestration quality","description":"Before committing to OpenAI as primary, evaluate model quality for orchestration tasks.\n\nTest cases:\n1. Orchestrator session with o3 - strategic planning, synthesis\n2. Worker spawn with gpt-5.2-codex - investigation task\n3. Worker spawn with o4-mini - feature-impl task\n4. Compare completion quality to Opus 4.5 (via Docker)\n\nSuccess criteria:\n- Agents complete tasks without confusion\n- SYNTHESIS.md quality comparable to Claude\n- No auth/session issues over extended use\n\nDocument findings in investigation artifact.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-20T18:20:03.591591-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-20T19:25:10.755792-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-20T19:25:10.755792-08:00","close_reason":"Phase: Complete - OpenCode authentication with OpenAI backend confirmed working; session creation with openai/gpt-5-nano succeeds; OAuth configured; 50+ OpenAI models available"}
