{"id":"orch-go-b111k","title":"kb index: surface knowledge artifacts at session start","description":"Add `kb index` command that outputs a concise index of knowledge artifacts for session context injection.\n\n## Problem\nOrchestrators repeatedly rediscover existing models/guides because .kb/ contents aren't surfaced at session start. This causes awareness lag - each session is surprised by what already exists.\n\n## Solution\n`kb index` scans .kb/ and outputs a formatted index:\n\n```\n## Knowledge Index (query with kb context \"\u003ctopic\u003e\")\n\n**Models:**\n- decidability-graph - Authority boundaries, Work/Question/Gate nodes\n- daemon-autonomous-operation - How daemon traverses work\n\n**Guides:**\n- spawn - Flags, context quality, troubleshooting\n- agent-lifecycle - States, completion, abandonment\n```\n\n## Implementation\n- Scan .kb/models/*.md, .kb/guides/*.md, .kb/decisions/*.md (recent)\n- Extract title from filename or H1\n- Extract summary from first paragraph or frontmatter\n- Output formatted markdown index\n- Session start hook calls `kb index` (like `bd prime`)\n\n## Integration\n- Hook in ~/.claude/hooks/ or similar calls kb index at session start\n- Output injected into orchestrator context\n- Orchestrator sees what exists, queries with `kb context` when relevant\n\n## Note\nImplementation is in kb tool (orch-knowledge repo), but tracked here as it serves orchestration workflow.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-01-23T09:55:24.42132-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-23T11:12:41.425839-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-23T11:12:41.425839-08:00","close_reason":"Phase: Complete - Implemented kb index command in kb-cli repo. Creates index.go (300+ lines) and index_test.go (250+ lines). Command scans .kb/ and outputs formatted markdown index of models, guides, and recent decisions. Tests pending host execution (Go not available in sandbox). Commits: kb-cli@5e52def, orch-go@eaaa8f48.","labels":["triage:ready"]}
