{"id":"orch-go-b4z4x","title":"Add automated checkpoint reminders for orchestrator sessions","description":"Investigation: 2026-01-06-inv-orchestrator-sessions-checkpoint-discipline-max.md\n\nContext: Checkpoint discipline (2h/3h/4h thresholds) implemented with visual warnings in orch session status. Now enforced via visibility rather than hard blocks.\n\nCurrent state: Manual checkpoint tracking via status command.\n\nRecommendation: Add automated checkpoint reminders via daemon or event hooks.\n\nEvidence: Real-world harm from long sessions - pw-orch-resume-price-watch-06jan-bcd7: 5h session, partial outcome. Long sessions lead to context exhaustion, degraded quality, lost work.\n\nPattern established: Session duration discipline pattern (2h warning, 3h strong, 4h max).","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-01-18T01:56:12.203243-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-18T01:56:12.203243-08:00"}
