{"id":"orch-go-b6hwn","title":"P0: Supervise overmind via launchd for reliability","description":"Create launchd plist to supervise overmind process. Currently overmind manages services but has no supervisor - if overmind crashes, all services go down and service monitor goes blind. Architecture should be: launchd supervises overmind → overmind manages services → service monitor monitors services. Implementation: Create ~/Library/LaunchAgents/com.overmind.orch-go.plist with KeepAlive=true, RunAtLoad=true. Success: Overmind auto-starts at login, auto-restarts on crash, service monitor continues working. References .kb/decisions/2026-01-09-dashboard-reliability-architecture.md principle 'launchd owns ALL persistent services'.","status":"closed","priority":0,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-01-09T23:58:13.826574-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-10T00:59:37.84843-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-10T00:59:37.84843-08:00","close_reason":"Created launchd plist for overmind supervision with KeepAlive, tested crash recovery (5s auto-restart), documented in CLAUDE.md. All deliverables committed.","labels":["triage:ready"]}
