{"id":"orch-go-balvg","title":"Investigate: Interactive orchestrators as compensation pattern","description":"## Problem\n\nHypothesis emerged from meta-orchestrator session: interactive orchestrators may be compensation for daemon/system gaps rather than a legitimate coordination layer.\n\nEvidence:\n- 94% manual spawn vs 6% daemon (prior data)\n- HTTP/2 orchestrator session completed without needing interactive guidance\n- What interactive orchestration 'provides' is mostly timing control (impulse)\n- Goal refinement could be front-loaded into issue creation\n\n## Questions to Answer\n\n1. What does daemon need to handle orchestrator-level coordination autonomously?\n2. What priority/urgency signaling is missing from the issue→daemon flow?\n3. What would break if interactive orchestrators disappeared tomorrow?\n4. Is 'conversation during execution' actually needed, or is it compensation?\n\n## Proposed Evolution\n\n```\nCurrent:  Dylan → Meta-orch → Interactive Orchestrator → Workers\nFuture:   Dylan → Meta-orch → Issues (refined) → Daemon → Workers\n```\n\nMeta-orchestrator becomes planning partner (outputs issues), not spawning partner (outputs `orch spawn`).\n\n## Success Criteria\n\n- Clear understanding of daemon gaps blocking this evolution\n- Decision on whether to proceed with Phase 2 (reduce interactive orchestration)\n- Identified what 'priority signaling' would look like\n\n## Context\n\n- Prior session: meta-orch-strategic-session-review-05jan-c3eb\n- Principles: Perspective is Structural, Pressure Over Compensation, Premise Before Solution\n- Related: orch-go-eyvap (--bypass-triage friction, now shipped)","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-06T08:00:41.950482-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-06T08:15:42.402012-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-06T08:15:42.402012-08:00","close_reason":"Investigation complete - finding: interactive orchestrators serve legitimate functions, daemon underutilization is separate problem","labels":["skill:architect","triage:ready"]}
{"id":"orch-go-bcyq7","title":"Synthesize api investigations (13)","description":"## Synthesis Needed\n\nTopic **api** has accumulated 13 investigations that may benefit from consolidation.\n\n### Investigations to synthesize:\n\n- 2025-12-20-inv-add-api-agentlog-endpoint-serve.md\n- 2025-12-20-inv-poc-port-python-standalone-api.md\n- 2025-12-24-inv-add-api-usage-endpoint-serve.md\n- 2025-12-26-inv-add-api-errors-endpoint-error.md\n- 2025-12-26-inv-api-endpoint-api-agents-hangs.md\n- 2025-12-26-inv-evaluate-building-api-proxy-layer.md\n- 2025-12-27-inv-api-agents-endpoint-takes-19s.md\n- 2026-01-03-inv-add-api-changelog-endpoint-orch.md\n- 2026-01-03-inv-map-serve-go-api-handler.md\n- 2026-01-05-inv-pending-reviews-api-times-out.md\n- 2026-01-07-inv-api-beads-endpoint-takes-5s.md\n- 2026-01-08-inv-backend-sends-last-activity-api.md\n- 2025-12-26-add-api-reflect-endpoint-expose.md\n\n### Chronicle Timeline\n\n```\n2025-12-19 [INV] CLI Orch Status Command\n2025-12-19 [INV] SSE Event Monitoring Client\n2025-12-19 [INV] Desktop Notifications on Completion\n2025-12-19 [INV] OpenCode POC - Spawn Session Via Go\n2025-12-19 [INV] Fix comment ID parsing - Comment.ID type mismatch\n... (run kb chronicle for full timeline)\n```\n\n### Suggested Action\n\n1. Run `kb chronicle \"api\"` to understand evolution\n2. Identify patterns and contradictions across investigations\n3. Create a synthesized decision or consolidated investigation\n","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-08T12:13:48.990992-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-08T15:43:22.863952-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-08T15:43:22.863952-08:00","close_reason":"Phase: Complete - Duplicate spawn detected. The 13 API investigations were already synthesized by a prior agent today (2026-01-08-inv-synthesize-api-investigations-13-synthesis.md). Guide updated with TTL caching patterns, prior synthesis marked superseded. No additional action needed.","labels":["triage:review"]}
{"id":"orch-go-bdd","title":"Epic: Headless Swarm - Batch Execution with Rate-Limit Management","description":"## Goal\n\nEnable concurrent batch spawning of headless agents with intelligent rate-limit management across Claude Max accounts.\n\n## Scope\n\n**In Scope:**\n- Batch spawn command (`orch swarm` or daemon enhancement)\n- Concurrency control (configurable max active agents)\n- Rate-limit detection before hitting limits\n- Auto-account switching when capacity exhausted\n- Spawn queuing when all accounts at limit\n- Aggregate progress visibility\n\n**Out of Scope:**\n- Multi-model routing (flash vs opus based on task complexity)\n- Distributed architecture across machines\n- UI dashboard (CLI-first)\n\n## Success Criteria\n\n- [ ] Can spawn N agents concurrently with `--concurrency N` flag\n- [ ] System detects approaching rate limits and switches accounts\n- [ ] Spawns queue when all accounts exhausted (no errors from rate limits)\n- [ ] `orch status` shows aggregate swarm progress\n- [ ] No manual account switching required during batch operations","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"epic","created_at":"2025-12-20T19:24:10.128888-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-22T16:21:11.362556-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-22T16:21:11.362556-08:00","close_reason":"All 6 children complete. Headless swarm infrastructure shipped: capacity tracking, worker pool concurrency, orch swarm command, SSE completion tracking."}
{"id":"orch-go-bdd.1","title":"Add usage/capacity tracking to account package","description":"## Context\n\nPart of orch-go-bdd: Headless Swarm epic.\n\nFoundation task: Before we can manage rate limits, we need to know current usage per account.\n\n## Task\n\nExtend `pkg/account/` to track and expose usage capacity:\n\n1. Add `GetUsage(accountName string) (*UsageInfo, error)` function\n2. Cache usage data with TTL (avoid hammering API)\n3. Expose capacity percentage and reset time\n4. Detect 'approaching limit' threshold (e.g., 80%)\n\n## Implementation Notes\n\n- Build on existing `pkg/usage/usage.go` which already fetches from Anthropic API\n- Need to make it account-aware (currently uses whatever auth is active)\n- Cache in memory with ~1 minute TTL\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] Can get usage for any saved account by name\n- [ ] Returns capacity percentage (used/limit)\n- [ ] Returns time until limit resets\n- [ ] Cached to avoid excessive API calls\n- [ ] Unit tests for cache behavior","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-12-20T19:24:20.343487-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-03T14:17:24.153645-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-03T14:17:24.153645-08:00","close_reason":"Abandoned agent from Dec - force closing stale work","labels":["skill:feature-impl","triage:ready"]}
{"id":"orch-go-bdd.2","title":"Add capacity manager for multi-account coordination","description":"## Context\n\nPart of orch-go-bdd: Headless Swarm epic.\nDepends on: orch-go-bdd.1 (usage tracking)\n\n## Task\n\nCreate new `pkg/capacity/` package to coordinate spawning across accounts:\n\n1. `CapacityManager` struct that tracks all accounts\n2. `AcquireSlot() (accountName string, err error)` - get next available account\n3. `ReleaseSlot(accountName string)` - mark agent completed\n4. `Queue()` behavior when all accounts exhausted\n5. Auto-refresh usage when account approaches limit\n\n## Key Design Decisions\n\n- Track 'in-flight' agents per account (not just API usage)\n- Conservative threshold: switch account at 80% capacity\n- Queue with timeout when all accounts busy\n- Emit events for capacity changes (for monitoring)\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] Can acquire slot from least-used account\n- [ ] Queues when all accounts at limit\n- [ ] Auto-switches to fresh account when current exhausted\n- [ ] Thread-safe for concurrent access\n- [ ] Unit tests with mock usage data","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-12-20T19:24:29.418274-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-22T13:40:29.797994-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-22T13:40:29.797994-08:00","close_reason":"Implemented in pkg/capacity/manager.go - AcquireSlot, ReleaseSlot, queue behavior, auto-refresh all working"}
{"id":"orch-go-bdd.3","title":"Add concurrency control to daemon","description":"## Context\n\nPart of orch-go-bdd: Headless Swarm epic.\nDepends on: orch-go-bdd.2 (capacity manager)\n\n## Task\n\nEnhance daemon to spawn agents concurrently with controlled parallelism:\n\n1. Add `--concurrency N` flag to `daemon run`\n2. Use worker pool pattern (N goroutines)\n3. Integrate with CapacityManager for rate-limit awareness\n4. Track active agents and wait for slots\n\n## Implementation Notes\n\n- Use `golang.org/x/sync/errgroup` or similar for worker coordination\n- Each worker: acquire slot → spawn → wait for completion → release slot\n- Respect both concurrency limit AND capacity limits\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `orch daemon run --concurrency 3` spawns up to 3 agents in parallel\n- [ ] Respects rate limits via CapacityManager\n- [ ] Graceful shutdown (wait for active agents)\n- [ ] Progress output shows active/queued/completed counts\n- [ ] Integration test with mock spawner","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-12-20T19:24:37.682484-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-22T16:02:43.775144-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-22T16:02:43.775144-08:00","close_reason":"Added WorkerPool-based concurrency control with --concurrency flag. Pool provides semaphore-based slot acquisition, integrated with Daemon. Tests passing (75.2% coverage)."}
{"id":"orch-go-bdd.4","title":"Add batch spawn command (orch swarm)","description":"## Context\n\nPart of orch-go-bdd: Headless Swarm epic.\nDepends on: orch-go-bdd.3 (concurrent daemon)\n\n## Task\n\nAdd new `orch swarm` command for explicit batch operations:\n\n```bash\n# Spawn from list of issues\norch swarm --issues proj-1,proj-2,proj-3 --concurrency 2\n\n# Spawn all ready issues\norch swarm --ready --concurrency 3\n\n# Spawn with specific skill\norch swarm --skill investigation --issues proj-1,proj-2\n```\n\n## Implementation Notes\n\n- Builds on concurrent daemon infrastructure\n- Focused on explicit batch operations (vs daemon's continuous polling)\n- Returns when all spawned agents complete (or --detach for fire-and-forget)\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] Can spawn list of specific issues concurrently\n- [ ] Can spawn all triage:ready issues\n- [ ] Shows aggregate progress (spawned/active/completed/failed)\n- [ ] Respects rate limits via CapacityManager\n- [ ] `--detach` option for fire-and-forget","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-12-20T19:24:45.912231-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-22T16:20:55.57753-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-22T16:20:55.57753-08:00","close_reason":"Implemented orch swarm command with --issues, --ready, --concurrency, --detach flags. Progress display shows spawned/active/completed/failed. All tests pass."}
{"id":"orch-go-bdd.5","title":"Enhance status command with swarm progress","description":"## Context\n\nPart of orch-go-bdd: Headless Swarm epic.\nCan be done in parallel with other tasks.\n\n## Task\n\nEnhance `orch status` to show aggregate swarm information:\n\n```\n$ orch status\nSWARM STATUS\n  Active:    3/5 (concurrency limit)\n  Queued:    2\n  Completed: 7 (today)\n  \nACCOUNTS\n  personal:  45% used (resets in 2h)\n  work:      12% used (resets in 5h)\n  \nACTIVE AGENTS\n  SESSION ID     BEADS ID    SKILL           ACCOUNT    RUNTIME\n  ses_abc123     proj-1      investigation   personal   5m23s\n  ses_def456     proj-2      feature-impl    personal   2m11s\n  ses_ghi789     proj-3      debugging       work       45s\n```\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] Shows active/queued/completed counts\n- [ ] Shows per-account usage percentages\n- [ ] Shows which account each agent is using\n- [ ] Runtime duration per agent\n- [ ] Works with `--json` for scripting","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-12-20T19:24:56.295463-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-20T23:34:18.736037-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-20T23:34:18.736037-08:00","labels":["skill:feature-impl","triage:ready"]}
{"id":"orch-go-bdd.6","title":"Add SSE-based completion tracking for headless agents","description":"## Context\n\nPart of orch-go-bdd: Headless Swarm epic.\nDepends on: orch-go-bdd.3 (concurrent daemon needs to know when agents complete)\n\n## Task\n\nEnsure headless agents are properly tracked via SSE events:\n\n1. Enhance `CompletionService` to track all headless agents\n2. Emit completion events that CapacityManager can consume\n3. Update registry when headless agents complete\n4. Release capacity slot on completion\n\n## Implementation Notes\n\n- Current `pkg/opencode/service.go` handles SSE monitoring\n- Need to integrate with CapacityManager.ReleaseSlot()\n- Must handle disconnection/reconnection gracefully\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] Headless agent completion triggers slot release\n- [ ] Registry updated on completion\n- [ ] Handles SSE disconnection gracefully\n- [ ] Works with multiple concurrent agents\n- [ ] Logs completion events for debugging","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-12-20T19:25:04.050342-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-22T16:20:56.044592-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-22T16:20:56.044592-08:00","close_reason":"Created CompletionService for SSE-based headless agent completion tracking. Bridges Monitor completion detection with WorkerPool slot management. 13 unit tests pass. Commit da97969."}
{"id":"orch-go-bdfgu","title":"Synthesize spawn investigations (37)","description":"## Synthesis Needed\n\nTopic **spawn** has accumulated 37 investigations that may benefit from consolidation.\n\n### Investigations to synthesize:\n\n- 2025-12-20-inv-add-missing-spawn-flags-no.md\n- 2025-12-20-inv-fix-spawn-use-standalone-mode.md\n- 2025-12-20-research-orch-spawn-vs-opencode-agents.md\n- 2025-12-21-inv-add-concurrency-limit-orch-spawn.md\n- 2025-12-21-inv-phase-evaluate-spawn-session-id.md\n- 2025-12-22-inv-fix-pre-spawn-kb-context.md\n- 2025-12-22-inv-flip-default-spawn-mode-headless.md\n- 2025-12-22-inv-implement-tiered-spawn-protocol-add.md\n- 2025-12-22-inv-orch-spawn-auto-init-if.md\n- 2025-12-22-inv-pre-spawn-kb-context-noise-filtering.md\n- 2025-12-22-inv-spawn-agent-tmux.md\n- 2025-12-22-inv-update-spawn-command-help-text.md\n- 2025-12-23-inv-verify-spawn-works.md\n- 2025-12-24-inv-explore-orch-send-vs-spawn.md\n- 2025-12-24-inv-test-spawn-24dec.md\n- 2025-12-25-inv-pre-spawn-phase-complete-check.md\n- 2025-12-25-inv-pre-spawn-token-estimation-prevent.md\n- 2025-12-26-inv-orch-spawn-remove-fake-interactive.md\n- 2025-12-26-inv-spawn-context-includes-invalid-beads.md\n- 2025-12-26-inv-test-orch-spawn-context.md\n- 2025-12-26-inv-test-spawn-context.md\n- 2026-01-02-inv-test-spawn-works.md\n- 2026-01-03-inv-add-reproduction-section-spawn-context.md\n- 2026-01-03-inv-gate-orch-spawn-issue-beads.md\n- 2026-01-05-debug-orch-spawn-workdir-flag-not.md\n- 2026-01-06-inv-add-friction-orch-spawn-require.md\n- 2026-01-06-inv-proactive-rate-limit-monitoring-spawn.md\n- 2025-12-22-inv-test-spawn-context.md\n- 2025-12-22-inv-test-spawn-tracking-works.md\n- 2025-12-22-inv-test-spawn-verify-investigation-skill.md\n- 2025-12-22-inv-test-spawn-verify-pre-spawn.md\n- 2025-12-22-inv-test-spawn-works-after-phantom.md\n- 2025-12-23-inv-test-spawn-after-fix.md\n- 2025-12-23-inv-test-spawn-fresh-build.md\n- 2025-12-23-inv-test-spawn-functionality.md\n- 2025-12-23-inv-test-spawn.md\n- 2026-01-03-inv-extract-spawn-cmd-go-main.md\n\n### Chronicle Timeline\n\n```\n2025-12-19 [INV] CLI orch complete Command Implementation\n2025-12-19 [INV] CLI orch spawn Command Implementation\n2025-12-19 [INV] CLI Orch Status Command\n2025-12-19 [INV] CLI Project Scaffolding and Build Setup\n2025-12-19 [INV] OpenCode Client Package Session Management\n... (run kb chronicle for full timeline)\n```\n\n### Suggested Action\n\n1. Run `kb chronicle \"spawn\"` to understand evolution\n2. Identify patterns and contradictions across investigations\n3. Create a synthesized decision or consolidated investigation\n","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-07T15:37:21.168868-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-07T21:14:30.02243-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-07T21:14:30.02243-08:00","close_reason":"Synthesized 60 spawn investigations. Guide needs update for ~10 flags and 3 behaviors. Created orch-go-9tg1d for follow-up.","labels":["triage:review"]}
