{"id":"orch-go-be9z9","title":"Change spawn default from opencode to claude backend","description":"Switch default spawn backend from OpenCode API (pay-per-token) to Claude CLI (Max subscription).\n\n## Context\n- Jan 18: $402 API spend discovered, switching to Max subscription for cost control\n- All spawns (manual and daemon) should use Claude CLI by default\n- This trades headless ergonomics for flat-rate pricing\n\n## Changes Required\n1. pkg/spawn/config.go - Change default backend from 'opencode' to 'claude'\n2. Verify daemon spawns work with claude backend (creates tmux windows)\n3. Update CLAUDE.md to reflect new default\n4. Keep --backend opencode as opt-in for when API tracking is implemented\n\n## Test\n- orch spawn feature-impl 'test' should use claude backend without --backend flag\n- Daemon preview should show claude backend","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-01-18T15:00:22.524866-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-18T15:14:52.60021-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-18T15:14:52.60021-08:00","close_reason":"Changed spawn default backend from opencode to claude. Tests: go test ./cmd/orch/... -run TestModelAutoSelection - 5/5 passed. Commit: 0bca3dec. Investigation and SYNTHESIS.md created."}
