{"id":"orch-go-bigrc","title":"Fix kb ask synthesis and grounding","description":"kb ask is failing to synthesize answers even when context exists. This is the root cause of the 'ask command inline' friction (8x gap) identified by orch learn. The tool needs to be more robust in its grounding and synthesis logic.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-01-07T20:32:05.498439-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-07T21:06:45.512442-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-07T21:06:45.512442-08:00","close_reason":"Fixed kb ask synthesis by adding keyword extraction from natural language questions. Root cause was kb context expecting keywords, not sentences. Added extractKeywords() to filter stopwords and runKBContextWithFallback() for progressive query strategies. All tests pass."}
