{"id":"orch-go-blz1p","title":"OpenCode session accumulation leak - 266 active sessions, 129k part files","description":"Impact: orch status shows stale agents, abandoned sessions not removed, visibility degraded. Root cause: OpenCode session lifecycle doesn't match orch abandon expectations. Investigation needed: session storage architecture, cleanup mechanisms. Workaround: Accept noise until proper fix. Related to observability gap being addressed by orch-go-0ydvu.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-01-09T22:04:18.451025-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-11T20:00:25.732703-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-11T20:00:25.732703-08:00","close_reason":"Designed two-tier cleanup strategy: event-based (existing abandon/complete) + periodic background cleanup via daemon extension. Investigation documented with implementation sequence."}
{"id":"orch-go-bmhd","title":"[orch-go] architect: Redesign daemon-managed dev servers with HARD C...","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-12-27T16:38:35.67762-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-27T16:44:37.946209-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-27T16:44:37.946209-08:00","close_reason":"Designed launchd-native dev servers with gen-plist/install commands. Supersedes on-demand health check approach. Servers auto-start via RunAtLoad+KeepAlive like orch daemon."}
{"id":"orch-go-bmho","title":"Glass: empty labels for icon-only buttons","description":"Many buttons return 'label: \"button: \"' with no text content. These are likely icon-only buttons. Could extract aria-label, title attribute, or icon class name to provide meaningful labels.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2025-12-27T19:02:21.673517-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-27T22:34:27.945088-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-27T22:34:27.945088-08:00","close_reason":"Fix implemented in glass repo (9bee9f4), investigation and synthesis committed to orch-go (f1ee381c). Empty labels for icon-only buttons resolved via priority-based fallback chain.","labels":["triage:ready"]}
{"id":"orch-go-bn50","title":"Epic: Agent Detail Pane Redesign - Narrative Tabs","description":"Redesign the agent slide-out pane to tell the full agent lifecycle story through tabs. Current issues: redundant 'current tool' box, reverse chronological feed (should be oldest-top/newest-bottom like Claude Code), no markdown rendering, raw event names shown, no narrative structure.\n\nProposed tabs:\n1. **Issue** - Beads issue details, description, comments (the 'why')\n2. **Context** - SPAWN_CONTEXT.md, spawn params, model (debugging 'what was it told?')\n3. **Activity** - Live feed, Claude Code style (watching work happen)\n4. **Deliverables** - SYNTHESIS.md, commits, artifacts (reviewing output)\n\nActivity tab improvements:\n- Chronological order (oldest top, newest bottom, auto-scroll to bottom)\n- Remove redundant 'current tool' box at top\n- Render markdown in assistant messages\n- Group related events (edit + result as one block)\n- Human-readable labels instead of raw events (step-start, patch, etc.)\n- Collapsible tool details (show summary, expand for full)","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"epic","created_at":"2025-12-30T19:29:38.547709-08:00","updated_at":"2026-01-02T10:20:11.493124-08:00","closed_at":"2026-01-02T10:20:11.493124-08:00","close_reason":"All 5 child issues completed - tab structure, activity feed, deliverables/context/issue tabs implemented"}
{"id":"orch-go-bn50.1","title":"Add tab structure to agent detail pane (Issue/Context/Activity/Deliverables)","description":"Create the tab navigation component for the agent detail slide-out pane. Four tabs:\n- Issue: Show beads issue details\n- Context: Show SPAWN_CONTEXT.md and spawn metadata  \n- Activity: Current live feed (to be improved in separate task)\n- Deliverables: SYNTHESIS.md, commits, artifacts\n\nTab should persist selection, default to Activity for active agents, Deliverables for completed agents.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-12-30T19:29:44.948184-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-31T17:56:33.228333-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-31T17:56:33.228333-08:00","close_reason":"Tab navigation implemented: Issue/Context/Activity/Deliverables with persistence"}
{"id":"orch-go-bn50.2","title":"Improve Activity feed - chronological order, markdown, grouping","description":"Fix the Activity tab feed to match Claude Code/OpenCode style:\n\nCurrent issues:\n- Shows newest at top (should be oldest top, newest bottom)\n- Redundant 'current tool' box duplicates feed content\n- Raw event names (step-start, patch, step-finish) not human-readable\n- No markdown rendering (backticks shown literally)\n- Events not grouped logically\n\nChanges:\n1. Reverse order - chronological, auto-scroll to bottom on new events\n2. Remove 'current tool' box (redundant)\n3. Render markdown in assistant messages\n4. Group related events (edit file + result = one expandable block)\n5. Human-readable labels: 'Edit: path/to/file', 'Run: command', etc.\n6. Collapsible tool details (show summary by default)","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-12-30T19:29:52.57095-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-31T18:27:24.580393-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-31T18:27:24.580393-08:00","close_reason":"Activity feed redesigned with Claude Code style: chronological order with auto-scroll, human-readable labels (Edit: file, Run: command), markdown rendering, expandable event groups, removed redundant current tool box. Implementation verified via screenshots. Investigation committed to .kb/investigations/2025-12-31-inv-improve-activity-feed-agent-detail.md"}
{"id":"orch-go-bn50.3","title":"Implement Deliverables tab - SYNTHESIS viewer, commits, artifacts","description":"Create the Deliverables tab showing agent outputs:\n\nContent:\n- SYNTHESIS.md rendered with markdown (primary view)\n- List of commits made by agent (from git log since spawn time)\n- Links to created artifacts (investigation files, etc.)\n- Delta section highlighting (files modified/created)\n\nFor completed agents, this should be the default tab. Shows the 'what did it produce?' story.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-12-30T19:29:58.952242-08:00","updated_at":"2025-12-31T18:27:13.424144-08:00","closed_at":"2025-12-31T18:27:13.424144-08:00","close_reason":"Implemented /api/agents/deliverables endpoint and updated Deliverables tab to show commits, file delta, and artifacts sections. Go tests pass. Visual verification pending (web changes made)."}
